title: heloise's salt substitute
directions: Combine the ingredients. Use as you would salt.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Cover beans with water; soak overnight.
Drain.
Cover beans with water; simmer until tender.
Add remaining ingredients; pour into casserole.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Add ham or fried bacon in small pieces if desired.

title: raisin nut pie
directions: In bowl, beat eggs slightly.
Stir in corn syrup, brown sugar, butter, vanilla and salt.
Stir in raisins and nuts.

title: crunchy tuna salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except tomato and cucumber.
Refrigerate. Serve with tomato and cucumber.
Makes 4 servings.

title: toffee
directions: Grease cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with 3/4 cup chopped nuts. Cook 12 minutes the butter and brown sugar in a heavy skillet. Pour over nuts.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top.
While chips are still warm, spread with knife.
Sprinkle nuts on top.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Chop beef fine.
Mix cream cheese, milk and sour cream together until smooth.
Add the chopped dried beef and green pepper.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Great on crackers, especially Melba toast or rye thins!

title: easy key lime pie
directions: Chill mixing bowl and then whip cream until stiff.
In another bowl mix milk and lemonade.
With a slotted spoon, fold in whipped cream.
Pour into crust and chill.

title: blintzes
directions: Trim crust from bread; flatten with rolling pin.
Mix cream cheese, egg yolk, sugar and lemon juice.
Spread 1 teaspoon cheese mixture on each piece of flattened bread.
Roll up bread slices. Mix brown sugar and cinnamon.
Dip each roll in melted margarine, then roll in cinnamon mixture.
Place on cookie sheet and cut in half or thirds.
Freeze 3 hours on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: broccoli with basil mushrooms
directions: Cook broccoli spears; drain well.
Melt butter in small saucepan.
Add basil and mushrooms.
Cook and stir until thoroughly heated.
Spoon over broccoli.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine sour cream and soup. Pour over chicken. Crumble Ritz crackers and pour melted butter over the top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry slush
directions: Mix half thawed strawberries and pineapple.
Mix lemonade using only half the water.
Quarter cherries and slice the bananas.
Freeze and thaw to a slush.
Serve mixed with 1 quart of 7-up or Sprite.

title: taco soup
directions: Do not drain anything.
Brown meat with onion.
Simmer for 30 minutes on low.

title: chocolate banana pudding pie
directions: Microwave chocolate, milk and margarine in a medium bowl on High 1 to 1 1/2 minutes, stirring every 30 seconds or until melted. Spread evenly in crust.
Refrigerate 30 minutes until chocolate is firm.
Arrange banana slices over chocolate.
Pour milk and pudding mixes into a large bowl and beat with a wire whisk 1 minute.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Spoon over bananas and then top with Cool Whip. Refrigerate 4 hours until set and must be stored in fridge.

title: spaghetti sauce dip
directions: Mix dry spaghetti sauce mix into sour cream.
Refrigerate. Good to dip chips, pretzels or vegetable sticks.

title: date nut balls
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add sugar, dates and coconut. Cook on medium heat 7 or 8 minutes or until mixed good.
Pour over 4 cups of rice cereal and 2 cups pecans.
Roll in balls.
Roll in confectioners sugar.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Combine all but whip and fold in egg whites and add topping last.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: poor david's soup
directions: Pick over and wash beans.
Cover with water and add a tablespoon of salt.
Soak overnight.
Next day, bring 2 quarts of water to boil; add ham hock.
Drain and rewash beans.
Add to the 2 quarts of boiling water.
Add whole onion, sliced celery and 1/2 teaspoon of salt.
Cook until beans are barely tender.
Add chopped turnip roots and greens, potatoes and carrots.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Scrub and cook the potatoes with skins on until fork-tender. Cool, peel and slice.
Place in casserole.
Bake, basting every 10 minutes for about 1/2 hour.
Bake at 350°.
May add marshmallows for the last 5 to 10 minutes.

title: apple brown betty
directions: Arrange apple slices in baking dish.
Sprinkle with sweetener and cinnamon.
Crumb bread and melt margarine.
Mix bread, oleo and sweetener together to form crumbles.
Sprinkle over apples. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
You may also add 1 ounce grated cheese to bread mix.
This would be 1 breakfast.
Eliminate cheese and it can be a dessert for lunch.

title: ricotta cookies
directions: Mix ingredients.
Flour hands then roll into a long roll about 1 1/2 inches thick.
Pinch off into small balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: hamburger - harvest casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine beef, onions, tomatoes, Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Pat into 1-inch layer in a 3-quart buttered casserole dish.
On top, place in layers, potatoes, flour, corn, limas and then green peppers.
Bake, covered, 45 minutes, then sprinkle with cheese and bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes longer or until vegetables are tender.
Makes 8 servings.
For less, cut recipe in half.

title: german chocolate topping
directions: Dissolve cornstarch in milk. Place cornstarch mixture, sugars, egg yolks, butter and salt in a medium saucepan over medium-low heat. Cook, stirring constantly, until thickens and just starts to bubble, about 7 minutes. Scrape the sides of blender with a rubber spatula and blend several more seconds. Transfer the mixture to a medium-size bowl and stir in the vanilla. Put a piece of plastic wrap over bowl and allow to cool to room temperature. When cool, stir in the nuts and coconut. Makes about 2 cups of topping.

title: rice pudding
directions: Add milk, rice, sugar and salt to a 3-quart saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until tiny bubbles form around the edge of the pan.
Stir mixture frequently.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover; simmer 1 hour or until rice is very tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in vanilla.
Cover and refrigerate until well chilled, about 3 hours.
Whip cream into soft peaks.
Fold cream into pudding with a rubber spatula.
Spoon into dessert dish; sprinkle with nutmeg and/or cinnamon.
Makes 10 servings.

title: real mincemeat pie with whiskey hard sauce
directions: Grind beef and suet (butter) together or chop in food processor.
Chop apples and orange or add to processor using on and off motions.
Combine all ingredients, except pastry in a large pot.
Simmer about 1 hour or until most of the liquid is gone.
Cool.
Prepare pastry for 2 crust pie.
Line a 9 to 10 inch pie pan with bottom crust; fill with cooled mincemeat mixture, top with remaining crust.
Crimp edges and prick top. Bake at 450 degrees for 10 minutes then lower heat to 350 degrees and bake for 30 minutes more.

title: congo squares
directions: Melt margarine and mix with brown sugar until creamy.
Add eggs and flour.
Mix and add morsels and nuts.
Pour in ungreased 9 x 13 pan and bake 50 minutes at 300°.

title: pepper steak
directions: In cup, stir cornstarch and 1/2 cup water; set aside.
Mix sauces with steak.
In skillet, put in 1 tablespoon hot oil. Stir-fry beef in 2 batches until browned.
Remove.
In addition, 2 tablespoons hot oil, stir-fry peppers, onions, mushrooms and tomatoes with ginger, garlic powder and soy sauce until tender and crisp.
Add consomme and cornstarch mixture.
Cook until mixture boils and thickens.
Stir constantly.
Return beef to skillet. Heat thoroughly.
Serve over rice.

title: charcoal-grilled bass
directions: Remove head and fins from cleaned bass, and skin the fish. Melt butter or margarine over low heat, stirring in lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce.
Add Tabasco sauce and simmer for 5 minutes.
Use this as a baste sauce.

title: vegetable cheese soup
directions: Bring water to boil.
Add vegetables.
Return to boil and cook 10 minutes.
Add soup and cheese.
Cook over low heat until hot and blended.
Serve with crusty French bread.
Quick and delicious!

title: cheesy puffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix all ingredients; beat vigorously 1/2 minute.
Fill 12 greased (bottoms only) medium muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Serve warm.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: ten minute salad
directions: A large bowl is needed to mix all ingredients.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix and store.	Can be used a small amount at a time.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Note:
3/4 of 2nd can of French onion soup for top of chicken is enough.

title: peanut oatmeal cookie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll into small balls and bake at 425° for 7 minutes.

title: tab's apple pie
directions: Mix sugars, flour, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Cut in butter. Place apples in a large bowl.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Add sugar mixture, coating apples evenly.
Arrange in pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350°.
Bake for 30 minutes or until apples are tender.
Pour cream over apples carefully.
Bake 10 minutes longer.
Serve warm.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Place chicken parts in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Top each with 1 slice of cheese.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Pour over chicken and cheese.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 1 1/2 hours. Uncover for last 10 minutes.

title: cool and crunchy cole slaw
directions: Combine all ingredients, mix lightly and chill.
Garnish with green pepper rings, if desired.

title: easy chicken cacciatore
directions: Brown chicken in olive oil with garlic.
Before turning chicken, sprinkle with oregano, salt and pepper.
Remove garlic. Add mushrooms; brown lightly.
Add stewed tomatoes; cover.
Simmer 30 minutes; uncover.
Continue cooking until sauce is reduced to desired consistency and chicken is very tender.
Serve with spaghetti.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: date nut torte
directions: Place dates in a bowl, sprinkle with soda and pour on boiling water.
Let stand while preparing other ingredients.
Cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg and corn syrup and mix well.
Add date mixture.
Add flour that has been sifted before measuring and then mix with nuts.
Bake in greased pan in 375° oven for 30 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or hot lemon sauce.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots in salted water; drain.
Combine other ingredients in a pan. Cook until it boils.
Pour over carrots; mix and refrigerate for several days.
Do not cook onion and green pepper.

title: frozen cucumbers
directions: Do not peel cucumbers.
Slice thin.
Soak slices in water to cover with 1 heaping tablespoonful salt added.
Soak for 1 hour. Drain.
Add chopped onion and chopped green pepper.
Mix sugar with vinegar and add celery seed and mustard seed.
Stir until dissolved.
Pour over cucumbers and freeze in plastic containers.

title: pecan sandies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Make into rolls or balls with hand.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and roll in confectioners sugar.

title: martha's company casserole
directions: Grease a large casserole dish.
Cook egg noodles as per directions.
Brown the hamburger and add the onion and pepper and drain.
Mix the cottage cheese, cream cheese and sour cream. First place 1/2 of the noodles in the casserole dish, then layer cheese mixture on top.
Place remainder of noodles over the cheese and then layer the hamburg mixture.
Cover with the tomato sauce and either Mozzarella or Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350°
for 30 to 40 minutes, or until it bubbles.
Very yummy!
Serves 4 to 6.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix flour, cornstarch and sugar.
Add the boiling water, stirring the mixture as water is added.
Stir and cook over low flame 15 minutes.
Put the egg yolks into a bowl and beat them slightly.
Pour a portion of the hot sugar and starch mixture into the egg yolk and mix.
Then return this mixture to the remainder of the sugar and starch mixture and stir and cook over low flame until the egg yolks are thickened.
Remove from the flame; add lemon, butter and salt and mix.
Cover with meringue.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: crawfish eggplant casserole
directions: Fry onion in hot fat.
Add sliced eggplant, chopped bell pepper and celery.
Let simmer, stirring frequently.
Add chopped tails and let cook about 10 minutes.
Mix thoroughly with bread, which has been moistened.
Season to taste.
Place in casserole. Cover with bread crumbs and keep hot in oven until ready to serve.

title: buttermilk rolls
directions: Scald buttermilk.
Add to butter, sugar and salt.
Place in a large bowl.
Cool to warm. Add dissolved yeast and eggs.
Stir in flour mixed with the soda and salt.
Knead.
Grease dough with butter.
Let rise in warm place until double in size.
Knead down. Shape into rolls.
Let rise again until double.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: french onion soup
directions: Saute onions in butter until golden brown. Sprinkle with pepper. Bring bouillon cubes and water to a boil. Add onions and salt. Simmer, covered, for 1 hour.
Place 1 toast round in each soup dish. Pour in soup and sprinkle with cheese.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sweet ricotta puffs(sfingi)
directions: From a family friend, Anna.

title: graham cracker pie crust
directions: In plastic bag, finely roll graham crackers (about 1 2/3 cups crumbs).
Combine crumbs, sugar and butter or margarine.
Blend well with fork or pastry blender.
Using back of large spoon, press crumb mixture inside 9-inch pie plate to coat bottom and sides evenly.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Set on wire rack to cool.
For no-bake crust, chill in refrigerator 30 minutes before using.
Fill with your favorite chilled pie filling or freeze for ice cream pie.

title: barbecue pork with sauce
directions: Cook pork loin at 375°.
Insert meat thermometer.
Place pork loin in brown and cook bag.
Cook until meat thermometer reaches desired temperature for pork.
(Look on thermometer for pork indicator.)
Be sure pork is completely thawed prior to cooking. After pork is completely done, allow to cool and remove fat. Slice and place in food processor to grind meat to small pieces.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, nutmeg and creamed butter.
Beat in the baking powder and wine.
Add flour; mix dough well.

title: dutch oven potatoes deluxe
directions: Follow directions for Dutch Oven potatoes, however, add another can of
cream
of mushroom soup mix and delete the can of cheese
soup.
As you layer the potatoes, also sprinkle the desired amount
of sausage, ham or hamburger.
Follow the rest of the directions.

title: hamburger quiche
directions: Brown ground beef and pour off grease.
Combine eggs, milk, onion, salt and pepper.
Beat well.
Add 1 cup cheese to mixture. Layer 1/2 of remaining cheese on bottom of pie shell.
Pour ground beef over cheese, then pour egg mixture over ground beef.
Add remaining cheese to top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Grease 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Put crackers on bottom; add 1/2 of the asparagus, 1/2 the egg sliced, 1/2 grated cheese and 1/2 of the mixed soup and liquid.
Repeat.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: rainbow finger paints
directions: In small saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Cook over medium heat until thickened and smooth, stirring constantly, with wire whisk.
Cool finger paints to room temperature, about 10 minutes. Stir before painting.
Makes 1/2 cup.

title: ham rolls
directions: Dry ham slices on towels.
This is very important.
Add Italian dressing mix to softened cream cheese, mixing well. Spread on dried ham slices, making sure you go to the edges.
Roll up as you would a jellyroll and chill.
Slice into 5 equal pieces per roll.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: lite chicken marengo
directions: Heat large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat until hot. Add oil; heat until it ripples.
Add chicken breasts; brown on all sides.
In medium bowl, combine flour, basil, garlic, pepper, wine and tomato paste; blend until smooth.
Stir in tomatoes.
Move chicken to side of skillet; add tomato mixture.
Place chicken in tomato mixture, skin side up.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium-low; cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Turn chicken over; stir in pepper and onion.
Cover; cook an additional 8 to 10 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender.
Stir occasionally.
Stir in olives.
Makes 4 servings.
Serve over buttered noodles.
One serving contains 260 calories and 8 g. fat.

title: strawberry banana salad(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add fruits, Cool Whip and nuts.
Pour into mold and chill until firm.

title: turnip greens or mustard
directions: Pick and wash greens.
Wash well in warm water twice, then in cool water as many times as needed.
Cook in boiling water with bacon or bacon grease and salt until tender, about 1 hour.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream the butter, shortening and cream cheese and gradually add sugar; beat at medium speed.
Add eggs one at a time; beat between each.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Add to mixture and stir just enough to blend.
Add coconut, vanilla and coconut flavoring; stir to blend.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan; pour in cake mixture and bake in a preheated 320° oven for about 1 1/2 hours.
Cool 15 minutes in pan.
Check with toothpick when done.

title: quiche
directions: Grease pie plate, sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion in plate. Beat remaining ingredients together until smooth.
Pour into plate.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for about 40 minutes until knife comes out clean.
Serves 6.

title: queets' frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix fruit, nuts, sugar and sour cream together.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Freeze.
Put out 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: key lime pie
directions: Blend condensed milk, lime juice and grated peel. Add egg yolks and extra egg. Blend well. Pour into crust. Beat egg whites until stiff (but not dry), gradually adding sugar and beating constantly. Swirl meringue over filling. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Chill and decorate before serving.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar together, then add berries and apple butter.
Add the unbeaten eggs and add buttermilk with the soda mixture and beat well.
Add the spices.
Bake in a 350° oven until toothpick comes out clean; bake in a long bread pan (makes a big cake).

title: chicken crescent rolls
directions: Mix chicken with soup and cheese; mix well.
Place 1 heaping tablespoonful on unrolled Pillsbury crescent roll.
Roll up and press each end down.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: blackberry cobbler(makes 4 servings)
directions: In saucepan, combine 3/4 cup sugar and the cornstarch until well blended.
Gradually add water and cook and stir until boiling; boil 1 minute.
Add berries.
Pour into greased
1 1/2-quart casserole and dot with butter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: tunnel of fudge cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Use 10-inch tube pan.
Cream butter in large mixing bowl at high speed.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Gradually add sugar, continue creaming at high speed until light and fluffy.
By hand, stir in flour, dry frosting mix and walnuts until well blended.
Pour batter into 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes.
Cool 2 hours, remove and cool completely before serving.

title: spicy meat balls
directions: You will also need 1 (14 x 20-inch) Brown-in-Bag.

title: chowning's tavern brunswick stew
directions: Cut chicken in pieces and simmer in 2 or 3 quarts water for 2 1/4 hours.
Remove chicken; add vegetables to broth and simmer, uncovered, until beans and potatoes are tender.
Stir to prevent scorching.
Add chicken (boned and diced) and seasonings. Brunswick Stew is better if made a day ahead and allowed to stand in refrigerator overnight in order for flavors to blend.
Serve with a salad and chunks of bread and butter.

title: spinach salad
directions: Chill and serve fresh.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Sprinkle vinegar over zucchini and let set while getting pie dough ready and rolled out.
Mix rest of ingredients together, then mix with zucchini and pour into unbaked crust.
Put on top crust.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes at 350° or until done.
Has a taste similar to mincemeat pie.

title: baked yams
directions: Bake yams until soft.
I wrap them in foil, then when done remove foil and peel.
Put in large bowl and mash real well.
Add brown sugar and oleo to taste.
Add marshmallows on top and brown. (Yams are better than sweet potatoes.)

title: beef stew with mashed potatoes
directions: Brown meat thoroughly on all sides (30 minutes) in heavy saucepan (3-quart).
Add all ingredients except vegetables. Cover tightly.
Cook 2 hours or until tender.
Cook vegetables separately or cook with meat and liquid at this time. Finish cooking and serve over mashed potatoes.
If you wish to thicken the stew, which I do, slowly stir in 1/2 cup water and 1/4 cup flour which have been shaken in a jar.
Bring to a boil and boil 1 minute. Taste, season and serve.

title: lime icebox pie
directions: Make a syrup (don't congeal) with sugar, hot water, jello, and lemon juice.
Fold in 1 large can evaporated milk.
Pour into pie crust and chill.
Can use graham crackers around the sides and bottom of pie dish to take place of crust.

title: zucchini lemon bars
directions: In medium bowl, combine eggs, sugar, oil, lemon juice and rind.
Beat by hand until well blended.
Add zucchini; mix well. Sift together the dry ingredients and stir into zucchini mixture. Fold in nuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 13 x 2 pan.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Cool in pan and cut into bars.
Serve.

title: tzatziki(cucumber and yogurt dip)
directions: Whisk the olive oil, vinegar, garlic and yogurt together. Season with salt and pepper. Fold the cucumber and mint into the mixture. Season with salt and pepper. Cover and refrigerate until chilled. Serve with black olives and slices of toasted pita bread. Yield: About 2 1/2 cups.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Combine cream cheese, eggs and 1/3 cup sugar and beat well. Add chocolate chips and set this mixture aside.
In another bowl, mix together flour, 1 1/2 cups sugar and cocoa.
Add water, oil, vinegar and vanilla and beat well.
Grease muffin tins and line with papers.
Fill 1/3 full with chocolate mixture, then add 1 teaspoon cream cheese (mixture) in center.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Frost if desired.
Suitable for freezing.

title: baked cheddar potato slices
directions: Mix soup, sour cream and pepper to taste. In greased oblong baking dish, arrange potato slices in overlapping rows. Sprinkle with cheese. Add soup mixture. Bake at 400° covered with foil for 45 minutes. Uncover; bake 10 minutes more.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine and cook over low heat until thick.
Cool.
Pour into cooked crust.
Top with meringue with 3 egg whites.

title: green bean bake
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, mix soup and milk.
Add beans and 1/2 of the onions to the soup mixture.
Sprinkle remaining onions on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream oil and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift flour, salt and soda. Add dry ingredients.
Add vanilla, nuts and apples.
Stir in apples and nuts by hand.
Bake approximately 1 hour at 325°.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix broccoli and cheese in large bowl.
In another bowl, pour vinegar over onion.
Let stand a few minutes.
Add mayonnaise and sugar; mix well and pour over broccoli mixture.

title: golden peanut brittle
directions: Spread peanuts evenly in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jellyroll pan; bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Set aside.
Combine soda and salt; set aside.
Combine sugar, syrup and water in a Dutch oven; cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, until mixture reaches soft crack stage (275°).
Add peanuts; cook, stirring constantly, until mixture reaches hard crack stage (300°).
Remove from heat; stir in butter and soda mixture.
Working rapidly, spread mixture thinly onto 2 buttered 15 x 10 x 1-inch jellyroll pans.
Let cool; break into pieces.
Yield:
About 2 1/2 pounds.

title: blueberry buckle
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg and milk and beat well.
Add sifted flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir until blended.
Add blueberries.
Spread into 9 x 13-inch pan (greased).

title: 7-up salad
directions: Drain pineapple. Add enough water to juice to make 1 cup liquid and bring to a boil.
Pour into blender and add gelatin and cheese.
Blend on medium speed about 2 minutes.
Add sugar, vanilla and 7-Up.
Blend on high speed 1 minute.
Add pineapple and mix 1 minute on low speed.
Pour into mold and chill in refrigerator about 5 hours.
Makes 6 servings.

title: seasonal squash medley
directions: Peel, seed and dice squash.
Blanch in boiling, salted water and chill.
Melt butter in a large skillet; melt sugar in butter. Add squash and seasonings; saute until tender.
Deglaze with Marsala; reduce to glaze consistency.
Serves 10.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Beat well.
Bake in a greased pie pan for about 30 minutes at 400°.

title: peanut butter chocolate chip cookies
directions: In small bowl combine oats, flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
In large bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat margarine and peanut butter until smooth.
Beat in sugars until blended.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour mixture.
Beat until well blended, also add in chocolate chips (however many you want!).
Drop by spoon on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes or so.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Mix chicken broth and soup in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Add meat, eggs and vegetables.
Set aside.
Mix butter, milk and flour together.
Lightly stir but do not beat.
(Mixture will be lumpy.) Pour on top of chicken mixture.
Do not stir.
Cook in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until brown.
Serves 6.

title: water cake
directions: Cream well shortening and sugar.
Blend eggs one at a time; set aside.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Combine water and vanilla.
Add alternately to creamed mixture beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Blend thoroughly after each addition with mixer on low speed.

title: banana-nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour bottom of loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inches.
Combine first six ingredients in large bowl.
Add baking mix and pecans, stirring just until blended.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes.
Loosen sides of loaf from pan.
Remove from pan.
Cool completely before slicing.

title: low calorie white sauce
directions: Combine water, dry milk, flour and salt in saucepan and boil until it thickens.
Add 3 drops of butter flavor.
For variation, add 1/4 cup sharp cheese.
Serve on your favorite vegetables.

title: evelyn's 60 - minute roll
directions: In a large bowl, mix 1 1/2 cups flour, sugar, salt, and yeast.
Combine milk, water, and margarine in a pan and heat to 120 degrees.
(Margarine does not need to melt.)
Gradually add to dry ingredients and beat 2 minutes by mixer.
Add 1/2 cup flour and beat again.
Stir in enough flour to make a soft dough.
Turn out on a floured surface and knead for 5 minutes or until smooth. Place in a greased bowl turning to grease the top.
Cover and place bowl in pan of warm (92 degree) water.
Let rise 15 minutes. Punch down and make into rolls.
Cover and let rise in warm place 15 minutes.
Bake at 400 degrees for 12 minutes or until done.

title: buffalo chips(chocolate chip cookies)
directions: Blend oleo, brown sugar and white sugar together.
Stir in eggs (be sure oleo is cooled), vanilla, oats and corn flakes.
In a separate bowl, mix flour, baking soda and baking powder. Gradually add flour mixture to other ingredients.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts and mix well.
Use an ice cream scoop to put dough on a very large cookie sheet, about 6 cookies to a sheet.
Bake at 325° on top rack.
Makes about 36 cookies.

title: old fashioned butter crunch
directions: Spread almonds in shallow pan.
Toast in 350° oven until golden.
Melt butter or margarine in large heavy saucepan; add sugar, corn syrup and water.
Cook, stirring often, to hard-crack stage (300° on candy thermometer).
Remove from heat; stir in 1 cup almonds.
Pour quickly into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan; cool completely. When set, turn out in one pieces onto wax paper.
Spread half of the melted chocolate over top.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup almonds; let set.
Turn candy over.
Spread with remaining chocolate.
Sprinkle with remaining almonds.
Let stand until chocolate sets.
Break into pieces.

title: mexican crock-pot(makes 12 servings.  prep time:  1 hour.)
directions: Brown ground beef and sausage together and drain.
Place meat in crock-pot and mix in Ro-Tel tomatoes, mushroom soup and taco sauce or salsa. Cut cheese into small pieces and add to mixture. Heat on low until cheese melts.
Serve over tortilla chips.

title: cheeseburger loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients into meat, except cheese.
Put half of mixture into a loaf pan.
Put 2 slices of cheese on top.
Layer rest of meat mixture, then other 2 slices of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
Allow loaf to cool for 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: apple walnut cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish or pan.
In saucepan, heat sugar and water until sugar melts. Cut shortening into flour until particles are like fine crumbs. Add milk and stir until dough leaves side of bowl.
Turn on floured surface and knead until smooth.
Roll dough into a large rectangle about 1/4-inch thick.
Spread apples on dough and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Roll up like a jelly roll.
Slice dough into approximately 16 slices, 1/2-inch thick.
Place slices, cut side up, in pan with melted butter.
Pour sugar syrup carefully around rolls.
(This looks like too much liquid, but the crust will absorb it.)
Bake for 45 minutes or until apples are done.

title: rhubarb bread
directions: Combine sugar with margarine for topping and set aside.
Heat oven to 325°.
Grease the bottom of two 8 x 4 inch loaf pans. Combine brown sugar, buttermilk, oil and eggs, and blend until smooth.
Add the flour and mix well.
Stir in the rhubarb and the nuts.
Pour into pans.
Sprinkle with a topping of 1/2 c. sugar mixed with 1 Tbsp. margarine.
Bake for 50-60 minutes, or until bread tests done.
Cool in pan 10 minutes then remove to wire rack and cool completely.

title: elbert's 9 day slaw
directions: Bring to a boil.
Pour over other ingredients.
Let stand 4 hours before serving.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Heat oil in a skillet and brown the chicken.
Set aside the chicken and spoon off fat.
In skillet, combine soup, milk, lemon juice and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Return chicken to skillet and cover and cook for 10 minutes over low heat.
Serves 4.

title: crisp onion potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Blend all ingredients except potatoes in shallow baking dish.
Add potatoes; turn to coat thoroughly. Bake, stirring potatoes occasionally, for 60 minutes or until potatoes are tender and crispy brown.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley.

title: autumn apple punch
directions: Place apple juice in non-aluminum pan.
Tie spices in cheesecloth and simmer together, uncovered, 15 minutes.
Discard spice bag.
Mix with remaining fruit juices.
When serving, add ginger ale.
Float ice ring.
Serves 25.

title: hamburger bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, drain.
Add onion soup, catsup, Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco sauce and salt.
Add red beans.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: microwave bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumber into 1/4-inch rounds (2 cups).
Slice onion in thin rounds (3/4 cup).
Mix all ingredients in a 2-quart microwave soft bowl.
Microwave on High for 7 or 8 minutes, stopping to stir twice until cucumbers are crisp-tender and onion is translucent. Ladle into glass jar (rinsed with hot water).
Cover; cool slightly.
Refrigerate.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: brownies
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add sifted ingredients.
Alternate with melted butter.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes in 9 x 12-inch pan, greased and floured.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar while hot.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix flour, butter and powdered sugar.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients thoroughly and pour on top of crust.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut while warm.

title: spicy chicken with broccoli
directions: Toss chicken with cornstarch, salt and pepper. Refrigerate 20 minutes. Boil broccoli pieces in water 1 minute. Drain.
Cut green onions and chili into thin slices.
Heat oil in wok or heavy skillet. Add vegetables, onions, chili, brown bean sauce, garlic, sugar and ginger root.
Stir a few seconds. Add chicken. Stir-fry 2 minutes until chicken is white and well cooked. Serve with rice or noodles.

title: chicken ala sam
directions: Cook green pepper until tender in the oleo in a saucepan.
Add soup, noodles and chicken.
Mix well.
Cook over low heat, about 10 minutes.
Garnish with green pepper rings and additional chicken.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together and fry until golden brown using a large tablespoon to measure.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Dissolve Baker's chocolate in 1/4 cup boiling water.
Beat egg yolks and whites separately.
Measure flour before sifting. Dissolve soda in 1/4 cup boiling water. Cream the shortening and sugar. Add egg yolks, then chocolate.
Add buttermilk alternately with flour and vanilla.
Add soda.
Fold in beaten egg whites last.
Bake in a 350° oven in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan for 30 or 35 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together well.
With wax paper, form mixture into a ball.
Set aside.
Finely chop the beef.
Roll cheese ball in chopped beef, completely covering ball.
Cover well and refrigerate overnight.
Garnish with parsley or celery flakes. Serve at room temperature with crackers.

title: holiday potatoes
directions: Mash hot potatoes.
Add cream cheese, onion, butter and salt. Beat until dissolved.
Add sour cream.
Beat eggs and add to milk. Add to potatoes and beat well.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours or overnight in greased casserole.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: burrito casserole
directions: Brown meat with onions and garlic.
Add next 4 ingredients; mix well and simmer 10 minutes.
Layer tortillas, sour cream and cheese in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Repeat layers and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: walnut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into unbaked 9-inch pie crust.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes or until firm in center.

title: sunkist lemon bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix 1 egg, oleo and cake mix (dry) until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup.
Pat remaining mixture lightly in ungreased oblong pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Bake about 15 minutes or until light brown.
Beat 2 eggs, sugar, baking powder, salt, lemon peel and lemon juice with mixer until light and foamy.
Pour over hot crust.
Sprinkle with reserved crumb mixture.
Bake about 15 more minutes or until light brown.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: cajun dirty rice
directions: Bring to a boil; cover and simmer until tender.
Add 1/2 pound sausage, browned and drained.

title: pasta house salad
directions: Mix olive oil, red wine vinegar and parmesan cheese.
Chill dressing for at least one hour.
Slice onions and artichoke hearts.
Mix with lettuce and pimentos in a large salad bowl. Toss salad with dressing and serve immediately.

title: little pizzas
directions: Get some muffins.
Then, get some pizza sauce and cheese. Spread the sauce around and put the cheese on.
Put it on a pan. Put it in the oven at 5°.
Cook for 6 hours.
The look delicious and taste good.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Place in refrigerator to chill.
Put cherries in ice trays; fill with punch.
Freeze and use as garnish when punch is served.

title: 7-layer cookie bars
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over butter. Add remaining ingredients in this order: coconut, chocolate chips, butterscotch chips and nuts. Spread layer of milk over all. Bake 25 minutes (no longer) at 350°.
Cool and cut in bars. Makes about 15 bars.

title: good salad dressing
directions: Beat eggs, then add sugar, salt, vinegar, butter, pepper and mustard.
Cook until thickened and clear.
Makes 1 cup.
Can be used to coat lettuce leaves or used cold in place of mayonnaise for salads.

title: onion mushroom meatballs
directions: Mix onion soup mix with ground chuck; form into small meatballs.
Brown meatballs in deep frypan.
Reduce heat.
Spoon mushroom soup (undiluted) into pan, covering meatballs.
Add 1/4 cup water; cover tightly.
Cook and stir until soup forms gravy. Serve over noodles or canned potatoes.
Serves 4.

title: texas chocolate sheet cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix flour and sugar in a large bowl.
Mix water, cocoa, shortening and margarine in a small saucepan.
Bring to a boil and stir until smooth.
Add to flour-sugar mixture and stir until smooth.
Add buttermilk, baking soda, salt, eggs and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes.
Bake in a greased 11 x 18-inch pan for 20 minutes at 350°.
Save saucepan and bowl for frosting.
Do not wash.
Leave cake in pan.

title: golden hush puppies
directions: Combine corn meal and onion.
Add milk and egg, stirring well. Carefully drop batter by tablespoonfuls into deep hot oil (370°). Cook only a few at a time, turning once.
Fry until hush puppies are golden brown, 3 to 5 minutes.
Drain well on absorbent towels. Yields about 2 dozen.

title: watergate cake
directions: Mix cake according to box directions.
Add pudding mix.
Bake at 350° in a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: weight watchers vegetable soup
directions: Combine all ingredients, except parsley and pepper.
Stir to dissolve broth mix.
Cover with plastic wrap; vent one corner. Microwave on High 17 minutes, stirring halfway through cooking time.
Remove bay leaf.
Add parsley and pepper.

title: lobster stuffed potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cut baked potatoes in half lengthwise and carefully scoop out insides, reserving skins.
In a bowl, mash potatoes, add butter, sour cream, onion and pepper.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in lobster meat and mushrooms and place mixture in the 12 potato skins.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and place on a baking sheet.
Bake 15 - 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: veg-all beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles until tender.
Drain.
Lightly brown onion in butter.
Add ground beef and cook until brown.
Drain.
Blend in flour.
Add cooked noodles, Veg-All with liquid, tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Pour into a baking dish and bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: oriental shrimp
directions: Combine all ingredients and marinate 1 to 2 days in refrigerator.
Drain shrimp and reserve marinade.
Grill 4 to 6 minutes total, basting with marinade.
Serve with Mr.
Mustard.

title: mom's pasta salad
directions: Boil pasta to tender.
Crumble Feta cheese and mix with sliced olives and defrosted spinach.
Add pasta (drained and rinse with cool water).
Toss with Greek dressing.
Refrigerate and serve cold.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream together sugars and Crisco.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: strawberry yogurt shake
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender; cover and blend until smooth.
Pour into glasses and garnish with a fresh strawberry if desired.
Serve immediately.
Quick and easy drink that is cooling and easy to prepare.

title: cherry crunch
directions: In a 9 x 13 dish, smooth cherry pie filling over the bottom. Then add pineapple over cherries. Sprinkle sugar over the pineapple. Smooth cake mix over the sugar. Pour melted butter over the cake mix. Then top with pecans. Bake at 350° about 45 minutes or until brown.

title: 4 bean salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Marinate for several hours before serving.

title: easy jello salad
directions: Sprinkle dry jello powder over cottage cheese and mix. Combine with rest of ingredients.

title: a & w style chili sauce
directions: Brown beef.
Combine and simmer 4 hours.

title: brown bread
directions: Combine dry
ingredients
in a large bowl; add molasses and buttermilk, mixing well.
Stir in raisins.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix together with fork.
Preheat iron skillet with a little oil in it at 450°.
Pour mixture into hot skillet.
Cook until golden brown, about 10 minutes.

title: church slaw
directions: Mix together and pour over shredded cabbage.
Store in refrigerator.
Will keep indefinitely.

title: marvelous margaritas
directions: Combine the ingredients in a blender and fill the space that remains with ice.
Blend at low speed until desired consistency.

title: graham cracker pralines
directions: Place crackers on a cookie sheet.
Bring butter, sugar and salt to a boil; boil for 2 minutes.
Add nuts.
Spoon over crackers while hot.
Bake for 10 minutes at 325°.

title: coconut-apple crisp
directions: Mix butter, sugar, flour and coconut together.
Press in 9-inch pan (saving some for topping) in bottom and up a little on the sides.
Pour pie filling on crust.
Add remaining crumbs for topping.
I sprinkle a little extra coconut on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve with a dollop of ice cream.
Yum, yum!

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add beaten eggs.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Pour in pie shells (unbaked).
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes or until center is firm.
Delicious with whipped cream!

title: shrimp spread or dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and serve with assorted crackers and chips.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Grease sides and bottom of pan.
Reserve 2/3 cup cake mix and then combine remaining mix, butter and 1 egg.
Press into pan thinly and bake 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Combine remaining mix (2/3 cup), 3 eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Mix well and pour over the browned crust.
Sprinkle on nuts and bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Drain.
Arrange crosswise in 13 x 9 x 2-inch (3-quart) baking dish.
Melt butter; add flour, broth and cream.
Cook until thick.
Stir in cheese and sherry and salt. Pour half of the sauce on broccoli.
Arrange chicken slices on top of broccoli, then pour on the remaining sauce.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350° or until hot, then broil just until sauce browns.
Trim with sliced peaches.
Can be made a day ahead of time and refrigerated until ready to use.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix margarine with potatoes.
In separate bowl mix sour cream, onion, soup,
cheese,
salt
and
pepper.
Combine with potatoes and
put
in
a 3-quart casserole dish.
Drizzle with margarine. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: peanut butter crunch
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to rolling boil.
Add peanut butter, cereal and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoonful on waxed paper.
Let cool.

title: great grandma's mija pie
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar, cinnamon and rolled or crushed graham crackers (save 1 cup for topping).
Press into a pie crust pan. Cook at 350° for 8 minutes.
Cool.
Add capful of vanilla to prepared pudding and pour into cooled pie crust.
Top pudding with graham cracker mixture and crushed Heath bar pieces.
Enjoy.

title: mahi mahi
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender, except the mahi mahi.
Pour mixture over fish in shallow pan.
Cover and put in refrigerator for 2 to 3 hours.
Either grill on an outside grill or broil in oven until meat is tender.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Soften yeast in warm water in a large bowl.
Add salt and sugar.
Mix in flour; knead to make a soft, smooth dough.
Do not let rise.
Cut immediately into smaller pieces.
Roll into ropes and form pretzel shapes.
Place on cookie sheets covered with foil and dusted with flour.
Brush pretzels with beaten egg and sprinkle with coarse salt.
Bake 15 minutes or until light brown.
Serve warm or cold.
Plain or with mustard or cheese sauce.
Makes 3 to 6 dozen.

title: unusual banana bread(diabetic)
directions: Beat eggs and flavorings together.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into a 1-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
May be baked in muffin tins, if desired.
Yields 2 servings.

title: breakfast hot dish
directions: Place croutons in dish; top with cheese.
Cook sausage; drain. Put on top of cheese.
Mix eggs, mustard, milk, mushrooms and soup; pour over sausage.
May be refrigerated overnight and reheated.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: sticky bread
directions: Melt butter in a sauce pan over low heat.
Stir in 1 tablespoon cinnamon, remove from heat.
In a large Ziploc bag, combine 1 tablespoon cinnamon, nutmeg, and sugar.
Set aside.
Cut each biscuit into 4 sections.
Drop sections into bag - coat. Layer coated biscuits in a Bundt pan.
Pour melted butter mixture over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 15-20 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Break chocolate into small pieces; mix with sugar, corn syrup, salt and cream.
Cook until soft ball stage, about 235° on a candy thermometer.
Remove from heat; add butter without stirring. Allow to cool until lukewarm; add vanilla and beat until thick.

title: spicy fried chicken
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Add chicken pieces, turning to coat.
Cover and refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.
Drain chicken, discarding buttermilk mixture.

title: venison jerky
directions: Cut venison in very thin strips.
Marinate the meat for 17 hours in the refrigerator.
Drain the meat and bake at 150° for 5 hours.
Drain the cookie sheets and turn the meat occasionally.

title: dump cake
directions: Bake until it turns brown.
Layer each item.
Don't mix.
Melt butter in pan first.

title: linguini salad
directions: Mix and marinate overnight.
Must be made a day ahead.

title: toffee bars
directions: Spray cookie sheet with "Pam."
Cover cookie sheet with a layer of graham crackers.
Boil together for 3 minutes brown sugar and butter.
Remove from stove and add chopped nuts.
Pour mixture over graham crackers.
Bake 10 minutes (only) at 325°.
Cool and crack apart.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve both packages of Jell-O with 2 cups of boiling water. Put in frozen strawberries and stir.
When strawberries are melted, add cherry pie filling.
Refrigerate.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Melt butter or margarine in large saucepan.
Saute onion and celery for 4 to 5 minutes.
Add vegetables along with chicken broth.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Simmer 15 to 25 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Blend flour and salt with a small amount of milk to make a smooth paste.
Add remaining milk and flour mixture to soup mixture.
Heat just to simmer. Stir to keep smooth and thick.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Keep warm on low heat.
Do not boil.
Soup will curdle.

title: cracker spread
directions: Mix in blender or mixer; chill.

title: egg custard no-knead rolls
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Add melted butter, salt and custard mix.
Add flour gradually and mix until mixture forms a ball.
Knead 12 times on lightly floured surface.
Roll dough to form 8 x 20-inch rectangle.
Cut in half lengthwise.
Cut each 4 x 20-inch piece of dough into 2 x 4-inch rectangles.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Cover and let rise in warm place for 1 hour or until doubled in bulk. Bake 10 to 15 minutes in 400° oven.

title: grandmother's sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening until light.
Add egg and milk and blend well.
Sift all dry ingredients and add to first mixture. Add flavoring and mix well.
Roll out 1/8-inch thick on floured board and cut with cookie cutter.
Sprinkle with plain or red sugar.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350°
until light brown. Great recipe for Christmas cookies, decorate with frosting, etc.

title: pineapple cheese pie
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Whip cream cheese and sugar together well.
Fold in whipped cream.
Add pineapple.
Spoon into filling into pie shell.
It's easy and good.

title: lite pie
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water. Add yogurt and mix thoroughly. Then add Cool Whip. Pour into crust. Refrigerate for several hours or overnight. Serve and enjoy.

title: baked beans
directions: Dice onion.
Chop bell pepper.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake in casserole dish at 400° for approximately 45 minutes.
Hint: Brown bacon on the stove and add to dish about 20 minutes before done.

title: grilled salmon steaks
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in shallow pan.
Add salmon or Lake Trout; marinate for 1 hour in refrigerator, turning 2 or 3 times.
Grill 5 to 8 minutes per side over medium-hot briquets or medium on gas grill.
Fish must flake when tested by a fork. Serve with lemon wedges and butter, if desired.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Pour ingredients in ice cream freezer and freeze.

title: bob's manhattan clam chowder(makes 6 servings)
directions: Open clams over a large bowl to catch the juice.
Add juice to a large pot and add the remaining ingredients.
Cook all ingredients for 1 hour and 15 minutes, then add diced clams and cook 15 minutes.
Serve.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well. Chill. Roll in 1 cup chopped pecans.

title: cheese puff pastry
directions: Combine flour, butter and sour cream in a bowl and mix. Divide into 4 portions. Wrap and chill. Roll out one at a time onto a floured surface to 12 x 6-inch rectangle.
Sprinkle each with seasoned salt and pepper, then with 3/4 cup cheese.
Roll up into a long roll about 2-inches wide.
Seal edge and ends.
Place seam side down onto ungreased baking sheet.
Make diagonal slits at 1-inch intervals.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cut into strips.
Serve hot.
(Can be made ahead and frozen.)

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix nuts and coconut; spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake mix according to directions; pour cake mix over coconut and nuts. Mix margarine and cream cheese on top of stove.
Mix sugar, margarine and cheese.
Pour cake mix as even as possible.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cake will crack open.

title: whip cream icing
directions: Cook flour and milk until thick.
Add oleo and cool completely.
Add Crisco, white sugar and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: microwave quick fudge
directions: Blend powdered sugar, cocoa and milk.
Cut butter or oleo on top.
Mix well.
Heat in microwave 2 minutes at Full power or until butter is melted.
Add vanilla and nuts; mix well.
Pour into buttered pan and chill.

title: mock oil down
directions: Grate coconut in blender with water.
Place chicken and onion in bottom of large pot.
Top with potatoes.
Pour coconut water through a strainer into pot to 1 inch below tops of potatoes.
If needed, add more water to blender and strain again until enough water is obtained.
Add spices.
Boil dry until chicken beings to fry.
Serves 8.

title: english toffee
directions: Place first 4 ingredients in a saucepan and cook until brown (about 15 minutes), stirring all the time to prevent burning. Pour into a buttered pan (cookie sheet or 9 x 13-inch pan).
Lay Hershey bars on hot mass and spread.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Cool and break in pieces.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine all ingredients well in container
of
electric blender; process
until smooth.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: chicken stir-fry whip-up
directions: Cook chicken breasts in Miracle Whip in large skillet on medium-high heat for 3 minutes.
Add vegetables.
Stir soy sauce and garlic powder into mixture.
Continue cooking 5 minutes or until the chicken is cooked through.
Serve over rice if desired.

title: good tuna and potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salted water for 10 minutes.
Drain. Melt butter in top of double boiler over direct heat.
Stir in flour, then mustard.
Add milk, salt and pepper and stir over boiling water until smooth and thickened.
Arrange potatoes, tuna and onions in alternate layers in greased 2-quart casserole.

title: peanut butter cookies, too
directions: Cream butter or shortening with peanut butter; add sugars and cream again until mixture is light and fluffy.

title: crab meat dip(microwave)
directions: Combine the onion and margarine in a microwave-safe dish. Microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Stir in the cheese.
Microwave for 1 to 2 minutes or until the cheese is melted, stirring occasionally.
Add the crab meat and soup.
Microwave for 3 to 4 minutes or until heated through, stirring occasionally.
Yields 16 servings.

title: rhubarb bars
directions: Pat 3/4 of crumbly mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour in rhubarb mixture and sprinkle remaining crumbs over the top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: angel trifle with ding dongs
directions: 1 layer Angel food cake

title: peppermint bark
directions: Put peppermint candy in a bag and crush into small pieces. Put almond bark in microwave cooker around the edges and microwave for 6 minutes on 50% power. Check every 2 minutes. Be ready to immediately stir peppermint in and then pour on to wax paper or baking mat.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in pan in oven.
Mix other ingredients.
Pour batter in pan.
Pour fruit over batter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake at 350° to 40 to 45 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and sugar.
Mix well.
In a separate bowl, combine eggs and oil.
Fold into dry ingredients.
Stir in pecans.
Fold in strawberries until moistened.
Pour in a greased and floured Bundt pan or two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° or until lightly browned, approximately 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool completely before slicing. (Frozen strawberries may be substituted if fresh not available.)

title: pork and rice
directions: Sprinkle chops with parsley, salt and pepper.
Lay pork chops on top of rice.
Pour soup and liquid on top of pork chops.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate peanut butter brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a jellyroll pan.
Mix margarine, cocoa, water, buttermilk and eggs; heat and stir until boiling.
Remove from heat; add sugar, flour, baking soda and vanilla.
Pour into pan and bake for 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: sausage scramble
directions: Cook and drain sausage.
Place sausage in greased baking dish (13 x 9-inch).
Beat eggs, milk and salt.
Stir in cheese.
Pour egg mixture over sausage.
Sprinkle croutons on top.
Bake, uncovered, 45 to 50 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Cook meat and onions.
Drain and spread in pie plate.
Salt mixture and then sprinkle with cheese.
Stir together remaining ingredients.
Pour over meat mixture.
Bake 25 minutes at 400°.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Let cream cheese and oleo soften at room temperature.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and frost.

title: mexican caviar
directions: Mix and marinate with 3 tablespoons oil, 1 tablespoon lemon juice and garlic salt to taste.
Let set and chill before serving.

title: cream cheese sandwiches
directions: Mix ingredients until well mixed.
(May need a little pineapple juice.)
Spread on Roman meal bread or any whole wheat bread (thin).

title: oatmeal chipper cookies
directions: Put dry ingredients into a bowl.
Mix well.
Stir in oil, eggs and vanilla.
Mixture seems dry.
Shape into 1-inch balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: old fashion pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat sugar, butter, eggs, flour, syrup, vanilla and salt, beating after each addition.
Fold in chopped pecans.
Pour mixture into crust.
Decorate top with pecan halves. Bake 40 minutes on middle rack of oven until center of pie is firm.

title: white chocolate pecan pie
directions: With electric mixer, beat together egg, egg yolk, and 1/3 c light brown sugar for 5 minutes.
Mix in 1/4 c each of light and dark corn syrup, 2 Tbsp butter, 1 tsp vanilla and pinch of salt. Stir in 2 cups pecans and 3/4 c chopped white chocolate.
Pour into refrigerated pie crust and bake in 350 degree oven for 40 minutes.
Drizzle with melted white chocolate.

title: do ahead breakfast squares
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put 1 layer of bread in bottom. Sprinkle ham pieces, cooked and crumbled sausage or cooked and crumbled bacon.
Top with cheese.
Beat together milk, eggs, mustard and salt.
Gently pour over meat and cheese.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
In morning, sprinkle top with corn flake crumbs and pour melted butter over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until golden brown.

title: train wreck
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage.
Heat spaghetti sauce and hamburger, spices and cut up sausage pieces.
Simmer for 1 hour. Cook rigatoni.
Put cooked rigatoni into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spoon sauce mixture over top; stir well.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: tex-mex bean dip
directions: Combine ingredients in saucepan.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve hot with corn chips or tortilla chips.
Makes 4 cups.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix drained vegetables, soup, diced chicken and mayonnaise together and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Put second crust on top, sealing edges.
Bake at 375° to 400° until crusts are brown, about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: milky way ice cream
directions: Melt Milky Ways with can of condensed milk.
When melted, add milk; mix well.
Add 1/2 can Hershey's chocolate syrup.
Pour into ice cream churn; finish filling with milk.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: In a skillet, melt butter over medium heat.
Saute onion until tender.
Stir in potatoes, soup and milk.
Add cheese, green pepper and 1/2 cup cracker crumbs.
Pour into a shallow casserole and top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: magic margarita pie
directions: Combine pretzel crumbs, butter and sugar; press firmly on bottom and sides of buttered 9-inch pie plate.
Combine in large bowl the canned milk, lime juice, tequila and Triple Sec (any orange liqueur); mix well and fold in whipped cream.
Pour into crusts; freeze 4 hours or chill 2 hours.
Garnish with whipped cream or pretzels.

title: cherry cream cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually add condensed milk. Mix well.
Add lemon juice after ingredients are well blended. Pour into pie crust.
Chill.
Add cherry topping.

title: sweet onion and zucchini relish
directions: Place all of the ingredients in a medium saucepan with 1 cup water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, partially cover and simmer for about 40 minutes or until slightly thick, stirring occasionally.

title: lu lu paste dip
directions: Beat egg yolks, sugar and vinegar together.
Add margarine. Cook over medium heat for a few minutes.
Don't overcook; cool. Beat in cream cheese, then add grated onion, chili powder, pimentos and chopped green pepper.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding, milk and sour cream, then fold in Cool Whip. Layer vanilla wafers and 6 or more sliced bananas.
Pour pudding mix over wafer and banana mixture.

title: maple syrup
directions: Boil sugar, honey and water 2 minutes; add flavoring.
Great on waffles or pancakes.

title: joel's favorite kasha
directions: Coarsely chop the onion and cook in the oil until translucent, in a large skillet.
Meanwhile, in a separate pot, cook the bow tie pasta according to the directions on the package.
Lightly beat the egg and stir it into the kasha until all the grains are moist.
Add the kasha to the pan with the onions and heat until the grains are dry.

title: hershey bar brownies
directions: Mix according to directions on box. Put half of the batter in 13 x 9 pan. Arrange Hershey bars (broken in large pieces) on top. Pour remaining batter over this. Bake according to directions on box. Cool completely before cutting into squares.

title: cashew chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake in an ovenproof dish for 40 minutes at 325°.

title: 5 minute coconut pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add sugar, mix well.
Add milk, mix well.
Fold in coconut and extract.
Add whipped cream and mix well.
Pour into pie shell. Ready to serve.

title: cheese drop biscuits
directions: Combine flour, salt and baking powder; cut in cheese and shortening.
Add milk all at once and stir carefully until dry ingredients are damp.
Stir vigorously until mixture forms a soft dough that clings to bowl.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: dixie cornbread
directions: Stir dry ingredients; add buttermilk, egg and drippings, mixing just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Pour into a greased (hot) 10-inch ovenproof skillet.
Bake in a preheated 450° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Saute onion, pepper and celery.
Drain scrambled sausage and put all ingredients together in baking dish.
Cover with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: pastichio(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Brown meat and onion in margarine; add remaining ingredients. Cook until sauce is thick, approximately 30 minutes.

title: burrito casserole
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with half of tortillas.
Brown ground beef with onion and seasonings.
Spread layers of beef, beans and sliced Velveeta cheese.
Repeat layer of tortillas, layer of beef, beans and sliced Velveeta.
Mix soup with tomatoes and green chilies.
Pour over all other ingredients.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for one hour.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top with paprika.
Return to oven and bake a few minutes more until cheese is melted.

title: hmmmm chicken
directions: Sprinkle breasts with parsley and garlic salt.
Roll up; secure with a toothpick.
Roll in butter, then dressing mix. Place in heavily greased baking dish.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs over chicken; moisten lightly with water.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sweet potato salad
directions: Heat water to boiling; add potatoes.
Heat to boiling, then reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until tender, 30 to 35 minutes. Drain potatoes; slip off skins.
Cut potatoes into 1/2-inch cubes. Add celery, onion and orange.
Mix remaining ingredients, except lettuce leaves; pour on vegetables and orange.
Stir to blend. Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Serve in lettuce-lined bowls. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken on sunday
directions: Spread 1 c. dry rice over bottom of 13 1/2 x 8 1/2 inch pyrex dish.
Combine 1 can of mushroom or celery soup with 1/2 c. milk, heat and pour slowly over rice.
Lay pieces of raw chicken- unfloured and unsalted on top of rice.
Sprinkle 1 package of dry onion soup mix over top of chicken.
Seal tight with foil.
Bake 2 hours and 15 minutes at 325 degrees.
(Don't peek.)
Do not salt and pepper.

title: peanut butter oatmeal bars
directions: Sift together flour, peanut butter and shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Mix in egg and milk.
Add oats. Mix well.
Spread in greased baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cranberry salad molded
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Grind cranberries, orange and apple together.
Add liquid artificial sweetener and lemon juice.
When gelatin begins to set, stir in cranberry mixture and pour into square pan.
Chill until set.
Serve on lettuce leaf. Yield:
4 servings.
Carbohydrate ?? g, protein 0 g, fat 0 g, calories 28.
One serving = 1/2 fruit exchange.

title: potatoes with cheese
directions: Grate cold potatoes.
Stir together sour cream and cheese. Heat together soup, butter and onions.
Mix all together with potatoes in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: vegetable beef and biscuit casserole
directions: Cook beef over medium heat until brown, stirring to separate. Drain off fat.
Stir in soup, water, mixed vegetables and Worcestershire sauce.
Spoon into a 3-quart baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, or until hot and bubbling.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into pie shells.
Chill. Makes 2 pies.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Combine in a medium bowl corn syrup, molasses and boiling water.
Stir in baking soda.
Beat a little of this mix into egg. Then stir back into mixing bowl.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Combine butter and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well. Add crushed chips and butterscotch chips.
Mix flour and baking soda.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Bake at 375° on greased sheet for 10 minutes.

title: mincemeat cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large mixer bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, beating until smooth.
Combine dry ingredients. Gradually add to creamed mixture.
Stir in mincemeat and nuts. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart on Pam sprayed baking sheets.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until browned.
Cool.

title: fruitcake
directions: In large bowl, cut up cherries and pineapple. Add flour and coat well. Stir in pecans. Cream butter and sugar well; beat in eggs, vanilla and lemon extract. Combine with fruit mixture. Bake at 325° in tube pan for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Mix whatever glaze you desire and pour over cake; cool.

title: sausage dip
directions: Brown and drain ground beef and sausage.
Cut the Velveeta into very small cubes and melt.
Mix meat, cheese and remaining ingredients.

title: chianti's delight
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine ground turkey, garlic, oatmeal, bread crumbs and egg whites in a medium mixing bowl.
Shape into small balls, using about 1 tablespoon of turkey mixture.

title: pot roast
directions: Season meat with salt and pepper.
Brown in 1/4 cup dressing in Dutch oven over low heat.
Add remaining dressing and water. Cover; simmer 2 hours.
Add onions, carrots and potatoes.
Cover. Continue simmer 1 hour or until meat and vegetables are tender. Remove meat and vegetables to platter.
Gradually add water and flour, stirring until well blended.
Gradually add flour mixture to hot liquid in pan.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until mixture boils and thickens.
Simmer 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Serve with meat and vegetables.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cake mix peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in bottom of pan so it won't stick.
Pour half bag cake mix over pan.
Drain juice off peaches in a bowl.
Pour peaches in pan.
Mix sugar and flavoring with peach juice, then pour the rest of your cake mix in pan.
Pour juice on top of everything.
Chop a little butter over the top.
Place in oven and cook until done at 200° to 250°.

title: green punch
directions: Mix water, sugar, lime and Kool-Aid.
Add limeade, orange juice and pineapple juice.
Add ginger ale and liquor when ready to serve.

title: dutch baby(german pancake)
directions: Mix flour, milk and salt together and add eggs.
Mix until smooth.
Melt butter in baking dish and grease sides.
Pour batter into dish.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve immediately with jelly or syrup.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Mix flour and soda.
Cut shortening into flour until mixture resembles corn meal.
Add buttermilk; mix to form soft dough. Turn onto floured surface; knead lightly several times until dough is smooth.
Roll to desired thickness.
Cut with floured biscuit cutter.
Place on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: peanut butter and jelly sandwich
directions: Spread peanut butter on bread first, then spread the jelly on.

title: all-night drop cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg white and salt on high speed until soft peaks form.
Beat in sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, until soft and glossy.
Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.

title: banana sponge
directions: Mash bananas with fork.
Soak gelatin in water.
Dissolve sugar in boiling water.
Cool this mixture; stir in banana pulp. Chill the jelly until it begins to thicken.
Whip it.
Fold in beaten egg whites with salt.
Fold into gelatin.
Fill sherbet cups or a serving dish.
Top with whipped cream with vanilla.

title: lox, salmon and eggs
directions: Saute onions until golden brown.
Cover in a 3-quart oblong dish with onions and fat.
Put pieces of lux and salmon over onions.
Beat eggs with milk.
Pour over all.
Do not mix together.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let stand about 10 minutes before cutting.

title: grandma's cake
directions: Beat together Crisco and sugar.
Then add eggs, one at a time, beat well.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add flour mixture to Crisco.
Mix.
Then add milk and lastly the vanilla.
Grease a tube pan.
Pour batter into pan and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Cool.
Remove from pan.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar when cooled.

title: garden beans with honey cashew sauce
directions: Wash, trim and cook to tender-crisp the beans.
Drain well. In a skillet or large saucepan, melt butter.
Add cashew pieces and saute lightly over low heat.
Add the honey and stir about 1 minute to blend and warm.
Add beans and stir gently to reheat the beans and coat with the honey mixture.

title: shrimp and mushrooms with angel hair pasta
directions: Peel and devein shrimp; set aside.
Cook pasta according to package; drain.
Melt butter.
Add garlic and basil; cook 1 minute, stirring often.
Add shrimp, mushrooms and pepper; cook about 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve over pasta.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix; spread well over mixture.

title: swedish cookies
directions: Mix flour, sugar and butter like for a pie crust.
Roll in balls the size of walnut, put on cookie sheet about 1 inch apart. Pat down with fork dipped in hot water.
Bake for 12 minutes at 400°.
When cool, roll in powdered sugar.

title: mary's lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger with onion and bell pepper.
When about brown, add garlic salt and then sauce.
Simmer.
Cook noodles until soft. When done, layer noodles, then meat sauce and sour cream all over.
Repeat until ingredients are gone.
Sprinkle cheese over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: fiesta casserole
directions: Cook onion in hot oil until tender.
Add meat and brown.
Stir in tomatoes and seasoning.
Blend eggs and milk.
Combine with meat mixture.

title: praline cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cream margarine and brown sugar well. Blend in egg, vanilla and dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Cool.

title: bean casserole
directions: Brown the hamburg, stirring often to break into fine chunks, with the onion.
When thoroughly cooked, drain off grease and set aside.
Cut bacon and fry slowly until semi-crisp.
Drain off grease.
Don't use the grease.
Mix the remaining ingredients. Bake at 325° to 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Can be microwaved.
Put the casserole in a round covered dish.
Cook for 20 minutes, stirring at 15, 10 and 5 minutes.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Wash fresh blueberries.
Mix all ingredients, including blueberries together in a bowl.
Pour into unbaked pie crust and bake at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: blueberry jello mold
directions: Dissolve jello in hot pineapple juice.
Mix Cool Whip with blueberry pie filling.
Add to jello mixture and mix.
Pour into a jello mold.

title: frozen cherry salad
directions: Drain all of the fruit; reserve some cherries and oranges to garnish and set aside fruit.
Save fruit liquid for another use. In medium bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy; blend in sour cream, sugar and salt.
Put in fruit, marshmallows and nuts; spoon into 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pan and freeze for 6 hours.
Unmold and garnish with fruit.
Makes 8 servings.

title: oven fried fish
directions: Preheat oven to 500 degrees.
Cut fish into four serving pieces if necessary.
Add salt and pepper to crumbs.
Pour milk into shallow pan and dip fish in milk, then in crumbs.
Arrange fish on baking sheet sprayed with nonstick vegetable cooking spray.
Sprinkle oil over fish.
Bake for 10 minutes.

title: layered salad
directions: Mix the sugar and sour cream.
In another bowl, thin mayonnaise with vinegar to pouring consistency.
Layer in pan or salad bowl the lettuce, sour cream mixture, celery, onion, mayonnaise mixture, bacon and cheese.
Let stand in refrigerator not longer than 8 hours.
Toss before serving.

title: ursula's cookies
directions: Sift together flour and baking powder; set aside.
Cream butter and confectioners sugar.
Add egg yolk and beat 1 minute. Add milk, vanilla and almond flavoring to creamed mixture.
Blend together.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.

title: 5 "p" salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin according to directions on box.
Add other ingredients and chill.

title: dirt and rocks
directions: Step 1:
Put milk into a bowl (cold).
Add pudding mix.
Beat with a whisk 2 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: blender potato pancakes
directions: Put in blender eggs, onions, flour and some potatoes on low for 1 minute and then add the rest of the potatoes (on low) for another 1/2 minute.
Put on pancake grill or frying pan; fry until crisp (both sides).
Serve with applesauce or sour cream.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Beat egg yolks in medium bowl and stir.
Add condensed milk. Stir in lemon juice a little at a time.
Stir well and pour into pie shell.
Beat egg whites adding about 1/4 cup of sugar a little at a time until stiff peaks form.
Bake at 400 degrees for 5 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender; debone and salt to taste.
Add milk to chicken and soup in baking dish.
Add a dash of pepper.
Add chicken broth to stuffing mix.
Arrange stuffing around chicken. Bake at 250° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Butter a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Blend sugar, cornstarch and salt in baking dish.
Beat eggs and stir into sugar mixture.
Add pineapple chunks and juice.
Mix well.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake covered for 1 hour in a 350° oven or microwave for 10 to 15 minutes.
Great for brunch.

title: rainbow ribbon salad
directions: Dissolve each jello in 1 cup boiling water; add 1/2 cup water. Pour 1st layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan; jell.

title: easy apple cake
directions: Place apples in mixing bowl; add sugar, stir to mix.
Let stand 1/2 hour.
Add oil and eggs; blend.
Add flour, cinnamon, baking soda, salt and vanilla.
Pour into well-greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool in pan. Dust top with powdered sugar.

title: german chocolate cake and icing
directions: Melt chocolate over boiling water; cool.
Cream margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolks, 1 at a time and beat after each.
Add melted chocolate and vanilla.
Mix well.
Sift together flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Add alternately with buttermilk to chocolate mixture; beat well.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Line the bottom of 3 (9-inch) cake pans with brown paper. Grease and flour paper.
Evenly divide the batter into the 3 pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool.
Frost tops only. Frost with Coconut Pecan Frosting.

title: brownie pie
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes in greased pie plate.

title: best coconut pound cake
directions: Preheat over to 350°. Grease and flour bundt pan well. Cream together 2 c. sugar, 1 c. oil and 4 whole eggs. Mix in flour, buttermilk, coconut flavoring and small bag of coconut; mix well. Pour in bundt pan and bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes. When cake is done and is cooling make glaze filling.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and peanut butter. Add beaten eggs alternately with dry ingredients. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Press lightly with fork to make crisscross pattern. Bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix in ice cream freezer container and freeze according to directions.

title: mary beth nielsen ham's creamy potatoes
directions: Scrub and slice potatoes into 1/2 to 1/4-inch slices.
Spread potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Pour in cream.
Dot top with butter.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and onion powder.
Bake at 356° for 45 minutes to 1 hour until golden brown, bubbly and tender.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Grease and flour 3 loaf pans. Bake at 350° approximately.

title: taco soup
directions: In a Dutch oven or large saucepan, cook beef over medium heat until no longer pink; drain.
Stir in taco seasoning, corn, beans, and tomatoes.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes or until heated through, stirring occasionally.

title: bea golden's dirty rice
directions: Brown meat.
Saute onions and bell peppers in 1/4 cup oil; add to meat.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well and bake in covered casserole sprayed with Pam.
Bake 1 hour at 350° on center rack of oven.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cherry icebox dessert
directions: Tear cake in pieces.
Put on bottom of a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Add pie filling to cake.
Make pudding according to directions.
Mix with sour cream and drained cherries.
Spoon mixture on top, cover and refrigerate for several hours.

title: quick cheeseburger bake
directions: Saute beef and onion until browned.
Drain.
Stir in soup, vegetable and milk.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli in small pieces. Fry bacon crisp and crumble. Put all ingredients in a bowl, adding as much cheese as desired.

title: quick rolls
directions: Beat egg; add sugar, shortening, yeast, salt and flour (add flour slowly).
Let rise in greased pan until double in bulk. Make into rolls; let rise again.
Gently oil tops of rolls before they are put in oven to bake.
After 25 minutes, watch carefully. Take out when browned as desired.
Bake in 350° oven approximately 25 to 30 minutes.
May oil with butter again.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients except paprika.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Sprinkle the top with the paprika.
Bake at 250° to 300° until set and slightly brown.

title: date bread
directions: Pour soda and water over dates and raisins.
Cream butter, sugar and vanilla, beat well.
Add flour.
Pour in dates and raisins including the water and nuts.
Bake at 350°.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Continue beating and add oil, sugar, zucchini and flavorings.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to first mixture.
Fold in nuts.
Spoon into 3 greased and floured pans. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done (golden brown on top). Cool on rack.
Freezes well.
Tinfoil pans work great for baking bread in.

title: holiday nut roll
directions: Crumble crackers, raisins, nuts, coconut and cherries.
Set aside 1 cup of nuts and cherries to sprinkle on top.
Melt margarine and marshmallows together.
Mix thoroughly; add cherry juice.
While hot pour over cracker mixture and stir.
Add milk. Press in loaf pan lined with wax paper.
Top with nuts and cherries.
Chill overnight and slice.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese.
Add sugar and continue beating until well mixed.
Alternate eggs and flour, mixing well after each addition.
Mixture will be very thick.
Add extracts and mix well.
Spoon into large tube pan and bake in 325° oven for approximately 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: oven-cooked chicken in sour cream
directions: Combine sour cream with seasonings.
Dip chicken pieces in sour cream mixture.
Coat pieces in bread crumbs.
Pour melted butter into a baking pan.
Place chicken pieces in pan, skin side up.
Bake in a 400° oven for 1 hour or until tender.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Salt and pepper shrimp and set aside.
Saute onions, celery, bell pepper and garlic in oleo.
Add the shrimp and cook until the raw shrimp turn pink and curl (about 10 minutes).
