Add soups; dissolve cornstarch in water.
Add and simmer 15 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: pecan sandies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar. Stir in vanilla. Add flour. Mix on low until well blended. Stir in pecans. Mix well. Chill for 30 minutes. Roll into 1-inch balls. Place on a greased baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes or until bottom edges are golden brown. Cool on a wire rack. Yield: about 1 1/2 dozen.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together and form into small balls.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: green jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and boiling water; stir until dissolved.
Let cool slightly, then add all ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour in shallow dish.
Refrigerate until set.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients well; put in baking dish.
Sprinkle topping on top.

title: coconut bundt cake
directions: Mix together and pour into greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for approximately 1 hour.
Do not peek.

title: jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and let set in fridge for 30 to 40 minutes. Then fold in other ingredients.
Makes 4 servings.

title: spicy cheese dip
directions: In crock-pot, melt the cheese.
In a skillet, brown the sausage and drain.
After the cheese is melted, add all other ingredients and let get hot.

title: country apple cake
directions: In a medium bowl combine flour, baking powder, 2 cups of the sugar, oil, eggs, orange juice, salt and vanilla.
Beat until thoroughly combined.
In another bowl, toss apples with cinnamon and remaining sugar.
Spread 1/3 of batter in a greased 10-inch tube pan.
Cover with half of the apples.
Repeat layers.
Spoon remaining batter over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Cool in pan for 20 minutes before putting on a rack, dust with confectioners sugar, if desired.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: In large skillet, melt 2 tablespoons butter or margarine and chicken broth.
While melting, grate onion, carrots and broccoli. Saute vegetables in skillet with melted butter and broth, while preparing remainder of soup, until onion is transparent.
Grate Velveeta and Cheddar cheese.
Set aside in a bowl.
Melt 6 tablespoons butter or margarine in at least 3-quart saucepan. Add flour, blending well.
Pour milk in gradually, blending well. Bring to a boil.
Add cheese and remove from heat.
After cheese is stirred in and thoroughly melted, add vegetables and season to taste with Tabasco or other spices.

title: little supper pizzas
directions: Prepare Sausage Topping.
Heat oven to 450°.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in shortening, water, lemon juice and egg yolk.
Mix until dough cleans side of bowl; divide into 24 parts. Pat into 3 1/2-inch circles on ungreased baking sheets; prick with fork.
Bake until light golden 6 to 8 minutes.
Remove from oven; leave crusts on baking sheets.
(Crusts can be baked several hours ahead of time.)
Reduce oven temperature to 400°.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Chop artichokes and mix all together.
Put in lightly greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: barbecue
directions: Fry hamburger with chopped onions and green peppers.
Add spicy brown mustard and mix well.
Add barbecue seasoning mix. Add other spices and barbecue sauce, then add more tomato sauce, if needed.

title: low-fat burritos
directions: Spray pan and brown turkey.
Add burrito seasoning and prepare as directed on package.
Heat burrito bread and add what you want on it.

title: mandarin salad
directions: In small pan saute and stir constantly the almonds, butter and sugar until golden brown.
Remove and spread out to cool on wax paper.
In a large bowl mix together all other ingredients; add almonds.
Serve with red wine vinegar salad dressing.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: pizza bake(appetizer or party food)
directions: First mix egg, milk and flour.
Add oregano, cheeses and pepper or bacon.
Pour into lightly greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for approximately 30 to 35 minutes, until browned and bubbly.
Let cool.
Cut into squares.

title: pear relish
directions: Run pears, onions and peppers through meat chopper.
Add other ingredients (tie pickling spices in cheesecloth bag).
Cook 30 minutes after mixture comes to boil.
Put in scalded jars and seal.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix pineapple, water, sugar, cornstarch, egg yolks, butter and salt on top of flame until thickened.
Beat egg whites until peaks form.
Fold into mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: quick apple betty
directions: Spread pie filling in greased and floured 9-inch round cake pan.
In medium size mixing bowl, mix nutmeg, cinnamon and cake mix.
Sprinkle mixture evenly over top of pie filling.
Drizzle top with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes, or until top is golden brown.

title: *spicy walnut bars
directions: Cover raisins with boiling water and allow to plump while combining remaining ingredients.
Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs and mix.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with buttermilk to the sugar mixture.
Fold in raisins and nuts.

title: brown rice
directions: Add mix to melted margarine and cook 1 hour in a 425° oven.

title: sweet bread dough
directions: Stir yeast into warm water and 1 teaspoon sugar.
In a large bowl, heat milk, margarine, 1/2 cup sugar and salt to about 110°. Add yeast.
Beat in about 2 cups flour and add eggs (room temperature).
Beat in as much remaining flour as possible. Continue to add remainder gradually, kneading 8 to 10 minutes. Place dough in a large greased bowl.
Cover and let rise in warm place (85°) until doubled.
Punch down.
Turn out on a lightly floured surface.
May be used for cinnamon rolls, caramel rolls, buns or 2 loaves of bread.

title: chili dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on bottom of glass pan.
Cover with 1 can of green chilies.
Next layer with chili with beans, then add second can of green chilies.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.
Cover with shredded Cheddar cheese and reheat until melted.
Serve with sour cream and chips.

title: "oh boy" waffles
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt, and sugar; set aside.
In a separate bowl mix together beaten eggs, milk, and oil; add all at once to the dry ingredients, beating only till moistened.
Bake in preheated waffle baker.
Makes 10 to 12 waffles.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix and press the crackers and butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix together next 4 ingredients; beat 15 minutes until fluffy. Spread over graham cracker mixture.
Slice 3 or 4 bananas lengthwise.
Place over mixture; add 2 cups crushed pineapple (well drained).
Add frozen strawberries.
Add Dream Whip.
Top with chopped pecans.
Refrigerate for 12 hours.

title: savory baked chicken
directions: Heat oven to 400° and place a 13x9 baking pan in oven with the butter.
In a bag, mix the potatoes and cheese together.
Dip the chicken pieces in beaten eggs then place in bag and shake until coated.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: corn for freezer
directions: Heat and simmer 5 minutes over low heat.
Cool in ice water and freeze.
To serve, heat in covered dish in microwave.

title: deli-in-a-skillet
directions: Mix corned beef, sauerkraut and water in a large skillet. Bring to a full boil. Stir in rice and top with cheese.
Cover. Remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes. Serves 4.

title: old fashion cream pie
directions: Mix together ingredients, folding in stiffly beaten egg whites last.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until knife comes out clean.

title: aunt vera's molasses cookies(soft)
directions: Dissolve soda in hot water mixture and mix all ingredients well.
Add enough flour so mixture will be heavy enough to roll out 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into circles.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 5 or 6 dozen.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Place peaches (juice and all) in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Sprinkle jello over peaches.
Sprinkle cake mix over total mixture.
Cut margarine into small pieces and dot on top.
Do not stir or mix layers.
Pour water over recipe.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: sweet-sour dressing(makes one pint)
directions: Blend in blender, adding oil very slowly.
Refrigerate.

title: pound cake
directions: Put everything at once in large mixing bowl.
Blend thoroughly and then beat 20 minutes at high speed.
(Must be 20 minutes for enough air.)
Pour in large tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fanny farmer fudge
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, evaporated milk and butter. Bring to a boil for 10 minutes, stirring constantly. Pour over chocolate chips, Marshmallow Creme, chocolate bar and walnuts. Stir until chips are melted. Pour into a wax paper lined and buttered 9 x 10-inch baking dish and cool. Makes 5 pounds of fudge.

title: cheese ball
directions: Blend together all ingredients (except pecans).
Roll in crushed pecans.
Refrigerate.
Serve with crackers, chips, etc.

title: rhubarb and pineapple jam
directions: Mix rhubarb, pineapple and sugar.
Allow to stand about 30 minutes.
Bring
mixture
to
a
boil and then cook for 12 minutes,
stirring
constantly.
(Don't turn your back, it can burn
quickly.) Remove from heat and stir in package of jello. Pour
into
sterilized
glasses and cover with paraffin or use handy screw-top jelly
jars.
Makes about 6 half-pint glasses.

title: chop suey
directions: Brown meat.
Put mushrooms, bamboo shoots, sliced water chestnuts and their liquids in a large pan.
Add bean sprouts and 1/4 of the liquid.
Add meat to vegetables.
Fry onions and celery until they get a glossy look.
Add to meat and vegetables.
Add sugar, oil and soy sauce.
Cook over medium heat.
Cook about 40 to 45 minutes, then mix starch, water and a little liquid from bean sprouts and add to vegetables and meat.
Cook 10 minutes more, then serve over rice or chow mein noodles.

title: a favorite rice ring
directions: Mix all the rice, melted butter, cheese and carrots together and add the slightly beaten egg.
Put in a buttered casserole pan or dish.
Bake in a 350° oven, uncovered, for 45 minutes.
Turn out on a warm dish or platter.
Make a hole in the center and pour in peas or beans.
A tasty and colorful dish.

title: mexican vegetable bake
directions: Saute first 5 ingredients in oil.
Add garbanzo beans, stewed tomatoes and corn.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Mix mayonnaise, milk, flour and eggs together.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into pie crust and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: blueberry yum-yum
directions: Combine blueberries, 1 cup sugar and 1/4 cup water in a medium saucepan; cook over low heat until berries are soft (about 15 minutes).
Combine cornstarch and 3 tablespoons water in a small mixing bowl; stir well.
Add cornstarch mixture to blueberry mixture; cook, stirring constantly, until thick.
Set aside to cool.
Combine flour, margarine and pecans in a small bowl; mix well.
Press dough into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, cool.
Combine cream cheese and 1 cup sugar; beat until smooth.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spread evenly over cool crust.
Pour blueberries over top.
Refrigerate.

title: spinach cheese bits
directions: Mix all ingredients except pepperoni, making sure the spinach is well drained. Place a pepperoni in the bottom of each mini muffin cup pan and place a spoon full of the mixture on top. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool 10 minutes before taking out of pan.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix ground beef, onion, milk, and 2 tsp. Worcestershire sauce. Roll into small balls. Place on baking sheet. Broil until brown.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add pie filling and undrained pineapple.
Stir.
Cool and set in refrigerator to congeal.
Mix cream cheese and sugar until fluffy.
Fold in sour cream and spread over congealed blueberry mixture.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Keep refrigerated.

title: salad dressing
directions: Blend all together in blender.
Very good on tossed greens.

title: pineapple cheese cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix 2 cups flour, 2/3 cup margarine or butter, 1/2 cup almonds and 1/2 cup powdered sugar in medium bowl with fork until crumbly.
Press firmly and evenly in bottom of ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake until set, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: After grating cheese, mix ingredients.
Roll out and cut as desired.
Top with pecan half.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes. If desired, dust with confectioners sugar.
Makes 60.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Arrange bread slices in pan. In a large bowl, beat eggs, then add tomato sauce, water and Italian seasoning.
Mix well.
Pour mixture over bread slices evenly moistening bread completely. Top with pepperoni, Pizza Mate and shredded cheese.
Cover and refrigerate for 4 hours or overnight. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix dry ingredients together and add to beaten eggs, vinegar and water.
Then add butter.
Boil until thick like custard.
May be used this way or thinned with cream to desired consistency.
It is excellent for potato salad, deviled eggs, etc.

title: pizza dip
directions: Spread softened cream cheese on a large, flat serving dish. Spread on pizza sauce, pepper
and onions.
Cover (Saran Wrap) and leave overnight in fridge.
Add ground beef and mushrooms.
Spread cheese over this.
Slice olives lengthwise to decorate.

title: boston's  blueberry muffins
directions: Mix together butter, sugar, and eggs.
Add milk, salt, flour, baking powder, and fruit.
Put into greased and floured muffin tins and sprinkle tops with sugar.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Yields 12 - 18.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes and drain.
Combine other ingredients, except cracker crumbs.
Add broccoli and pour into buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with cracker crumbs. Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes.

title: jelly roll
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar gradually.
Add flour sifted with salt and baking powder.
Then add melted butter, milk and vanilla.
Turn into a large shallow pan which has been greased or lined with wax paper.
Bake in 375° oven about 12 minutes.
Turn onto a cloth, sprinkled with powdered sugar if desired.
Spread with any kind of jelly while cake is still warm and roll cake.
Wrap tightly with cloth.
Allow to stand until cold.
Unwrap and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown hamburger; add salt, garlic salt, pepper and chili powder.
Add flour, stir well into meat.
Add 4 cups water. Simmer until thick juice, about 20 minutes.
Dip tortillas in hot oil for couple seconds; set aside until 1 dozen tortillas are done.
Fill with hamburger mixture and roll.
Sprinkle with cheese and onions (optional).
Pour remaining mixture over all and cover with foil.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pepperoni lasagne
directions: In large pan or skillet, brown hamburger and large mango. Drain if too much grease and put in large pan.
Add soups and pizza sauce.
Cook rotini, drain and add to mixture.
Mix together. Makes two 9 x 13-inch pans (Pam the pans).
Cover with Mozzarella cheese and pepperoni.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Great for a crowd, or if you like, freeze 1 pan for another time.

title: asparagus - pea casserole
directions: Alternate layers of asparagus and peas.
Pour mushroom soup on top.
Place dabs of butter on top and bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Sprinkle crumbs on top and brown.

title: jeannie's shingles
directions: Line a large cookie sheet (with sides) with foil.
Cover with graham crackers solid and tight.
Boil margarine and sugar for 2 minutes.
Pour over crackers.
Bake at 375°
for 8 minutes. Remove and pour chocolate chips over cookies.
Spread with knife until it is a solid sheet of chocolate over cookies.
Immediately freeze for 15 minutes.
Remove and break into pieces.

title: date bars
directions: Combine dates, sugar and water in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat till thick, set aside to cool.
Mix remaining ingredients with spoon till crumbly mixture-do not use beater.
Spread half of crumb mixture in bottom of greased 13x9-inch pan.
Spread with date mixture; top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40-50 minutes.

title: napa salad
directions: Combine cabbage, green onions and sunflower seeds in large bowl. Set aside. Mix together remaining ingredients. Add to salad just before serving.

title: stuffed sweet potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes,
prick with fork and bake in 425° oven, 40 to 60	minutes, until tender.	Cut a lengthwise slice from top of each potato.
Remove skin from slices and put pulp into mixing bowl.
Mash
potatoes.
Add
butter,
marmalade, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Mash until well blended.
Spoon mixture into
potato shells.
Sprinkle
chopped nuts on top.
Makes 6 servings.	Can be	made
ahead
of
time and placed in baking dish, refrigerated. Heat in 425° oven for 30 minutes or until heated through.

title: frozen cherry salad
directions: Mix and freeze in pan.

title: sweet and sour mixed baked beans
directions: Drain butter, lima and kidney beans.
Fry bacon crisp and crumble it.
Place onions in the skillet with bacon grease.
Add sugar, mustard, garlic powder, salt and vinegar.
Cook, covered, for 20 minutes.
Add to beans in a 3-quart casserole.
Add bacon. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Spray two 9 x 13-inch pans with shortening/oil spray.
Mix chicken and soup.
In separate bowl, mix onion, 1 cup Cheddar cheese, Monterey Jack cheese, Velveeta cheese, sour cream and picante sauce.
Combine chicken and soup mixture with cheese mixture (may add jalapeno juice and chopped jalapenos).
Spoon some of mixture onto flour tortillas.
Roll up and place in pan(s).
Pour remaining mixture on top.
Add remaining 1 1/2 cups grated Cheddar cheese and jalapeno slices on top to garnish.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes (foil covered or lid).
Remove foil or lid and bake an additional 10 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: lemon bars
directions: Combine
these	ingredients
and
pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 10 minutes at 275°.

title: baked lima beans
directions: Wash the lima beans. In a large kettle, cover the beans with plenty of water. Bring to a boil. Remove from heat and cover for 1 hour.
Lightly fry the bacon (leave soft).
Discard the grease. In a large roaster, add drained lima beans and the remaining ingredients. Cover with just enough water to barely touch the top of the beans.
Mix well.
Bake in a covered roaster at 300° for 2 to 3 hours.
Mix occasionally, checking for doneness.
This makes a lot and can be cut in half.

title: mexican cornbread salad
directions: In a large bowl layer as follows:

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Layer in
13 1/2 x 9-inch pan chicken and Veg-All.
Mix together soup,
broth and butter on stove and bring to a boil. Pour over Veg-All; cover with pie crusts.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Peel if using fresh shrimp; set aside.
Melt oil.
Add onion, celery and tomato paste.
Cook slowly in heavy, uncovered, pot until onion is wilted.
Dissolve cornstarch in cold water.
Add to mixture.
Bring to a boil and add seasoning and shrimp.
Cook over medium heat 20 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: ambrosia
directions: Mix together; chill for 2 hours.
Serves 6.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown beef or sausage with onion.
Drain fat.
Combine soup and milk.
Mix with meat.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with cooking spray.
Place a layer of Tater Tots on bottom of pan.
Place meat mixture over Tater Tots, then another layer of Tater Tots.
Sprinkle top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Cover. Bake at 450° for 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: marinated brisket
directions: Mix all ingredients except brisket and spread over brisket. Wrap brisket in foil and marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Next day, bake 4 hours at 325°.
Open foil carefully and baste with 1/2 jar of Woody's cooking sauce, then close foil and cook 1 hour longer.
Very good!

title: molasses crumb cake
directions: Mix as for crumbs with pastry blender the flour, sugar, salt and oleo.
Set aside full 1/2 cup of crumbs.
Mix molasses and baking soda in a cup, then put in larger bowl.
Add to molasses mixture 2 cups boiling water, then add this to dry ingredients. Stir good.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan which is greased and floured.
Sprinkle with crumbs which were set aside.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: 24-hour cole slaw
directions: Mix vegetables together with salt and pepper.
Combine sugar, oil, vinegar and celery seed in small saucepan.
Simmer until clear.
Pour hot mixture over vegetables and store in refrigerator for about 24 hours before serving.

title: artichoke mushroom pie
directions: Cook garlic in	oil
and
add artichokes and mushrooms. Line bottom of pie
shell.
Combine
eggs,
cheese, olives and pepper. Pour over vegetables.
Place top crust on pie and cut slits on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: christmas punch
directions: Prepare frozen juices according to directions.
Mix apples, bananas, and strawberries with 1 cup pineapple juice and blend in blender.
Put mixture in freezer until slushy.
Add sherbet and ginger ale.
Serve.

title: squash rolls
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix baking mix and squash.
Gently smooth dough into ball on floured cloth-covered board.
Knead 5 times. Roll dough into 12-inch circle; spread with margarine.
Cut into 12 wedges.
Roll up, beginning at rounded edges.
Place rolls about 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until golden brown, 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 12 rolls.

title: hot beef sandwiches
directions: Cook chuck roast all day in a slow cooker.
Start it out by adding 1 cup of water.
Add envelope of Lipton onion soup to water.
When roast is falling apart, drain excess fat.
Take a fork and shred the roast.
Add your beef consomme and mix into your roast.
Serve on a fresh dinner roll.

title: apricot stuffed pork chops
directions: Cut pocket in each chop, cutting from fat side almost to bone edge.
Season with salt and pepper.
Drain apricot juice.
Reserve 1/2 cup of syrup.
Place two apricot halves in pocket of each chop.
Cut up remaining apricots; set aside.
Grill chops over medium heat for 35 minutes.
Mix other ingredients and apricot juice and cook for 15 minutes, then pour over pork chops and simmer to desire.

title: quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Cover bottom of pie shell with Cheddar, Mozzarella, Swiss or any combination of cheeses. Sprinkle on onion, chili and ham. Beat eggs with milk. Add salt and pepper. Pour egg mixture over cheese and meat. Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 375°.

title: luscious lemon cooler
directions: Combine flour, margarine and 1/2 cup nuts.
Spread in 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool. Beat cream cheese and sugar until fluffy.
Fold in 1 cup whipped topping.
Spread over cooled crust.
Combine pudding mix, milk and lemon juice.
Beat well.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Top with remaining whipped cream and chopped nuts.
Chill overnight.

title: gone fudge
directions: Bring everything except vanilla, nuts and salt to a boil without stirring and continue until the mixture forms medium-hard balls when dropped in cold water.
Remove from heat and let sit without stirring until lukewarm.
Mix in vanilla, nuts and salt. Beat until it gets a dull glossy look.
Quickly pour into buttered pan and cut into squares before it gets too hard.

title: strawberry jello dessert
directions: Prepare jello according to package directions in a large bowl. After it has thoroughly jelled, whip with a mixer or wire whisk. Drain the fruit cocktail and strawberries; add to the jello along with sliced bananas.
Stir in whipped topping.
Chill for several hours or overnight before serving.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: Put fruit filling into shell.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°. In large mixer
bowl
beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually add Eagle Brand milk	and eggs, beating constantly.
Add lemon and vanilla. Whip until	smooth.
Pour
over
fruit in pie shell. Reduce temperature to
and
bake
minutes until set. Chill. Garnish.
Refrigerate any leftovers.
Makes 2 pies.

title: donuts
directions: Beat eggs and add sugar and Crisco.
Add rest of items one by one.
Chill dough and roll out 1/4-inch thick on floured board. Cut and fry in hot oil.

title: sweet potato cobbler
directions: Peel and slice sweet potatoes thin in a 9 x 13 pan.
Add water, sugar, margarine and
sprinkle with cinnamon.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over mixture in pan.
Sprinkle a little water on top of dry cake mix.
Cook in oven at 275° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: black bean salsa
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients together and chill in the refrigerator at least 8 hours or overnight before serving.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in a large bowl; mix well.
Spoon chicken mixture into a lightly greased shallow 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with cheese and top with potato chips.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken breasts with tomato butter
directions: Combine 3 tablespoons of the butter with the garlic, tomato paste and parsley.
Scrape onto a piece of plastic wrap and use to help form a cylinder of butter.
Wrap tightly and chill.
Combine flour, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Dredge chicken in flour mixture.
Melt remaining 1 tablespoon butter in large skillet.
Add chicken; cook over medium heat, turning once; cook until done (about 10 minutes).
Top hot chicken with slices of prepared butter.
Serves 4.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Blend sour cream, sugar, lemon juice and salt.
Add the bananas, pineapple, cherries and pecans.
Pour into cupcake papers placed in a muffin tin.
Freeze.
Serve on lettuce leaf with mayonnaise.

title: rocky road cake
directions: Grease and flour 12-cup Bundt pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cake mix, mayonnaise, eggs and water until blended.
Turn mix 2 minutes at medium speed.
Blend in nuts, etc.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes.
Serve plain or dust with 10x sugar.

title: banana split cake *
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine and mix with cracker crumbs.
Press into 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Melt 2 sticks margarine and add sugar and eggs. Beat for 10 minutes and pour over crumb crust.
On top of this, layer sliced bananas and then pineapple.
Cover with Cool Whip and top with nuts and cherries.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: potato soup
directions: 1. Fry bacon until crisp in a large pot. Remove bacon & most of the grease, leave about 3-4 Tbsp.
2. Saute onion in the remaining grease, then add potatoes
and enough water to cover the potatoes. Boil potatoes
until tender.
3. Drain most of water (leave about half of the water).
Add 2 cans of cream of mushroom soup, 1/2 c. milk, salt

title: chicken casserole
directions: Butter large baking dish.
Spread 1/2 of crackers in bottom of dish.
Mix everything but margarine and crackers.
Pour in baking dish.
Put remaining crackers on top.
Melt margarine and drizzle over crackers.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: crumb cake
directions: Mix brown sugar, flour, shortening and cinnamon together well until crumbly.
Take out 2 cups of crumbs.
Add the rest of the ingredients to remaining mixture.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle 2 cups reserved crumbs over batter.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: party punch
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add all other ingredients except ginger ale.
Freeze 15 hours or overnight.

title: homemade chocolate chip and oats granola bars
directions: Press dough into 13 x 9-inch pan that is sprayed with Pam. Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until brown.
Cool.
Cut into bars. Store in airtight container.
Makes about 3 dozen.
Delicious. One favorite of my children.

title: canadian cheese soup
directions: Melt butter
in
pot.
Add
onions, carrots and celery. Saute until
soft.
Add
flour
and
cornstarch and cook until bubbly. Add stock and milk and make a smooth sauce.
Add soda and cheese. Season
with salt and pepper.
Add parsley before serving.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Mix ingredients together in baking dish.
Coat chicken (leave in pan).
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: In a large bowl combine ingredients in order given.
Mix well. Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until pick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: mike's mayonnaise biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients and spoon into 12-count muffin tin (greased).
Should fill all 12 spaces.
Preheat oven to 400° and bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until brown.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream
sugars,
shortening,
and eggs until light.
Add applesauce,
mixing well.
Spoon flour into dry measuring cup. Pour
flour onto waxed paper and add soda, baking powder, salt and spices.
Stir well to blend.
Add blended dry ingredients to creamed
mixture,
alternately
with
water, beginning and ending with
dry ingredients.
Stir in fruit and nuts.
Blend well.
Pour into a well greased 9 x 13-inch oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Frost if desired.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes 20 to 25 minutes (not too soft).
Peel potatoes and cut into small cubes.
Mix oil, vinegar, salt and pepper together and pour over potatoes.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Add the remaining ingredients and serve.

title: zesty beets
directions: Heat beets in liquid; drain.
Add butter, horseradish, prepared mustard and seasoned salt.
Stir gently.

title: string bean ricotta
directions: Heat olive oil in heavy skillet.
Saute onion, string beans and parsley until onion becomes translucent.
(You may want to steam beans for about 5 minutes if you like them less crisp.)
Add tomatoes and sauce, then seasonings and stir.
Cook over medium heat for 10 minutes.
Add Ricotta cheese and mix well.
Cook over low heat for another 10 minutes.
Pour over brown rice and serve.

title: swiss steak royale
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients after meat.
Pound into steak and brown steak in shortening.
Remove from pan; add flour not pounded into meat and stir well.
Add liquid.
Add seasonings, mushrooms, garlic and onions.
Place steak in pan; cover tightly and cook slowly for 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Sift dry ingredients and mix them well!
Lightly spray the skillet.
Then preheat the skillet at moderately high heat.
Mix the liquid ingredients with the dry but do not overmix.
Batter should be lumpy but do not leave dry ingredients in bottom of bowl. Makes 20 (6-inch) pancakes.

title: easy homemade chili
directions: Brown beef and chopped onion in skillet.
Drain off excess grease.
Add tomato paste, water, salt, paprika and chili powder. Simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix together onion, bell pepper and pork and beans in baking dish.
Stir together mustard, brown sugar, catsup, syrup and cinnamon.
Put all in baking dish.
Put bacon on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Bacon strips will be done.

title: italian meatballs
directions: Soak bread slices in water for 2 minutes. Add eggs and mix well.
Mix with ground beef, cheese, parsley, salt, oregano and pepper.
With wet hands, form meat mixture into small balls. Brown slowly in hot salad oil. Drain. Add meatballs to sauce. Simmer, loosely covered, for 30 minutes.

title: cheese crunchies
directions: In small mixer bowl, mix ingredients 20 to 30 seconds.
On lightly floured board, mold dough into two 8-inch rolls.
Wrap; refrigerate overnight.
Heat oven to 375°.
Cut rolls into 1/4-inch slices; place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: yum yum coffee cake(this cake is yummy.)
directions: In a bowl, cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and sour cream or buttermilk; mix well.
Sift flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt together, then add to mixture.
Thoroughly mix, then place aside while you make topping.

title: quiche
directions: Place cheese on bottom of crust.
Sprinkle bacon over cheese. Mix remaining ingredients and pour over bacon.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine all the ingredients and chill thoroughly.
Serve on croissants.

title: dried beef ball
directions: Mix together.
Form ball.
Chill and roll in nuts.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes until tender and drain.
Beat softened cream cheese with half and half in mixer.
Add hot potatoes and blend well.
Add butter and seasonings.
Put in 2 quart casserole. Brush top with butter and sprinkle on paprika.
Bake in oven (350°) for 30 minutes.
Can be prepared ahead of time.
Just bake longer to heat and brown.

title: the irresistible peanut butter cookie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine peanut butter, Crisco, light brown sugar, milk and vanilla in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until well blended.
Add egg.
Beat just until blended.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture at low speed.
Mix just until blended.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet. Variation:
Flatten slightly in crisscross pattern with tines of fork.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes, or until set and just beginning to brown.
Cool 2 minutes on baking sheet before removing to kitchen countertop.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: potato skins - low cholesterol
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Scrub potatoes well; cut lengthwise into 6 wedges and dry on paper towel.
In a large bowl, toss potato spears with olive oil until they are well covered.
Spread potatoes on a baking sheet; dust with paprika and bake 20 to 30 minutes, or until fork-tender.
Serves 6.
Per serving:
79 total calories, 3 sat. fat calories.

title: chocolate-mint shamrocks
directions: Mix sugar, margarine, shortening, vanilla, eggs and food color in a large bowl.
Stir in flour, baking soda and salt.
Stir in chopped chocolate chips.
Divide dough into 4 parts.
Shape each part of dough into a roll, 1-inch in diameter and about 10 inches long.

title: crock-pot beef tips
directions: Roll beef tips in flour and brown in oil in skillet.
After browning, put tips in crock-pot and add consomme, water, bouillon cube, and onion.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cook on low heat until done.
Serve with potatoes or rice and a green salad or green vegetable.
Serves 6.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Cut Crisco in flour.
Add cheese.
Mix into a wet dough with milk.
Place on floured board and work only enough to handle.
Cut biscuits and bake at 425° until browned.

title: onion rice
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered.
After half hour, open and stir.

title: sugar-free strawberry pie
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine Jell-O, pudding and water. Cook until boiling; cool (will thicken as it cools).
Add strawberries.
Pour into pie shell.
Refrigerate for at least 2 hours.

title: fudge nut bars
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Mix in eggs and 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Sift together flour, soda and 1 teaspoon salt; stir in oats.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Set aside while you make filling.

title: rodney's duck gumbo
directions: Boil ducks with 6 pods of garlic, onions, beer, salt and pepper until the meat starts to fall off the bone.
If you can, turn the heat off.
Cover pot and let it set overnight or until good and cool.

title: cheesy chicken bake
directions: Take skin off chicken and place in oblong baking dish. Sprinkle spices to taste over chicken. Melt butter and mix with soup. Slice cheese and place over chicken. Pour soup and butter mixture over this. Bake at 375° for approximately 1 1/2 hours, uncovered.

title: lemon tea bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add beaten eggs and lemon peel. Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add alternately with milk.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done and lightly browned on top. Let cool in pan 15 minutes.
Dissolve 1/3 cup sugar in lemon juice; pour over bread.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: baked potato casserole
directions: Mix soups and milk.
Place potatoes in a large greased baking dish.
Pour soup mixture over potatoes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Toss to coat potatoes.
Put butter on top.
sprinkle with cheese, completely covering.
Cover and bake at 350° until thoroughly heated and cheese is melted.
Uncover, top with bacon bits, and bake an additional 5 minutes.

title: tunnel ridge hot dogs
directions: Pour barbecue sauce into pan and bring to simmer.
Add 3/4 of cup of grape jelly.
Stir until melted.
Add hot dogs; stir.
Keep hot while serving.

title: microwaved scalloped potatoes
directions: Microwave on High 251/2 to 291/2 minutes total.

title: oven chicken
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add chicken coated with flour, salt, pepper and paprika.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes. Over chicken, add pineapple, pepper, onion and brown sugar.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes more.

title: chocolate cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Combine butter, crumbs and sugar. Pat firmly on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan. In large mixer bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy. Add condensed milk; beat until smooth. Add remaining ingredients. Mix well. Pour into pan. Bake 1 hour and 5 minutes or until top is set. Cool at room temperature. Chill and then remove sides of pan.

title: cheese cake(serves 12)
directions: Mix zwieback with 1/2 cup sugar, cinnamon and butter or shortening.

Set aside 3/4 cup to sprinkle on top; press remainder of crumbs into a 9-inch spring-form pan, lining bottom and sides. Beat eggs with remaining 1 cup sugar until light; add salt, lemon juice and rind, cream, cheese and flour; beat thoroughly and strain through a fine sieve.
Pour into lined pan; sprinkle with remaining crumbs and nut meats.
Bake in a moderate oven (350°) about 1 hour or until center is firm.
Turn off heat, open oven door and let stand in oven 1 hour or until cooled.

title: creamy lime squares(low calorie)
directions: Pour gelatin in a bowl.
Stir in hot water and dissolve thoroughly.
Stir in cold water.
Chill until syrupy.
Combine cottage cheese and crushed pineapple in a blender or processor. Process until smooth.
Add gelatin mixture; process until well blended.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch square dish.
Chill until firm.

title: ham a la cajsa warg
directions: Take ham.
Ham which is to be roasted in a oven must not be too salty and should be placed in plenty of cold water for approximately 12 hours.
Remove the rind.
Place the ham on a large piece of baking foil.
Crush corns, marjoram and bay leaves in a mortar.
Rub the spice mixture on all sides of the ham.
Wrap the foil around the ham to make a tight package.
Insert a meat thermometer through the foil so that the tip reaches the thickest and meatiest part of the ham.
Place the ham in a baking pan and bake it in a 350° oven.
The ham is ready when the thermometer shows 170°.
Ham a la Cajsa Warg can be served hot or cold with boiled potatoes, mustard, red cabbage or other vegetables.

title: cocktail sauce
directions: Combine and chill.
Serve with oysters, clams, shrimp, lobster or crabmeat.
Mix together or use as dip.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix
all ingredients and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Blend shortening and sugars.
Blend in egg and vanilla; mix well.
Add combined dry ingredients; mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer the first 4 ingredients in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Cover with shredded Colby cheese, being sure to cover all.
Put Miracle Whip on top, covering completely.
Sprinkle sugar over Miracle Whip.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Mix just before serving.

title: pink congealed salad
directions: Combine condensed milk and lemon juice in large bowl; mix well.
Stir in cherry pie filling and pineapple; mix well.
Fold in whipped topping, nuts and dates.
If a darker shade of pink is desired, add a few drops of red food coloring.
Pour mixture into 9 x 13-inch dish.
Refrigerate several hours before serving. Makes 12 servings.

title: grandma ricci's bracciole
directions: Mix raisins, chopped garlic, parsley, pine nuts and Parmesan cheese in bowl.
With mallet, pound beef until 1/8-inch thick. Spread mixture across slices of beef and roll meat jelly roll fashion; salt and pepper.
Tie meat with string.
Brown rolled beef in small amount of oil or Pam.
Finish cooking in prepared simmering Italian sauce for 1 hour.
Remove string before serving.

title: fettucini
directions: Cook fettucini noodles as directed on box.
Put 1 stick butter (sliced) and whipping cream in a bowl at room temperature for about 1 hour.
Drain fettucini and add 1 stick butter.
Stir thoroughly.
Now add the 1 stick of butter and cream mixture and parsley.
Stir together thoroughly.
Now add the two cups Parmesan cheese and stir thoroughly.

title: halushki
directions: Cut up cabbage and onions in a large pot and cook covered in 1/2 pound butter.
Add salt and pepper.
Stir occasionally.
Cook until tender.
Cook Kluski noodles.
Drain and mix with cabbage and onions.
Add 1/4 pound butter (if desired).

title: kascaron
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Deep fry at 350° until golden brown.
Drain.
Roll in sugar or honey. Skewer 3 to a stick.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream well eggs, sugar and oil.
Add flour, soda, salt and cinnamon and mix well.
Then add apples, coconut, nuts and vanilla.
Batter will be very stiff.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: 7 layer casserole
directions: Place uncooked rice in a buttered 2-quart casserole.
Add a layer of corn, half the tomatoes and half the water, onions, green pepper and uncooked beef.
Salt and pepper each layer; pour remaining tomatoes and water over ingredients.
Season to taste. Cover and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Remove cover; bake for 30 minutes longer.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions.
Combine with all other ingredients and place in buttered casserole dish, 9 x 12-inches. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: seaside submarines
directions: Separate mackerel fillets into large pieces.
Mix half the Piquant sauce with the fish.
Spread on bottom halves of rolls. Arrange cheese, tomato and onion slices over mackerel.
Spread remaining sauce on cut sides of tops of rolls.
Place over the sandwiches.
Cut each sandwich in half to serve.
Makes 4 sandwiches.

title: bean soup
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add onions, tomatoes and spinach. Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients. Rinse and drain kidney beans.
Heat to boil; cover and simmer for 45 minutes.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: artichoke frittata(serves 16)
directions: Drain artichokes and keep juice from 1 jar.
Take artichoke juice, onion, parsley and garlic and cook until limp.
Beat 4 eggs and the Cheddar cheese and cracker crumbs.
Mix with other ingredients chopped artichokes.
Bake in a shallow 9 x 13-inch greased pan for 30 minutes at 350°.
Cut in squares and serve hot. May also be served at room temperature.

title: crock-pot layered enchilada casserole
directions: To prepare sauce, blend tomatoes in their liquid with onion and garlic in a blender or food processor.
Pour into medium-sized saucepan.
Add red pepper, salt and tomato paste.
Heat to a boil; simmer for 5 to 10 minutes.
Place 3 tortillas in bottom of crock-pot.
Layer on tortillas 1/3 of the ground beef, 1/3 tomato sauce and 1/3 of Cheddar cheese.
Repeat each layer two more times.
Cover and cook on low, 6 to 8 hours.
Makes 4 servings.

title: batter fried okra
directions: Cut up okra into 1/4-inch slices.
Beat egg in a container; add milk and stir together.
Stir okra into mixture until coated.
Put meal and flour into a small paper bag.
Shake well to mix flour and meal.
Place a small amount of okra into bag and shake until okra is coated.
Place 1/2-inch of cooking oil in a frying pan and heat. Place okra into hot oil and fry until brown.

title: quick crab soup
directions: Bring soup to a boil; add remaining ingredients along with crab meat.
Delicious.
Serves 4.

title: watermelon and watercress salad
directions: Mix dressing ingredients (oil, vinegar, lime juice, ginger root and turbinado) together well in a shaker jar and store overnight in fridge before using. Mix the watermelon chunks and watercress leaves. Small, tender stems are okay left on the cress. Toss with the dressing and serve immediately. Serves 6.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli and set aside.
In separate pan, melt and stir cheese and 1/2 stick margarine; then add to broccoli. Mix the melted margarine and crackers together and put on top of casserole.

title: breakfast sausage and cheese bake
directions: Line bottom and 1/2-inch up sides of 9 x 13-inch baking dish with
roll	dough; press seams to seal.
Brown sausage in skillet, stirring
until
crumbly; drain.
Sprinkle into prepared dish. Top with cheese.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in a small amount of boiling, salted water until tender.
Drain.
Cook bacon in a frypan until crisp.
Remove from pan and chop.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed. Add soup. Pour into baking dish. Layer cheese on top. Add melted butter to crumbled crackers, stirring well. Add to top of casserole. Microwave 5 minutes or bake until bubbly.

title: tabouli salad
directions: Chop all vegetables very fine.
Put cracked wheat in a bowl. Add oil, vegetables, juice of lemons and seasonings.
Mix all together.
Marinate in refrigerator a few hours.
Season again to taste.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: chocolate chip brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream together margarine and sugars. Add 2 slightly beaten egg yolks, water and vanilla; mix.
Add dry ingredients.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips.
Beat 2 egg whites until stiff, gradually adding 1 cup brown sugar.
Spread over top.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: gooey date bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add flour and baking powder sifted together.
Add dates and nuts and mix well.
Spread in a greased and floured pan and bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
When cool, cut into squares and roll in powdered sugar. Will keep for weeks if packed in a tin box.

title: zucchini bars
directions: Melt margarine and hot water in a pan.
Add brown sugar and mix well.
Let cool.
Beat eggs and vanilla, then add to previous mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Grease an 11 x 17-inch cookie sheet with cooking spray.
Add the batter and sprinkle a 6 ounce package of butterscotch bits on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes (watch closely).
Let cool before cutting into squares.

title: bugs-bunny salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together, even if they complain, except lettuce leaves, in a mixing bowl.
Cover with red plastic wrap and refrigerate for 15 minutes.
Remove from refrigerator.
Toss into air and catch in bowl 5 times.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Eat in a munching fashion.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Combine crumbs and butter.
Press into an 8-inch baking dish. Bake for 8 minutes at 350°.
Saute onions until tender; place on top of cracker mixture.
Mix other ingredients, except for cheese; pour over onions.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix sugar, peanut butter, cream cheese and milk until smooth, add cool whip.
Makes two pies.
Put in chocolate cookie crust or reduced fat graham crust.

title: almond brittle
directions: Melt butter in heavy skillet.
Add sugar, water and white Karo syrup.
Cook to hard crack (290° to 300°), stir constantly.
Add almonds.
Spread on cookie sheet and break in pieces when cool. Great with walnuts, too.

title: green bean-corn casserole
directions: Mix green beans, celery soup, corn, water chestnuts, onion and celery in a casserole dish.
Top with sour cream, grated cheese and then crushed Ritz crackers.
Drizzle with butter.
Bake at 325° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: orange cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° in Bundt pan.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Soak chicken in buttermilk several hours.
Roll in seasoned bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until tender.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Blend in a blender.

title: old english banana bread
directions: Mash bananas into sugar; add egg and shortening and stir. Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add to banana mixture. Next, add nuts and vanilla.
Put in loaf pan and bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: carol's chili
directions: Brown beef tips
in vegetable oil.
Add remaining ingredients, bring to a boil for 5 minutes, then simmer for 1 hour.

title: banana split cake ii
directions: Follow directions on cake mix package and prepare two round cake layers.
Allow to cool.
In large, glass bowl, layer:
cake, bananas, pineapple and strawberries.
Repeat with second cake layer.
Top with Cool Whip and pecans.
Drizzle chocolate syrup over top.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix until crumbs form.
Pat evenly in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Combine flour and sugar in a bowl.
Melt butter. Add cocoa and Coca-Cola and heat to boiling point. Cool slightly.
Pour over flour and sugar. Stir until blended. Add soda (dissolved in buttermilk), eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Stir in marshmallows and pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. This will be thin batter with marshmallows coming to top.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix
all
ingredients together.
Pour into glass baking dish. Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.	Serves 8.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Cook hamburger and onion in 10-inch skillet.
Stir in soup, salt, garlic, pepper and flour.
Cook 5 minutes stirring constantly.
Stir in soup and heat to boiling; stir constantly. Simmer uncovered 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream or yogurt and heat through.
Serve over hot noodles or rice.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend cream cheese and sugar together.
Add peanut butter and fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into pie shells.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix into small balls.
Bake in a 350° oven on greased cookie sheet.

title: crazy cake
directions: Mix flour, cocoa, soda, sugar and salt.
Sift right into greased, square 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Now make 3 holes in this dry mixture.
Into one, pour the oil.
Into the next, pour the vinegar.
Into the third, pour the vanilla.
Now pour cold water over it all.
Beat with a spoon until batter is nearly smooth and you can't see the flour.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Ice.

title: just corn
directions: Peel and slice sweet potatoes.
Cook potatoes in water for 5 to 10 minutes and add 1 teaspoon of vanilla.
Save water to add later. Make dough like you would biscuits.
Roll out thin strips and cover the bottom and sides with strips.
Use deep pan.
Lay sweet potatoes in bottom of pan, then put margarine on potatoes. Sprinkle sugar over margarine.
Repeat potatoes, magarine and sugar until you use all the potatoes, then pour the water which you used to cook the potatoes in and cover the potatoes completely.
Next, cut more dough strips and cover the top.
Then brush or cut small pieces on top of the dough.
Sprinkle sugar on top.
Very old recipe.

title: super easy cheese ball
directions: Bring cream cheese and
Cheddar cheese to room temperature. Mix together.
Stir
in
liquid smoke.
Shape into ball or log and roll in chopped nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: maryland crab cakes
directions: In a bowl, mix all ingredients, except crabmeat, thoroughly. Add crabmeat and mix gently.
Shape into cakes (6 to 8, depending on size).
Cook in frying pan in just enough oil to prevent sticking, until browned, about 5 minutes on each side.

title: red raspberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water in a bowl.
Stir in raspberries and applesauce.
Spoon into dish or mold.
Chill overnight.
Makes 6 servings.

title: ravioli
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Pour off grease.
Add soup, sauce and water.
Cook macaroni separately and pour into mixture.
Add 1/2 cup grated Cheddar cheese and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: french hamburgers
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients in bowl.
Spread evenly over bun halves, covering completely.
Place on baking sheet and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes 6 sandwiches.

title: poached halibut
directions: Combine water, wine, salt, bay leaf, peppercorns, thyme and parsley; bring to boil.
Add halibut.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 10 minutes per inch of thickness measured at its thickest part or until halibut flakes easily when tested with fork.
Gently remove halibut and drain.
Serve hot or chilled.
Garnish with cucumber slices.
Serve with Creamy Cucumber Dill Sauce.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: peanut butter cup bars
directions: Melt butter; stir in graham cracker crumbs, peanut butter and sugar. Pat into 9 x 13 pan.
Melt chocolate chips and frost top of mixture.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Chill overnight.
Make	into balls and roll in powdered sugar. Place on
greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: waterfront sunset
directions: Shake all ingredients together and pour over ice in a tall glass.

title: inside-out pizza
directions: Place one tortilla on a sheet of wax paper and sprinkle with cheese.
Add pepperoni.
Dribble sauce over all.
Cover with other tortilla.
Set on microwave-safe plate.
Cover with wax paper. Microwave on High for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes.
Cool, then cut in wedges.
Serves 2.

title: company limas
directions: Cook limas in water to cover. Cook 12 minutes on medium heat. Add salt to taste. Fry sausage; remove from grease.
Using 2 tablespoons grease, saute onion until soft. Add sausage and onion to limas. Cook, adding a pinch of sugar, until done, about 15 minutes.

title: mountain dew jello
directions: Make the lemon Jell-O with 2 cups of boiling hot water.
Then pour in 2 cups of cold Mountain Dew.
Then pour into 9 x 13-inch cake pan and put into the refrigerator.
When the Jell-O starts to harden, add the sliced bananas, pineapple chunks and miniature marshmallows.
Then place the Jell-O back in the refrigerator until firm.
When firm, mix the lemon pie filling and Cool Whip together in a separate bowl.
Spread this on the Jell-O.
Then let set for an hour in the refrigerator.

title: workout snack mix
directions: Combine cereal and nuts in 2-quart baking dish.
Combine margarine and next 4 ingredients and pour over cereal mixture. Toss to coat.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes; stir every 5 minutes. Remove from oven; immediately add popcorn.
Toss gently to coat; let cool completely.
Store in an airtight container.
Yields 5 cups (76 calories per 1/3 cup).

title: norwegian apple pie
directions: Mix apples and nuts
together.
Mix rest of ingredients together and stir in apples.
Bake for 30
minutes
in
2 (9-inch)
pie pans at 350°.

title: wacky cake
directions: Place the above in greased baking pan (9 x 13-inch) and make three holes separately in mixture.
Place 1 teaspoon white vinegar in one hole, 1 teaspoon vanilla in one hole and 5 tablespoons salad oil in the final hole.
Pour 1 cup water over mixture and mix well.
Bake in the oven at 375° for approximately 25 minutes.

title: ro-tel chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Pull chicken from bone.
Mix all canned goods together.
In a baking dish, make one layer of chips, then a layer of chicken.
Pour soup mixture over chicken and chips.
Top mixture with chips.
Bake until hot and bubbly, about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Combine shortening and sugar, creaming until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Combine flour and salt.
Add to creamed mixture, alternating with buttermilk.
Stir in flavorings.

title: corn casserole
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish, melt margarine.
Stir in other ingredients, except cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Sprinkle one half package of pizza cheese over top and return to oven until cheese melts.
This makes a large casserole, so you can make two and freeze one.
Add a little milk to the frozen one. Serves 6.

title: mini meatball stew
directions: Combine beef, onion, chili powder and salt.
Shape into small meatballs.
Brown in large skillet and drain fat.
Arrange vegetables in skillet with meatballs.
Pour sauce over mixture. Cover.
Simmer for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: potato cakes
directions: Boil potatoes until tender and mash. Add salt, pepper, margarine and milk. Add egg and flour to mash potatoes. Place small cakes in greased skillet and cook until brown.

title: celery au gratin for 2
directions: Boil celery and optional ingredients if desired in chicken broth in small saucepan until tender.
Beat egg well.
Pour small amount of hot broth into egg, stirring constantly.
Stir egg into celery quickly.
Pour into microwavable bowl.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Microwave on High until thickens almost to center. Place under broiler to nicely brown.

title: truffles
directions: Melt chocolate over hot water.
Combine cream and half and half.
Heat to scalding; cool cream mixture to 130°.
Add to melted chocolate all at once, beating until smooth and well blended.
Add vanilla and blend into mixture.
Chill in refrigerator until candy is firm but pliable.
Beat with mixer until candy is light and fluffy, then return to refrigerator until firm.
Form into 3/4 inch balls and immediately dip into dipping chocolate; set on wax paper to set up.

title: sausage chowder
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook for 1 hour.
Serve with fruit salad and fresh bread or bread sticks.

title: white chili(serves 8)
directions: Soak beans in water to cover in saucepan for several hours; drain.
Combine beans with chicken broth, garlic and half the onions in saucepan.
Simmer for 3 hours or until beans are tender. Saute remaining onions in oil in skillet.
Stir in green chilies, cumin, oregano, cloves and pepper.
Add to beans.
Stir in chicken.
Simmer, covered, for 1 hour, adding additional broth, if needed, for desired consistency.
Top servings with cheese. Garnish with chopped green onions.

title: microwave chicken and rice casserole
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a 10 x 10 baking dish.
Lay chicken thighs on top of rice mixture.

title: petey's rhubarb pie
directions: Sprinkle bottom of unbaked pie crust with sugar.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into crust. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes. Spread meringue on cool pie. Brown at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: In bowl, combine eggs, sugar, corn syrup, butter, vanilla and salt.
Blend well.
Sprinkle pecans in bottom of pie shell.
Pour sugar mixture over nuts.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve slightly warm. Garnish with sweetened whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.

title: savory brown rice
directions: Heat butter in a 2-quart saucepan over medium to low heat. Add seasoning blend and saut until tender, but not browned.
Add thyme, oregano and broth; let boil. Add rice and return to boiling.
Stir; cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir.
Replace cover and allow to stand for 5 more minutes.
Fluff rice with a fork, then serve.
Serves 6.

title: pineapple chicken(microwave)
directions: Place chicken pieces in glass 2-quart casserole dish. Cover with wax paper. Microwave on High for 12 minutes. Turn chicken over. Combine pineapple, soup and raisins. Pour over chicken. Cook in microwave oven, uncovered, on High for 12 to 15 minutes more.

title: guacamole
directions: Chop small or mash avocado; add chopped tomato, minced onion and chopped shallots and mix.
Add seasoning, oil and juice and blend well.
Serve cold on tortillas, melba toast, little hot biscuits or little hot crepes, rolled.

title: mike's barbecue sauce
directions: Boil for a few minutes all ingredients.
Good to sop on chicken while grilling.

title: fudgy pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium saucepan, over low heat, melt chocolate with butter.
Stir in sweetened (Eagle Brand) milk, hot water and eggs; mix well.
Remove from heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes, or until center is set.
Cool slightly.
Serve warm or chilled. Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: chocolate fudge pecan pie
directions: To prepare crust, place butter and cream cheese in mixing bowl.
Blend until softened.
Work in flour until mixture forms a dough.

title: shoney's strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and water and let come to a good boil.
Stir in strawberry jello.
Let cool until slightly thickened. Pour over the strawberries in the pie shell and refrigerate.
Add Cool Whip before you serve.

title: chocolate fondue or sauce
directions: An inexpensive cleaner to keep those pots at their height of brilliance is a paste made with:
salt (for abrasion), vinegar (for cleaning) and a little flour to make a paste so it will stay on the pot while you scrub it.

title: refrigerator fudge
directions: Place chips in top of double boiler over hot water; stir frequently until melted and smooth (or place chips in saucepan and stir carefully over very low heat). Stir in remaining ingredients. Pour in an 8 x 8 pan, lined with wax paper. Refrigerate
until firm. Remove from pan; peel off paper and cut. Makes 2 pounds.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: In a large bowl mix hamburg and cooked rice.
Add salt, pepper and garlic powder to taste.
Add mixture to cored peppers.
Place in Dutch oven.
Add the tomato soup and water.
Cook on the top of stove for about 1 hour.

title: easy seafood dip
directions: Chop everything fine and mix all ingredients together. Can bake at 350° for 20 minutes or serve cold with crackers.

title: chicken tacos
directions: Mix all and bring to boil.
Line 13 x 9-inch pan with crushed Doritos and grated Cheddar cheese.
Cover with mixture and top with more crushed Doritos and more cheese.
Heat at 350° until cheese melts and is warm throughout.

title: one pot dinner
directions: Combine all
ingredients
in crock-pot.
Cover and cook on low 4 to 9 hours.

title: roasted pecans
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Heat butter or margarine in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan until melted.
Stir in seasoned salt and Worcestershire sauce; add nuts, mixing until all pieces are coated.
(You need only enough margarine to coat all the pecans, so you may be able to put more than 6 cups of pecans in.)
Heat in oven 1 1/2 hours, stirring every 15 minutes.
Spread on paper towels to cool.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Cream the first 5 ingredients.
Add dry ingredients, then spread on 2 (10 x 15 x 1-inch) greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Frost with filling.

title: balsamic chicken and peppers
directions: Pound chicken to 1/2-inch thick.
Rub with combined flour, coriander and salt.
Brown chicken in oil in 10-inch skillet over medium heat on each side.
Remove and reserve.
Add onion, garlic and red pepper to skillet.
Cook and stir 2 minutes; garnish with green onions.
Serve over rice.

title: squash pickles
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; let stand for 1 hour.
In saucepan, bring to a boil the vinegar, sugar and seeds.
Add squash, onions, peppers and salt.
Boil 5 minutes.
Place in jars and seal.

title: smoked sausage, kale and orzo
directions: Slice sausage into half moon shapes and set aside.
Heat large soup pot over medium heat.
Add sausage and saute 2 minutes. Add roasted garlic.
Saute mixture 1 minute and add broth and orzo.
Simmer.
Stir soup frequently until orzo is fully cooked, 10-15 minutes.
Clean and finely slice the kale, add to the soup along with chile flakes and cheese.
Stir until smooth and kale begins to turn bright green.
Serve with extra cheese and chile flakes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain 1 large can pineapple chunks; set juice aside.
Drain 1 large can Mandarin orange slices; set juice aside.
Combine pineapple, Mandarin oranges, 2 to 3 large bananas (sliced), one pint fresh or frozen strawberries (sliced) and one large can cherry pie filling.

title: corned beef hash
directions: Cook and drain potatoes.
Place in a frying pan.
Add other ingredients and fry 15 minutes on low heat.

title: blackberry buckle
directions: Mix together sugar, butter and egg.
Stir in milk.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt. Stir into batter.
Mix well. Carefully blend into blueberries.
Spread batter into greased and floured 9-inch square pan.

title: black forest cake
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chocolate chips.
Mix until blended, then beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Fold in chocolate chips and pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: busy day casserole(microwave)
directions: Brown the ground beef 3 minutes on High; drain.
Arrange noodles on top of meat.
Mix tomato sauce, onion soup and water; pour over noodles.
Do not mix.
Microwave 10 minutes on High. Microwave 5 minutes on High.
Let stand, covered, for 5 minutes.

title: buttermilk cinnamon bars
directions: Pour
over
mixture
and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Delicious with browned butter icing.

title: papa jim's meatloaf
directions: In small bowl, mix together ketchup and reserved liquid from mushrooms and set aside.
In large bowl, mix together ground beef, spices, green chiles, mushrooms, eggs, crackers and onion.
Mix thoroughly (using your hands is easiest).
Form into a loaf and put in large loaf pan.
Lay bacon slices on top of loaf.
Pour ketchup mixture on top of bacon.
You may use the new pans that have holes to drain fat from the pan.
Bake in oven at 325 degrees for 50 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: fresh tomato salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Marinate at least 4 to 5 hours.

title: apple crunch
directions: Spread apples in a baking dish.
Cover with sugar and sprinkle with spice (either nutmeg or cinnamon).
Mix the remaining ingredients until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Spread over apples.
Bake slowly (300°) for 1 hour.

title: colored pasta, rice, sugar, etc.
directions: Mix ingredients for food coloring solution.
Let liquid cool at room temperature before dipping strung pasta.
The longer it is submerged, the darker the color will be.
Hang to dry.
Color rice, sugar and salt by placing in a jar with mixture.
Close jar and shake.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients together in a big bowl.
Spoon onto large cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Last 3 ingredients are optional.
Pecans make it good and cinnamon and vanilla add flavor to the mix.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Place chicken in greased baking dish.
Cover with cheese. Combine soup with wine; pour over cheese.
Sprinkle with stuffing; drizzle with butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 hour.

title: sloppy janes
directions: In pot, combine frankfurters with beans, mustard, onion and chili sauce.
Cover and cook on low for 2 to 3 hours.
Spoon over toasted hot dog buns.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Drain, rinse and chop shrimp.
Mix well with other ingredients. Makes about 2 cups of creamy dip.

title: layered salad
directions: Tear lettuce and place in bottom of a long casserole dish. Layer vegetables.
Spread mayonnaise and sprinkle with cheese, bacon and sugar. Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Heat potatoes in syrup; drain and whip until fluffy.
Add butter and other ingredients.
Beat well (I use mixer).
Pour into buttered casserole.
Bake about 2 minutes at 350°.
While baking, prepare the topping.

title: grilled crabcakes
directions: Prepare crabcakes:
Combine crab, 1/4 cup fine bread crumbs, egg, mayonnaise, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, salt, pepper and the 3 tablespoons minced parsley in a deep bowl.
Form into six firm patties.
Roll patties in flour, then dip into the beaten eggs.
Roll in bread crumbs.

title: banana muffins
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease muffin tins.
Measure all ingredients in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed for 1/2 minute, scraping sides and bottom of bowl constantly.
Pour approximately 1/4 cup of batter into each muffin tin.
Bake until brown.
Remove from pan.

title: cavatini
directions: Brown ground chuck, pepper and onion together. Drain grease. Cook macaroni as directed on the box. Drain. Mix all ingredients, except cheese, and pour into a large baking dish. Top with cheese and bake at 400° until hot through and cheese is melted.

title: pizza squares
directions: Cook and drain sausage. Mix with oregano, Worcestershire sauce and ketchup.
Cut Velveeta into cubes.
Mix with meat mixture and heat on stove or in microwave.
Spread on slices of party rye. Freeze.

title: strawberry sherbet
directions: Pour everything into freezer and it will mix when the freezer starts to turn.

title: cool whip pie
directions: Mix softened cream cheese, sugar and pineapple, using mixer. Add pecans.
Fold in Cool Whip and beat.
Pile mixture into 2 crusts and cover.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: poppy seed chicken casserole
directions: Mix and put in lightly greased casserole dish.

title: unbaked cookies
directions: Bring sugar, oleo, milk and peanut butter to boil; take off stove.
Add oatmeal, vanilla and cocoa.
Mix well and drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.

title: amish sugar cookies
directions: Combine sugar, powdered sugar, margarine and oil.
Beat well. Add eggs.
Beat again.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Drop small balls of dough on ungreased sheet and flatten with a fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar while warm.

title: herb cheese
directions: Combine water, lemon juice and cheese in a blender of food processor.
Puree for 1 minute or until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients and blend for 30 seconds.
Cover and chill.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: fruited ham slice
directions: Score fat or remove fat from ham.
Depending on slice of ham, place in 8-inch square dish or 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Drain syrup from fruit and save; arrange fruit over ham.
Place dish in microwave and cook 10 minutes.
Combine syrup, sugar, cornstarch and cloves; pour over ham.
Continue cooking 8 to 10 more minutes. Spoon juices over fruit and serve.

title: reception salad
directions: Mash cream cheese with pimentos.
Combine ingredients.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, egg and applesauce together, then add rest of ingredients.
Bake in tube pan 45 to 60 minutes.

title: salmon patties
directions: Drain salmon, reserving liquid.
Combine cracker crumbs and reserved liquid.
Let stand at least 5 minutes.
Stir in salmon, cornmeal, egg, salt and pepper.
Shape into 6 patties.
Fry in hot oil until browned, turning once.
Drain on paper towel.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Cook together, except whipped cream, until thick.
Cool.
Add whipped cream.
Mix all together and chill.
Even better the next day.

title: heavenly rolls
directions: Combine milk, butter and sugar. Cool to lukewarm. Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water, add yeast mixture, egg yolk, lemon rind and salt to milk mixture. Add 4 c. flour and beat until satiny. Cover

and let rise until full of bubbles. Continue to add flour mixture until a stiff batter is formed. Knead lightly until smoothe. Place in greased bowl and let rise until very light. Bake 20 minutes at 375°. Yields 20 to 24 servings.

title: peach cobbler
directions: If frozen peaches are used, add 2 more cups sugar.

title: cheese ball
directions: Have cream cheese and dried beef at room temperature.
Blend all ingredients together; mix well.
Chill in refrigerator.
Shape into 1 large or 2 small balls.
May roll in chopped nuts or dried beef pieces, if desired.

title: lemony cheesecake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. In medium mixing bowl, combine crumbs, pecans, sugar and melted butter; mix well. Reserve 1/3 cup; press remaining mixture into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake for 6 minutes. Remove and cool on wire rack.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar, flour, eggs, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, Wesson oil and carrots together.
Butter and flour 2 layered cake pans.
Pour batter into cake pan; place in oven for 30 minutes, or until cake is firm.

title: green beans and stewed tomatoes(great low-fat, low calorie dish!)
directions: Put all ingredients in medium pan with cover.
Bring to a boil and simmer for at least 30 minutes (about 25 calories per serving).
Serves 6 to 8.

title: quick italian spinach pie
directions: Thaw spinach and drain well.
Drain and chop red peppers. Mix all ingredients together and pour into a greased 9-inch pie plate. Bake at 350 degrees for 40 minutes or until center is set.

title: chop suey
directions: Brown pork; add onion and cook until clear.
Add celery and water.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Make sauce, adding flour, sugar and soy sauce.
Mix well; add to meat mixture and stir until thick.
Add bean sprouts and simmer until sprouts are heated through.
Serve over cooked rice.
Sprinkle Chinese noodles on top.

title: german potato salad
directions: Blend flour and 2 tablespoons water in a small saucepan; add remaining water, vinegar, sugar, pepper and 2 teaspoons salt.
Stir until mixture boils.
Place potatoes, onion, green pepper and celery in a large bowl and toss lightly.
Pour in hot dressing and mix well.
Cool to room temperature; add crumbled bacon and eggs. Toss again.
Taste for salt; add more if needed.
Serve at room temperature.
Serves 6, about 250 calories per serving.

title: party punch
directions: Mix ingredients.
Add crushed ice and float with lemon rings.

title: yogurt rolls
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; set aside.
Dissolve yeast in warm water in large mixing bowl and let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in yogurt mixture and eggs.
Combine flour and salt.
Stir 2 cups flour mixture into yogurt mixture and beat at medium speed with electric mixer until smooth.
Gradually stir in remaining flour mixture, cover and put in a warm place, letting rise until doubled in bulk, approximately 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Punch dough down and shape as desired.
Place on baking sheets coated with cooking spray.
Cover, let rise until double in bulk.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yield: 4 dozen (66 calories per roll).

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli.
Put in bowl and separate with fork.
Blend mayonnaise, cheese, eggs and onions.
Stir in with broccoli.
Pour mixture into 9 x 12-inch glass baking dish.
Cover with crushed Ritz crackers or more shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Makes 8 or more servings.

title: million dollar cake
directions: In
a
large
bowl
using
an electric mixer, cream the butter and sugar.	Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add milk,
crushed
vanilla
wafers, nuts and coconut. Mix
well. Pour
into	a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.	This is a great snack cake that doesn't need frosting.

title: short ribs and gravy
directions: Roll ribs in flour, slowly brown on all sides.
Place in baking dish, season with salt and pepper, 1 medium sliced onion and 1 cup water.
Cover and bake.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Drain but do not remove from saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook over low heat, stirring frequently, until cheese melts, about 5 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pizza casserole(very good)
directions: Brown meat and onion. Drain.
Add pizza sauce, salt, pepper and Italian seasoning.
Mix.
Cook macaroni.
Drain and mix with milk and beaten egg.
Add to meat sauce.
Pour in baking dish. Top with items of your choice (I use mushrooms and pepperoni).
Top all with 1 cup shredded Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8. Teenagers love it!

title: pickled mushrooms
directions: In saucepan, combine all ingredients except mushrooms.
Bring to boiling.
Add mushrooms and return to boiling.
Simmer, uncovered, 8 to 10 minutes.
Ladle into hot sealed jars or cool and store in covered container in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Makes 2 1/2 pints.

title: cheese fudge
directions: Heat cheese, chocolate and corn syrup in a 3-quart saucepan over low heat until melted.
Gradually add sugar to mixture, beating on medium until smooth.
Stir in pecans and vanilla; pour in buttered pan.
Smooth surface.
Cover and refrigerate several hours.
Cut into squares.
Makes 3 1/2 pounds.

title: ham ball
directions: Mix together ham, relish, mayonnaise, salt and pepper and form ball.
Refrigerate approximately 1 hour until hardened.
Spread softened cream cheese over ham ball and sprinkle crushed pecans over top and sides.
Serve with crackers.

title: harvard beets
directions: Cook all ingredients, less the beets until thick.
Then add beets, cook until beets are hot.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Heat oleo, sugar, eggs, vinegar and vanilla.
Add pecans, coconut and raisins.
Pour into 2 pie crusts and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: carrot with onions
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, combine carrots, onion, water, thyme, salt, garlic powder and pepper.
Microwave at 100% power for 6 to 8 minutes (until carrots are crisp-tender).
Add margarine; toss.
Makes 3 to 4 servings; only 62 calories and 1 gram fat.

title: new england boiled dinner
directions: Place meat into heavy skillet.
Cover with hot water.
Simmer about 3 hours.
Skim off excess fat and add onion, carrots, potatoes and turnips.
Cover and cook 20 minutes.
Add cabbage and continue cooking 10 to 15 minutes.

title: b.j.'s incredible cheese bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread on split loaves of French bread.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes until bubbly and beginning to brown.
This is excellent with lasagne or spaghetti and a tossed salad.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Chop broccoli and onion; cover with water and cook 15 minutes on high.
Lower heat and add canned milk and whole milk.
Add thickening and mushroom soup; stir often.
Simmer on low heat for 10 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: sweet "n" sour chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces in shallow 9 x 13-inch baking dish in single layer.
Combine salad dressing, soup mix and preserves; pour over chicken.

title: spring salad
directions: Boil noodles. Mix rest of ingredients in bowl. Add noodles. Chill overnight.

title: chicken and cheese burritos
directions: Boil chicken until thoroughly cooked.
Shred and mix with the mushroom soup.
Spread onto tortillas.
Top with both cheeses. Roll up burrito.
Top with more cheese, if desired.
Cook at 350° for about 15 to 20 minutes or until crispy.

title: miracle cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish.
Prepare a batter of sugar, flour, milk, baking powder and vanilla.
Pour into greased dish. Over batter, spread can of fruit.
Bake in 375° oven for 45 minutes.

title: salsa romesco(serves 1)
directions: Place the almonds, garlic and tomatoes on a roasting pan in a 200° oven.
Remove the nuts when toasted, about 5 minutes, and the tomatoes and garlic when the skins are blistered, about 30 minutes.
Grind the almonds.
Place the chiles in a saucepan with the vinegar and water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce the heat and simmer for 5 minutes.
