After removing the skins from the tomatoes and garlic, put them in a blender, along with the nuts, chiles and vinegar; puree to a smooth paste.

title: quick 'n cheesy beans
directions: Saute carrot in
margarine until tender.
Stir in flour and salt.
Blend well.
Add
milk.
Cook and stir until thickened. Stir in cheese until melted.
Add beans; heat thoroughly. Sprinkle with almonds.

title: fat-free zucchini bread
directions: Mix sugar, egg whites, applesauce and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to egg mixture.
Fold in zucchini.
Spray 2 loaf pans with vegetable cooking spray.
Divide batter between pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes to 1 hour.

title: fried rice
directions: Stir-fry cut up pieces of bacon (2 or 3) with onion.
Then scramble in 1 or 2 eggs.
Add 2 cups of cooked rice (do not use Minute rice for this).
After stirring a bit, fold in cooked peas (frozen taste best) and mushrooms (if desired).
Finally, sprinkle with soy sauce.
Yum!

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Put chicken in bottom of casserole.
Add broth and vegetables; let cool.
Place crust on top.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 375 degrees.

title: lemon basil chicken
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix salad dressing, juice, honey and basil.
Place chicken in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Spread with salad dressing mixture.
Bake 45 minutes or until cooked through. Makes 4 servings.
Preparation time:
10 minutes.
Cooking time: 45 minutes.

title: marinated sausage
directions: Ring and heat (to remove excess fat) sausage.
Bring to boil the brown sugar and pineapple.
Pour over sausage.
Marinate overnight.
Heat before serving.

title: miniature pastry shells
directions: Blend cream cheese and butter in bowl with a wooden spoon. Work in flour gradually.
Press dough flat in bowl.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes.

title: crab pasta
directions: Break spaghetti into thirds.
Cook and drain.
Chop scallions finely.
Mix everything together.
Serve on lettuce, if desired.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix vinegar and milk; add rest of ingredients and roll dough out for pies.

title: tex mex strata
directions: In medium size bowl, mash avocados.
Add lemon juice, salt, Tabasco sauce and pepper.
In another bowl, combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco mix.
In a 9 x 13-inch glass casserole, spread the bean dip in a layer.
Next, spread the avocado mixture, then the sour cream mixture.
Sprinkle with the green onions, chopped tomatoes and chopped olives.
Cover top with the cheese. Refrigerate until serving time.
Use tortilla chips for dipping.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, salt and nutmeg and gradually add water. Cook over low heat until thick and clear. Then add butter and lemon juice and blend thoroughly.

title: pan handle casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain between paper towels.
Layer sausage, cheeses and whole chilies in 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish. Combine eggs, milk and flour until well blended.
Blender makes this step easier.
Pour liquid over layered mixture.
For a festive brunch, decorate top with strips of green chilies in lattice design.
Sprinkle with paprika and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Slice and serve.

title: ham and cheese rolls
directions: Open rolls with sharp knife.
Spread top and bottom with butter and other ingredients mixed together.
Layer with ham and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole #7
directions: Steam
broccoli
until	crisp.	Add all ingredients and top with dressing mix.	Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Combine dry ingredients with shortening and mix with a pastry blender or two knives until the mixture has a coarse cornmeal-like consistency.
Stir in the milk, blending until all ingredients are together.
Turn onto a lightly floured board.
Pat out flat and fold over; repeat about 2 times.
Pat out to desired thickness (about 1/2-inch) and cut into desired shapes.
(This dough is very wet when trying to pat into shape, do not add additional flour.) Place in a well-greased baking dish.
Bake in a 425° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve hot.
Makes approximately 1 dozen medium size biscuits.

title: oven cooked country ham
directions: Dip each slice of ham in this mixture and place in a foil lined pan.
Cover ham with foil and cook at 300° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: super ice cream rice krispies dessert
directions: Mix all together and spread 1/2 in bottom of 9-inch square pan.
Soften 1 quart ice cream and put on top of Rice Krispie mixture.
Put the rest of Rice Krispie mixture on top of ice cream and put in freezer overnight.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: squash and zucchini casserole
directions: Steam the sliced squash and zucchini; drain well.
Chop onion and green pepper.
Beat eggs, then blend in garlic powder, salt and pepper, mayonnaise and Parmesan cheese.
Blend all ingredients together and pour into ovenproof dish.
Top with bread crumbs. Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350° and serve.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 9-inch layer cake pan, greased and floured.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve with whipped cream to which pulverized has been added.

title: chicken dumplings
directions: Simmer chicken in 4 cups water for 1 hour.
Remove chicken from broth.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cut in butter.
Beat egg and add milk; stir this into dry ingredients (batter should be quite stiff).
Drop by spoonfuls into chicken broth (or roll in flour like biscuits).
Cover pot.
Raise flame to 1/4 flame.
Steam for about 20 minutes without lifting cover. Remove cover and serve with or without chicken.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Bake pie shell.
Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt in saucepan. Gradually stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir at least half of the hot mixture gradually into egg yolks.
Stir into hot mixture in saucepan.
Boil and stir 1 minute; remove from heat.
Stir in margarine, vanilla and 3/4 cup of the coconut.
Pour into pie shell; press plastic wrap onto filling. Refrigerate at least 2 hours but no longer than 48 hours.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix well and serve over angel food cake.

title: ropa vieja(shredded beef in tomato sauce)
directions: In a suitable soup kettle, place the meat, bay leaf, whole onion, tomato, celery rib (cut in half) and the salt.
Cover with cold water and bring to a rapid boil.
Skim several times.
Lower heat and cook until meat is tender (approximately 1 hour).
Allow meat to cool in stock, then remove to platter and shred.
Strain stock and reserve to be used in sauce and the rest for a hearty soup.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar and beat well.
Add flour, baking powder and salt sifted together.
Beat well.
Heat milk and margarine to boiling.
Gradually add to beaten batter.
Add vanilla and blend well.
Makes 3 layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: microwave baked apple
directions: Wash and core apple.
Pare a thin section of skin from top of apple.
Place apple in custard cup.
Fill center of apple with brown sugar and top with butter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Cook, uncovered, in microwave 2 to 2 1/2 minutes on High or almost tender.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
(Two apples cook 3 1/2 to 4 minutes.)

title: strawberry pie
directions: In a small saucepan crush 1 cup of smaller berries; add 1 cup water.
Bring to boiling; simmer 2 minutes.
Sieve berry mixture.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil and debone chicken. Cut into pieces and put in bottom of a casserole dish.
Mix two cups of chicken broth with soup and vegetables.
Pour over chicken.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over mixture.
Bake at 400 degrees for 40-45 minutes.

title: sausage logs
directions: Mix ingredients and form into small log shapes.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until brown.
Can be frozen before or after baking.
Good when reheated in microwave.

title: blue and gold cobbler
directions: Pour
peaches
and
blueberry
pie filling into 12-inch Dutch oven.
Add	dry
cake mix and stir until mixed.
Put lid on and bake for 45 minutes.

title: meat marinade
directions: Use family steak or top/bottom round (approximately 1-inch thick).

title: baked beans
directions: Mix beans, brown sugar and mustard together. Fry bacon until crispy. Crumble and add to mixture. Saute green onion and onion in bacon grease. Add to mixture with ketchup.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Prepare minute rice.
Cook broccoli in water, just until tender, drain.
Add to rice.

title: pork chops ol
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix water, tomato sauce and taco mix. Place pork chops in baking dish; pour tomato mixture over top. Add rice and pepper.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Uncover and add cheese; bake until cheese is browned.

title: no. 1 houdini cocktail non-alcoholic drink
directions: Blend ice cream and milk until foamy; pour into glasses.
Pour 2 teaspoons of grenadine from spoon down inside glass.
It will form a bright crimson layer at bottom.
Serves 2.

title: no knead pecan rolls
directions: Measure warm water into bowl.
Sprinkle in yeast and stir until dissolved.
Add scalded milk, sugar, salt and oil.
Mix well.
Add 1 cup of the flour; beat well.
Add the eggs, beating well.
Gradually add remaining flour while still mixing.
Beat until light and bubbly.
Cover and allow to rise in a warm place, about 1 hour, until double.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Peel and core apples.
Put into baking dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon, salt and water.
Measure flour, oil and brown sugar into bowl.
Mix until crumbly.
Put over top of apples.
Bake about 40 minutes.

title: ravioli vegen
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling salted water; drain.
Combine all remaining ingredients, except tomato-mushroom sauce.
Using a 9 x 12 x 2-inch baking pan, alternate layers of macaroni and mixture. Pour sauce over casserole and bake in a 325° oven for 45 minutes.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown chopped meat with onion in frying pan.
Prepare mashed potatoes separate.
In a 1 1/2-quart casserole pan, place thin layer of potatoes at bottom.
Add seasonings to meat.
Layer meat on top of potatoes, then vegetables if you wish.
Alternate but potatoes have to be on top (thick layer).
Sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage, celery and onion until meat is brown and vegetables are tender; drain off most of the fat.
Add beef broth, 57 sauce and Worcestershire sauce; stir mixture.
Then add pimentos, mushrooms, salt and pepper to mixture and stir in rice. Pour mixture in baking dish, cover and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Prepare and bake the cake according to pkg. directions, using a greased 13 x 9 x 2 baking pan, cool. In bowl whisk together milk and pudding mix, let stand to thicken.
Stir in pineapple, spread over cake. Prepare whipped topping mix according to pkg., set aside.

In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until smooth. Beat in 1 c. whipped topping. Fold in remaining topping. Spread over pudding. Sprinkle with coconut. Cover and refrigerate for 3 hours or overnight. Yield: 12-15 servings.

title: shortbread tarts
directions: Combine butter, powdered sugar and flour in bowl.
Roll small amount of dough into balls the size of a walnut.
Place on cookie sheet and indent with thumb or large end of mellon baller.
Using a teaspoon, place small amount of jam or jelly in indentation. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes until bottom of tart is golden. Cool on sheet and remove to flat surface.

title: peanut butter sheet cake
directions: Bring butter, peanut butter, water and oil to a boil.
Cool to lukewarm then add remaining ingredients.
Bake 20 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: spinach salad
directions: Mix greens and onions.
Add bacon and eggs; toss.

title: orange slice cookies
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add eggs and butter.
Then add raisins, pecans and orange slice pieces.
Mix well.

title: almond amaretto dessert
directions: Blend cream cheese and 1/2 cup milk in large bowl until well blended.
Whisk together remaining milk with pudding in medium bowl until blended.
Add to cream cheese mixture.
Stir well. Stir in liqueur.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart straight-sided glass bowl. Chill.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken in water to cover in large saucepan until tender. Bone and chop chicken.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Combine soup and sour cream in bowl; mix well.
Spoon over chicken.
Sprinkle with stuffing mix.
Drizzle with margarine. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
May substitute 4 chicken breasts for whole chicken.
Yield: 12 servings.

title: beef stew(no peeking)
directions: Combine meat, vegetables, tapioca and juice.
Put in greased roasting pan and seal with aluminum foil.
Put lid on top.
(Must be well sealed.)
Place in a 250° oven for 5 hours.
No peeking. Ready to serve.
May use any other combination of vegetables.

title: minnesota fritters
directions: Allow bread dough to thaw.
Break off pieces the size of a hamburger and flatten.
Deep fry pieces of dough until they puff up and brown lightly.
Remove; drain.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Eat while warm.

title: rigatoni
directions: Brown ground meat until all pink is gone.
Saute onion and bell pepper in skillet with browned beef.
Drain all fat.
Add parsley, oregano, salt and pepper to taste.	Add tomato sauce, tomato paste, tomatoes and wine or water.
Stir and simmer slowly while rigatoni is boiled according to package directions.	Rinse in cold water; drain and add pasta to meat-tomato mixture.
Add Ricotta, 1/2 cup Parmesan, both types of olives and mushrooms.
Pam or grease 9 x 12-inch (or two 8 x 8-inch) pans.
Layer meat-tomato mixture with Cheddar ending with Cheddar.
Top with 1/2 cup Parmesan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Keep covered with foil so it doesn't dry out. Freezes well.
If frozen, bake at 400° for 1 hour.	Keep covered. Serves 12.

title: 3 fruit chutney
directions: Combine cranberries, apple, apricots, brown sugar, vinegar, ginger, allspice, dry mustard, 1/4 cup water and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce and simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes.
Stir frequently.
Spoon into containers.
Cover, seal and refrigerate or freeze.
Makes 2 cups.
Good accompaniment to cold cuts, such as ham, turkey and roast beef.

title: macaroni supreme
directions: In 1-quart glass dish, microwave onions in butter on High for 2 minutes.
Stir in soup, milk and macaroni.
Microwave on High for 6 minutes.
Stir until cheese is melted.

title: linda's baked beans
directions: In casserole dish, combine beans, seasoning blend, syrup and brown sugar.
Mix well.
Top with strips of bacon.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until onion is done.

title: corn chowder
directions: Bring potatoes, water and onion to boil in a large saucepan over medium-high heat.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 8 to 10 minutes, stirring once or twice until potatoes are tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, 3 to 5 minutes for flavor to develop.
Serves 4.
Per serving:
334 calories, 11 grams fat, 797 milligrams sodium.

title: good ole string beans
directions: Place prepared string beans in heavy pot along with fatback. Cook until done (well done).
May take most of morning.
Place potatoes in pot and cook long enough for potatoes to be done.
Add corn and heat until all is to boiling point again.

title: christmas frozen fruit cake salad
directions: Blend sour cream, whipped cream, sugar, lemon juice and vanilla together.
Fold in fruits and walnuts.
Pour into ring mold.
Freeze for several hours or overnight.
Unmold onto lettuce lined plate.
Garnish with additional cherries, if desired.
Let stand for 20 to 30 minutes before serving.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Mix cheese and crackers; dip pieces of chicken in melted butter and then roll in dry mixture.
Place in baking dish; bake uncovered at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: fabulous potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into baking dish.
Cook in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: savory shrimp
directions: In large skillet, saute carrots, pepper and garlic in butter. Stir in catsup, water, soy sauce, sugar and salt.
Cover.
Simmer 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Add shrimp and cook 5 to 10 minutes until shrimp are pink and tender.

title: faux champagne
directions: Simmer sugar and water in saucepan until sugar dissolves; cool.
Place juices and grenadine in punch bowl.
Add syrup and stir well; chill.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Add lemon peel strip to each glass.
Makes 18 glasses.

title: swedish yamzette(casserole)
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Brown onions, celery, carrots and green pepper.
Cook noodles in salt water; drain.
Rinse and drain again.
Mix all together, adding cheese last.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in Crisco, thoroughly. Add buttermilk and dissolved yeast.
Mix until all flour is moistened.
Store in refrigerator in covered bowl.
Take as much as needed, roll on floured board 1/2-inch thick and cut.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.

title: oriental chicken salad
directions: Combine the chicken, red pepper, jicama, water chestnuts and scallions in a large mixing bowl.
Add snow peas and cashews. Process the parsley and garlic in a food processor.
Add the teriyaki sauce, sesame oil, safflower oil, sesame paste, vinegar, sherry, brown sugar, coriander and chili oil, if desired.
Process until smooth.
Pour the dressing onto the salad and toss thoroughly.
Sprinkle with the sesame seeds.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 portions.
(I used 10 cups chicken and 1 1/2 portions of the remaining ingredients.)

title: lemon fluff
directions: Mix flour, melted margarine, and nuts until blended. Spread and press mixture in a 9 1/2 x 13 inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Cool completely.

title: jane's cornbread
directions: Mix sugar and meal in a bowl. Sift in flour, soda, baking powder, allspice and salt.
Mix well. Add egg, milk and melted butter. Stir well, but do not beat.
Pour into loaf pan or an 8 x 8-inch pan that has been greased.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until done. This freezes and toasts well.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix in order given and pour into greased pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Allow cake to remain in pan and cover with warm topping.

title: garlic bread
directions: Break bread into pieces in two pans.
Beat egg.
Add rest of ingredients and drizzle over bread.
Let rise.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pasta e fagioli
directions: In a large pot, heat oil and simmer onions, peppers, celery and garlic, stirring occasionally, for about 8 minutes.
Add tomatoes and seasoning.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Add meat, beans and Parmesan cheese.
Add pasta.
Heat thoroughly.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix well with margarine and 2/3 cup canned milk. Press half the mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Melt caramels and 1/3 cup of canned milk and pour over baked cake mixture.
Over this sprinkle pecans and chocolate chips, then pour remaining cake mixture on top.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetables in two cheese-beer sauce
directions: In covered 4-quart saucepan over medium heat in 1-inch boiling water, cook broccoli and cauliflower 6 minutes or until tender; drain.
Meanwhile, in 2-quart saucepan combine soup, beer, cheese and nutmeg.
Over medium heat, heat through, stirring frequently. Arrange vegetables on platter to resemble a head of cauliflower. Pour sauce over vegetables.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown and cook meat and onions.
Add all ingredients together in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Slice apples into large, flat dish.
Add the water.
Combine dry ingredients and crumb in butter.
Pour over apples and bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: easiest cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13 in baking dish.

title: vegetable patch marinade
directions: Cook carrots in a small amount of water until crisp-tender; drain.
Combine carrots and cucumber.
Pour dressing over vegetables.
Cover; marinate in refrigerator several hours or overnight.
Drain.
Serves 6.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix together.
Keep in sealed container.
Put 2 teaspoons in mug and add boiling water.

title: lima beans au gratin
directions: Cook and drain beans (reserve 1/4 cup liquid).
Saute onion and celery in margarine.
Stir in 1/4 cup flour.
Gradually add milk.
Cook until thick (stirring).
Stir in 1 cup cheese.
Add pimento, salt and thyme.

title: chicken pie
directions: Mix together chicken, Veg-All with liquid and soup.
Spread mixture in lightly greased baking dish (lightly grease dish with margarine or spray with Pam or other cooking spray).
Melt margarine; add flour and mix until smooth.
Slowly add milk and mix until smooth.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Put in a shallow baking dish.
Combine other ingredients and pour over broccoli.
Top with your favorite crushed crackers (cheese crackers are good).
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.
This casserole freezes well.
If you plan to freeze it, do not cook the broccoli tender.
Bake casserole for 10 minutes. Cool and cover casserole before putting in freezer.

title: low-fat ginger cookies
directions: Cream margarine and gradually add 2/3 cup sugar.
Beat with electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Add molasses and egg; beat well.
Combine flour and next 4 ingredients.
Gradually add to creamed mixture and stir well.
Divide dough in half and wrap both in plastic wrap.
Freeze for 30 minutes.
Shape into 1-inch balls, roll in remaining sugar and place 2-inches apart on cookie sheet coated with vegetable spray.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes; cool. Store in airtight container.

title: monkey bread
directions: Grease a tube pan.
Sprinkle the bottom with pecans.
Melt the margarine and add sugar, water and pecans.
Cut the biscuit dough in halves and ball up (40 balls).
Place 20 balls in bottom of prepared pan and drizzle with half of the melted mixture.
Place remaining 20 balls in pan and top with the rest of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: olive nut sandwich spread
directions: Mix softened cream cheese with enough mayonnaise to make it spreadable.
Add chopped green olives with pimentos and chopped nuts.
This is good on wheat bread!

title: fruit cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Fold in stiffly beaten eggs. Flour the fruits to prevent lumping together.
Put all ingredients into mixing bowl and stir until thoroughly mixed.
Bake in slow oven at 350° about 1 hour.

title: oatmeal scotchies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
In a large separate bowl, combine sugars, margarine, eggs and water.
Beat with mixer until creamy; then add first mixture, oats and butterscotch chips.
Spoon cookie mixture onto greased cookie sheets and bake until golden brown, about 10 to 12 minutes.

title: italian spinach casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except Ragu and noodles.
Layer mixture with noodles in 9 x 13 baking dish.
Pour Ragu over mixture.
Bake at 350 for 35-40 minutes.
Serves 6-8.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Drain pineapple, saving juice.
Prepare cake according to directions, but instead of water, use pineapple juice (add water to make right amount).
Spoon pineapple over cooled cake.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: Make pudding as directed; when it has thickened, add dry cake mix to hot pudding.
Stir until blended.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with nuts and chips.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: swedish limpa muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients.
Mix only until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fill well-greased muffin cups about half full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes until golden brown.
Serve hot.

title: stove top chocolate cookies
directions: Cook together first 4 ingredients until they begin to thicken. Remove from heat and add oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Drop on wax paper and cool.

title: chicken dumpling soup
directions: Boil cut up chicken until tender.
When cool, debone.
Return pieces to stock.
Add vegetables and soup starter.
When vegetables are tender, drop dumplings by teaspoon into hot soup. Do not boil at this time.
Steam for 5 minutes and serve.
My mother-in-law used new potatoes, fresh peas, etc. from the garden.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: In a 2-quart casserole dish, mix together mayonnaise, undiluted soup and lemon juice.
Drain asparagus; fold into mayonnaise mixture.
Spread bread crumbs and cheese on top; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cinnamon syrup
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a small saucepan; mix well.
Add water and bring to a boil.
After it starts to boil, let it simmer gently for 3 minutes.
Tastes great on French toast as well as many other things.

title: paula's quick quiche
directions: Beat together eggs and sour cream.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix with fork and pour into a greased 9-inch pie plate.
Top with 1/4 to 1/2 cup grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet.
Add beef, onion and garlic. Cook and stir until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Stir in catsup, Worcestershire sauce, brown sugar, salt, paprika, mustard, cayenne and 1 1/2 cups water.
Cover; simmer for 2 1/2 hours.

title: strawberry bread(2 loaves)
directions: Beat eggs and sugar; add oil and vanilla.
Mix in flour, oats, cinnamon, soda, salt and baking powder.
Add strawberries and mix well.
Pour into two greased and floured 4 x 8-inch loaf pans. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sausage balls
directions: Grate cheese and mix all ingredients together.
Roll into small balls and bake at 350° until brown, about 20 minutes.

title: john's secret sauce
directions: Brown ground beef, onions and green pepper.
Drain.
Add parsley, tomato sauce, Worcestershire sauce, wine, mint, hot sauce, garlic powder and salt.
Simmer 2 hours.
Spoon over cooked macaroni.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Mix together with the broth from the turkey, which has four tablespoons also added to it.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: cherry supreme dessert(no bake)
directions: This is a 4 layer dessert.

title: punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and sugar in about a quart of hot water.
Cool and add juices and more sugar, if desired.
Add ginger ale if desired just before serving.
Add crushed ice.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Toss apples in lemon juice.
Add rest of ingredients and toss well.
Stir gently.
Serve on bed of lettuce.

title: chicken wings
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl except chicken.
Separate chicken wings and add to mixture.
Marinate overnight in refrigerator. Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Turn over once during baking.

title: perfect peanut butter no bakes
directions: Place first 6 ingredients in saucepan and bring to a boil. Boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; add peanut butter until melted.
In a separate bowl, add oats.
Pour mixture over oats. Stir and scoop rounded teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: karen's barbecue sauce on stanbury
directions: Mix together ingredients and simmer, uncovered, for 2 hours.

title: butterfinger dessert
directions: Tear cake into pieces.
Crush 4 Butterfinger bars.
Mix these together, then mix cream cheese, confectioners sugar and marshmallow cream together.
Mix with cake and candy.
Press this mixture into the bottom of a pan.
Top with Cool Whip.
Crush the remaining 2 Butterfinger bars and sprinkle on top.

title: italian flags
directions: Grease three 10 1/2 x 15 1/2 x 1-inch pans.
Line with waxed paper and grease the paper.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: crisco pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time and beat well. Add a little flour at a time.
Use desired flavoring.
Put in oven and turn to 325°.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: mile high icing
directions: Place in a large mixing bowl the egg whites and corn syrup. Start beating on low and increase to high. Add vanilla.
When mixture holds its shape, spread on cake.

title: caramel popcorn topping
directions: Mix all the ingredients, except the soda; cook to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add 1/4 teaspoon soda.
Covers 1 cup uncooked popcorn.
Makes 3 poppers.

title: 7-layer cookies
directions: Melt butter in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Layer remaining ingredients in order given.
Cook at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool completely before cutting.

title: early bird party pizza
directions: Combine all ingredients except biscuits. Separate each biscuit into 3 pizza rounds. Spread with mixture.
Put pizza on cookie sheet and freeze.
Remove from cookie sheet and store in plastic bags.
Bake frozen pizzas at 425° for 10 minutes.

title: diet baked apples
directions: Peel, core and half apples.
Place in a baking dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Pour 1 bottle desired Faygo diet drink over apples.
Baste apples during baking process so they won't dry. Bake at 350° until apples are tender.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Dissolve jello in
hot
water.
Warm the soup; dissolve the cheese.
Add jello and
let
it
start
to set.
Add peas, shrimp, celery, onion, pepper and salad dressing.
Add this to the
jello, tomato
and
cheese
that is setting.
Place in a large mold. Let set 12 to 24 hours before serving.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Cool with 1 3/4 cups ice cubes and cold water.
Add pineapple and juice.
Rake through cranberry sauce with a fork and add to jello mixture.
Pour in 8 x 8-inch container. When slightly jelled, spread and cover over with mixture of sour cream, Cool Whip and sugar.
Serve as is or rake with a fork the sour cream mixture down into the jello.
Chill.

title: jalapeno cream sauce
directions: Blend 1 to 2 minutes or until jalapeno is finely minced. Yields 2 cups.

title: shanghai chicken wings
directions: Wash the chicken wings and dry with paper towels.
Cut off the tips and cut the wing in half at the joint.
Save the wing tips for chicken stock, if you wish.
Grate the fresh ginger and set aside.

title: milly's sweet 'n sour mustard pickles
directions: Dissolve salt in 6 cups boiling water.
Pour over cucumbers. Let stand until cool; drain.
Combine vinegar, sugar, seed and turmeric.
Add 1 1/2 cups water.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over pickles.
Let stand 24 hours, covered.
Bring all to boiling. Pack cucumbers and liquid into sterile, hot pint jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Wipe rims; adjust lids.
Process in boiling water bath 5 minutes.
Start timing when water boils.
Makes about 5 pints.

title: beer bread or rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into loaf or muffin pans.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: liver noodles
directions: Simmer the liver in boiling water for 30 minutes.
Then trim off any skin or ligaments and grind the liver fine.
Season. Mince the onion; add the butter.
Beat the eggs and add them. Work into this paste the flour, using enough to make the paste quite stiff.
Form into small balls and poach them in any meat soup for 15 minutes.
Serve them, swimming in the soup.

title: dream roll
directions: Cook together 2/3 cup sugar, cornstarch, jello, 2/3 cup water and frozen strawberries.
Cool.
Beat eggs until fluffy. Mix
dry ingredients.
Add
water, vanilla and flour to eggs. Pour into jelly
roll
pan and bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Empty roll
on
a
cup
towel
that was sprinkled with powdered
sugar. When
cooled,
unroll.
Spread
with
cooled strawberry
mixture. Roll
back like jelly roll.
Spread some strawberry mixture on top.

title: cranberry sour cream salad
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients. Chill slightly and add remaining ingredients.

title: baked cheese grits
directions: Bring milk to a boil.
Add grits and cook until thickened (about 10 minutes), stirring often.
Stir in margarine, salt and cheese.
Spoon into a lightly greased 1-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Mix spaghetti and sauce together.
Spread cooked spaghetti noodles and sauce in 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: hot relish tray
directions: Mix carrots (with liquid) and remaining ingredients in saucepan.
Heat through.
Makes 4 servings.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt chocolate pieces.
Add noodles and peanuts. Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Let cool.
Makes about 36.

title: divinity candy
directions: Gather about a double handful of hoarhound leaves.
Wash, then boil in a pint and half of water for about half an hour; strain and add 3 1/2 pounds of brown sugar; boil over a hot fire until sufficiently hard-ball stage.
Pour out in flat, well-greased tins and mark into sticks or small squares with a knife as soon as cool enough to retain its shape.

title: bob's barbecued pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides in a large skillet.
Coat a baking dish with vegetable cooking spray and put the browned chops in.
Combine the barbecue sauce with just enough water to thin it out and pour it over the chops.
Cover with foil and bake at 325° for one hour or until done.

title: wisconsin cheese bread
directions: Scald milk in saucepan. Add and stir in the sugar, butter and salt. Cool milk mixture to lukewarm. While mixture cools, put 1/2 cup warm water in large mixing bowl. Sprinkle yeast over water. Stir to dissolve. Stir in milk mixture. Stir in egg, then cheese. Add in 3 cups flour; beat well. Add additional flour to make dough leave side of bowl, about 3 cups. Turn dough out on lightly floured board and knead about 10 minutes or until smooth and elastic. Divide in half; shape into loaves. Place in 9 x 5 x 3-inch pans. Brush tops lightly with melted butter. Cover with towel and let rise about 30 to 40 minutes or until double in size. Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pork chops
directions: Melt shortening in pan.
Add pork chops and brown on both sides.
Fill pan with water.
Cover and let boil dry.

title: tomato pudding
directions: Add sugar and salt to tomato puree and water; boil for 5 minutes.
Place bread cubes in casserole.
Pour melted butter over them.
Add the tomato mixture.
Bake, covered, for 30 minutes at 375°.
Serve with meats.
Good!!

title: cranberry mold
directions: Combine cranberries, apples and sugar.
Dissolve gelatins in hot water.
Add syrup and chill until partially set.
Add cranberries and apple mixture and nuts.
Pour into mold.
Chill until firm.

title: extra tender pancakes
directions: Mix milk, egg, and butter or margarine.
Sift flour, sugar, and baking powder.
Stir milk mixture into flour just until moistened.
Cook on an oiled griddle.

title: clam chowder
directions: Cook vegetables in clam juice and enough water to just cover the vegetables.
Cook until tender.
In a large pan melt butter and gradually add the flour, stir until smooth.
Then add the half and half, stirring constantly.
Cook until very thick.
Add the vegetables, including the juice, and the clams to the white sauce. Cook an additional 5 to 10 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bread crumbs.
Pour into a 3-quart casserole dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
Top with bread crumbs. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: broccoli and stuffing
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions adding an extra 1/4 cup water.
When done, drain the juice, adding it to the chicken soup. Mix until smooth.
Grease 1 1/2-quart casserole; add half the broccoli, then half stuffing mix and half chicken soup.
Repeat. Add cut up cheese to the top.
Bake in 350° oven 30 minutes. Serve immediately.

title: date-nut balls
directions: Add remaining ingredients to stiffly beaten egg whites.
Drop cookies with spoon on a well-greased cookie sheet.
Top each cookie with a maraschino cherry.
Bake at 350° for approximately ten minutes.

title: yakitori sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Let food marinate for at least half an hour.
Saute or put on skewer and barbecue.
Keeps for 2 days.
Meats can be frozen in this marinade, then thawed and cooked for a quick meal later.
Makes enough for one pound of food.
Can be used for any kind of food.

title: cheese-garlic biscuits
directions: Mix Bisquick, milk and cheese until soft dough forms.
Drop dough by spoonfuls onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 450°.
Mix butter and garlic powder.
Brush over warm biscuits.

title: pasta with marinara sauce and ricotta
directions: Saute garlic in oil.
Add tomatoes and seasonings.
Simmer. Pour over pasta.
Stir in Ricotta cheese.
Makes a single serving.

title: low-fat chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms in butter for 7 minutes, until liquid is evaporated.
Stir in flour, then add broth, milk and cream cheese.
Bring to a boil and cook for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese, sherry, salt, garlic and pepper.
Add chicken and cooked spaghetti.
Pour into 3-quart casserole sprayed with Pam.
Top with 2 tablespoons Parmesan.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes, then uncovered, 10 minutes more.
Serves 6.

title: pudding in a cloud
directions: Combine pudding mix and milk in a medium saucepan; blend well. Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil; pour into bowl.
Cover surface of pudding with plastic wrap. Chill.

title: custard pie
directions: Prepare Never Fail Pie Crust.
Beat eggs.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into crust filled pie pan.
Bake 20 minutes or until set at 415° on lower shelf.

title: ida's pickled peaches
directions: Wash and sterilize jars and lids.
Peel as many peaches as you want to pickle or your kettle will hold.
Mix in large kettle, cider vinegar, sugar, cinnamon and whole allspice.
Place on stove and bring to a boil.
When boiling, drop in peaches and cook until tender.
Place in jars with juice to cover.
Seal at once.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Soften sherbet.
Mix with other ingredients and refreeze in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Soften before serving.

title: drop biscuits
directions: With a fork, mix dry ingredients together.
With pastry blender, cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Add milk and with fork stir dough until thoroughly mixed.
Do not knead dough.
Drop heaping tablespoonfuls of mixture on an ungreased cookie sheet 1 inch apart.
Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: dorothy's pot roast
directions: In heavy kettle, melt Crisco.
Brown roast slowly on all sides.
Add chopped onions, flour, brown sugar, dry mustard and salt.
Add vinegar and water.
Cover and simmer slowly for 3 to 3 1/2 hours, or until tender.

title: mrs. sanders peach cookies
directions: Cream sugar, butter and egg.
Sift dry ingredients; add to first mixture alternately with milk.
Add nuts and peaches and mix well.
Shape into rolls.
Wrap in wax paper and place in refrigerator until ready to bake.
Slice thin and bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yield: 5 dozen.

title: orange carrots
directions: Scrape carrots.
Cut carrots into strips.
In a microwave dish, place carrots.
Pour in orange juice and white Karo.
Add brown sugar and salt.
Cook in microwave at 80% for 24 minutes, or until tender.
Add vanilla and nutmeg.
Take 2 tablespoons of cornstarch with a small amount of water and add to carrots.
Cook a few minutes until thick.
Keeps well in the refrigerator.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix both pudding mixes with the milk.
Line bottom of pan with graham crackers.
Layer with vanilla and then chocolate pudding. Makes three layers.

title: chicken taquitos
directions: Poach chicken breasts until tender.
When cooled, remove meat from bones in small pieces.
Mix meat, 1 can salsa, cumin and heat. Heat oil in small skillet.
Dip tortillas in oil to soften.
Drain on paper towels.
Put small amount meat mixture in center of tortilla, roll and secure with a toothpick.
Reheat oil, fry taquitos until crisp.
Drain on paper towels.
Mash avocados and mix with salsa.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: peaches
directions: Put 1/2 stick margarine in electric skillet and let melt. Fill with peaches and sprinkle with sugar.
Cook, stirring frequently until peaches are slightly brown.
Pour into mixing bowl and beat.
Tastes like dried peaches.
Can be frozen for later use.
Makes great fried pies.

title: chocolate fruit salad
directions: In large glass bowl, put one layer of brownies.
Place one layer of sliced bananas on top of brownies.
Place one layer of sliced strawberries on top of bananas.
Spread a layer of Cool Whip on strawberries.
Repeat layer order, ending with Cool Whip. Crumble 1 brownie on Cool Whip.

title: wax cookies
directions: Mix peanut butter, dates, nuts and butter.
Add powdered sugar slowly.
Make into 3/4-inch by 2-inch rolls.
Chill overnight. Melt paraffin wax and butterscotch chips.
Dip rolls in wax and butterscotch with a fork.
Place on wax paper.
Place wax paper on cookie pan.
Very good Mrs. Zeck.

title: hot ham sandwiches
directions: Spread mixture on hamburger buns.
Add slice of ham and Swiss cheese.
Place on cookie sheet and cover with foil or wrap each individually in foil.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 8 sandwiches.
Great entertainment to serve hot potato with the foil wrapped sandwiches.
A New Year's Eve family tradition.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix fruit cocktail, strawberries and glaze in a bowl. In a separate bowl, mix cream cheese and a little sugar to taste. Mix until smooth. Press cookie dough into a pizza pan and bake until just slightly brown. (You want the cookie crust to be soft, so don't let it bake very long at all). Let cool. Spread cream cheese over the cookie crust. Put fruit mixture over that and then slice bananas over the top.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Mix in order as written.
Grease casserole dish.
Pour mixture in.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: banana chocolate chip muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat first 8 ingredients until smooth. Stir in chocolate chips.
Place batter evenly in lined or greased 2 3/4-inch muffin tins.
Bake for 25 to 28 minutes, until golden brown.
Yields 1 dozen.

title: cajun squash
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil in a skillet until crisp-tender. Add zucchini and yellow squash; cook mixture over medium-high heat, stirring constantly for 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes and remaining ingredients; cook, stirring constantly for 2 minutes. Serve immediately.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: pot roast
directions: Cut roast 2 inches thick; pierce with fork.
Sprinkle with tenderizer.
Then coat meat with marinade; let set for 15 minutes. Grill on charcoal or gas grill.
Slice into strips to serve. Taste like prime rib.

title: diabetic cinnamon raisin cookies
directions: Mix hot water, shortening and raisins; set aside.
Mix together nutmeg, cinnamon, eggs, sweetener and 1 tablespoon water. Sift together flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Combine with egg mixture.
Add raisins, water and shortening mixture. Drop by teaspoonfuls on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes in 350° oven.
Yields 48.

title: super potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in jackets.
Cool.
Peel and cube.
Stir in green pepper, onion, milk, cheese, salt and black pepper.
Mix well.
Turn into greased casserole; sprinkle with chopped dried parsley.
Pour all of melted oleo over potato mixture.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: salad dressing
directions: Cut up onion into blender, chopping or blending into puree and then add other ingredients, blending all until thick and creamy. Put into jar and store in refrigerator.
Use on tossed salads and as a dip.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: In small, deep mixing bowl, whisk together pudding mix, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Gradually add milk, beating at low speed until well blended.
Add sour cream; mix well.
Chill at least 2 hours before serving.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter, eggs and sugar together. Put sour cream and baking powder in separate bowl and mix together.
Add to cake mixture.
Fold in flour, a cup at a time. Beat well.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: sausage bread
directions: Thaw and let rise frozen bread dough.
Cook sausage and cut up in fine pieces and drain sausage on paper towel.
Roll dough out rectangle shape about 1/4-inch thick.
Sprinkle sausage and cheese over the dough and roll dough up long side first.
Place seam of loaf down on greased cookie sheet.
Pinch ends of loaf.
Bake at 350° for about 25 to 30 minutes or until top of bread is golden brown.
Let cool before slicing.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown ground beef with onion; drain.
Brown bacon and drain. Crumble into small pieces.
Combine all ingredients and bake at 325° for 2 hours or cook slowly in crock-pot.

title: everything in a skillet
directions: Line cold skillet with bacon.
Place hamburger patties in. Slice the potatoes, carrots and peppers on top.
Turn the skillet onto sizzle.
Add enough water to cover the hamburger halfway. Cover and steam for 40 minutes.
Remove the lid for the last 10 minutes.
Let the water cook out.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken cournado
directions: Boil chicken breasts until done; pick apart in small pieces. Place chicken in casserole.
Combine sour cream and cream of chicken soup and pour over chicken in casserole.
Crush enough Ritz crackers to cover top of casserole and combine with melted butter.
Top casserole with crumbs and bake 20 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serve with baked potatoes and green beans.

title: florida pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, margarine, butter and cream cheese.
Add alternately flour and eggs, a little at a time.
Add salt and vanilla.
Pour in greased, floured bundt pan.
Bake at 300 F for 1 1/2 hrs. The oven must NOT be preheated.
Place mixture in cold oven, then turn on heat.

title: strip steak
directions: Fry steak on medium high until brown on both sides with a little pink inside.
Then slice steak very thin, add fish sauce, pepper flakes and fresh squeezed lime juice and mix well.
Serve with cooked white rice.

title: grandma lelia's frozen raspberry surprise
directions: Using mixer, combine berries with 1/2 teaspoon sugar and liqueur.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Add remaining sugar and beat a few more seconds.
Add raspberry mixture. Carefully fold in raspberry-egg mixture.
Spoon mixture into chocolate cups and top with fresh berries.

title: lace cookies
directions: Combine ingredients. Work oats in with hands.
Drop by tablespoon.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: caramel corn
directions: In a large saucepan, mix the first 5 ingredients and bring to a boil, boiling gently for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in 1 teaspoon soda.
Mixture will foam.
Pour mixture over popped corn; mix well.
Place in oven for 1 hour at 200°.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Raw peanuts may be stirred in before baking.

title: kentucky pecan pie
directions: Combine syrup, sugar, salt, butter and vanilla and mix well. Add eggs and mix.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Sprinkle pecans over the entire top.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes. When cool, top with Cool Whip if desired or serve with ice cream. If using two pie crusts, add a few more pecans.

title: sweet rolls
directions: Mix milk, butter, sugar, and salt in pan and bring to a boil. Then cool until lukewarm.
Add yeast and flour until it becomes thick.
Then mix with hands.
Mix until no flour is visible.
Let rise in warm place for about an hour.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: pepper steak
directions: Roll steak strips in flour, salt, and pepper.
Sear in lard over medium heat.
Keep stirring so it doesn't burn.
When slightly browned, add bouillon cubes dissolved in boiling water. Cook over low heat until meat is tender, about 10 - 15 min.
Add peppers and onions to the meat; cook until vegetables are tender. You may need to add a small amount of water at this time, but not too much.
Add cornstarch mixed in water and soy sauce.
Cook for 5 - 10 min. until thick.
Serve over rice.

title: hot tamales
directions: Grind all fresh seasoning.
Then mix to raw ground meat with 1 can
tomato sauce; add chili powder and Ro-Tel and salt to taste with 1 cup raw cornmeal.
Shape about 1 tablespoon of meat mixture and
roll	in raw cornmeal that is seasoned with salt and red pepper.
Then
roll
in
paper
and
place	in a greased high pot. As
layers of hot tamales are placed in the pot, put paste
on top of each layer.	When this is completed, fill pot; put water as high
as
hot
tamales.
Let come to a boil and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix in order and put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: cheese cookies
directions: Mix cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla together.
Place cupcake liners in pans.
Put one wafer in each cupcake.
Fill about 1/2 with mix.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Top with cherry pie filling.
Makes 24 cakes.

title: help your heart ice cream
directions: Platanos (plantain) can be bought in Mexican town at "La Paloma" store.
They resemble bananas but outside is very green and they are larger (do not use regular bananas).
Serve like potato chips or to replace potatoes in meal.

title: spookie pumpkin pie (makes own crust)
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease 9 inch or 10 inch pie plate.
Beat all ingredients until smooth in a blender on high. Pour in pie plate.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, approximately 50 - 55 minutes.

title: sherried beef
directions: Place in a casserole in the order given.
Cover tightly and bake about 3 hours at 350°.
Serves 4 to 6.
Serve over noodles or potatoes.

title: fiesta corn nachos
directions: Brown meat in skillet, drain, stir in corn and salsa. Arrange chips in a large shallow pan. Spoon mixture over chips, and top with cheese. Bake at 400 degrees for 2 minutes until cheese is melted. Serve with sliced greed onions, tomatoes, salsa, and sour cream.

title: kahlua
directions: Bring sugar and water to a boil, then thoroughly add coffee a little at a time.
Bring to boil again.
Cool completely.
Slit vanilla bean from top to bottom without splitting clear through. Add this and vodka to mixture.
Make sure it is cool.
Place in 1/2 gallon jar and cap tightly.
Let stand for 2 weeks or more, turning upside-down once or twice.

title: american chop suey
directions: Brown onions and pepper in oil.
Add ground meat and cook until done.
Add spaghetti sauce.
Serve hot.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Chop hearts very fine.
Mix with other ingredients.
Place in deep baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly. Serve with crackers, chips or knot bread.
You should double recipe.
This won't last long.

title: buckeye drops
directions: In a medium bowl, stir together powdered sugar, peanut butter, butter or margarine and vanilla until well combined. Shape mixture into 1-inch balls.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: poppy seed ham sandwiches
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Slice entire package of rolls lengthwise, while in one piece.
Spread mixture on both halves of rolls.
Put ham on bottom half and sprinkle with cheese.
Place top layer of rolls on ham and cheese.
Wrap in foil.
Bake for 15 minutes in a 425° oven.
Cool for a few minutes, then slice and serve.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, sugar, oil and sour cream well.
Pour into sheet cake pan.
Mix in a separate bowl brown sugar, cinnamon, coconut and nuts.
Twirl into batter with knife.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: ricky skaggs' one pot meal
directions: Amounts will vary according to family size.
Layer potatoes, onions and carrots on top of pork.
Top with sauerkraut.
Simmer until tender (3 to 4 hours).

title: sally's famous doughnuts
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, sour cream and buttermilk. Mix in rest of dry ingredients; add enough flour to handle good. Roll out on board.
Cut and fry in hot lard.
Makes about 30 doughnuts

title: easy baked beans
directions: Empty 1 can beans in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine sugar and mustard.
Sprinkle 1/2 over beans.
Add second can of beans and sprinkle mixture.
Add crunched bacon and catsup.
Bake uncovered at 325° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cover and chill.
Makes 3 cups. Great served with party pumpernickel, rye bread or crackers of choice.

title: gourmet sweet potato classic
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Lightly grease a 9x13 inch baking dish. Set aside.
In a large bowl, mix together mashed sweet potatoes, salt, 1/4 cup butter, eggs, vanilla, ground cinnamon, sugar, and cream. Pour into prepared baking dish.
In a medium-sized mixing bowl, combine 1/4 cup butter, flour, brown sugar, and chopped pecans. Mix together with a pastry blender or fingers until it resembles course meal.
Sprinkle over potatoes.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: millionaires
directions: Melt caramels in double boiler.
Add 3 tablespoons water and chopped pecans.
Cool and drop by spoonful on buttered cookie sheet.
Let set until firm.

title: ranch crispy chicken
directions: You will also need a plastic bag.

title: squash casserole
directions: Wash squash; cut up.
Add onion.
Cover with water and cook until tender.
Drain.
Mash with potato masher.
Make dressing mix as directed on package then mix both dressing mix and squash together with oleo.
Put in oblong pan.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: swedish cheese potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into halves (lengthwise) and then crosswise into 1-inch wedges.
Arrange in single layer in shallow baking dish.
Pour margarine over potatoes.
Sprinkle with mixture of cheese, crumbs, salt and paprika.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: cream cheese fruit cupcakes
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and cream cheese together until smooth. Place cupcake liners in cupcake tray and place 1 wafer in bottom of each, flat side down.
Tablespoon mixture over wafer to half full.
Bake at 350° for 18 minutes.
Cool and top with pie filling.
Makes about 32 cupcakes.

title: "kota me patates ke bezelia" - baked chicken pieces, potatoes and
directions: Put potatoes in the bottom of a pot, then put chicken pieces over potatoes.
Season with salt.
Pour tomato sauce over it along with the oil.
Season with pepper and add 1/2 cup water.
Bake at 400° until chicken is browned on both sides, then make room on the sides for peas and add 1 cup water.
Season a little.
Bake for 10 minutes or until liquid has been absorbed.

title: marinated pot roast
directions: Choose any of the less expensive cuts of lean beef or rolled roast without fat.
Combine wine, bouillon, onions, garlic and seasonings.
Pour over roast; cover and refrigerate overnight. Remove meat and pat dry, reserving marinade.
Brown meat on all sides, using as little fat as possible and low heat.
Pour off fat and add marinade.
Bring to a boil; then cover tightly and place in a 450° oven.
After 10 minutes, reduce heat to 250°.
Cook until tender.
(Success depends on long, slow cooking.)

title: party cheese ball
directions: Bring cheeses to room temperature and blend well.
Stir in onion and garlic.
Chill until firm enough to handle.
Form into a ball.
Spread pecan meal on waxed paper; roll the cheese in the pecan meal to coat.
Chill until serving time.
Serve with crackers or toasted bread rounds.

title: old-fashioned baking powder biscuits
directions: Mix together the dry ingredients.
Cut in the shortening.
Mix in the milk.
Roll out on floured board.
Cut into biscuits.
Bake at 450° for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: cherries jubilee
directions: Drain cherries well.
Place in buttered Pyrex dish.
Add juice of orange.
Dot with brown sugar and butter (amount depending on how sweet you like it).
Heat thoroughly in a 375° oven.
Serve over ice cream.
Top each serving with a lighted sugar cube that has been soaked in lemon extract.

title: fruit custard cake
directions: Mix together ingredients and bake for 45 minutes in a baking pan at 350°.
Mix 1 beaten egg, 1/4 cup sugar and 3 tablespoons melted butter.
Pour over cake and bake 10 minutes longer.
Cool and serve.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine soda and buttermilk; let stand a few minutes.

title: pink cement dessert
directions: Mix until creamy the cream cheese and Eagle Brand milk.
Add cherry pie filling, crushed pineapple and Cool Whip.
Mix well and fold in 1/2 bag marshmallows.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Sift cocoa and sugar in a large mixing bowl.
Add milk and lay margarine stick on top.
Do not stir.
Cook on High for 6 minutes. Remove from microwave and stir thoroughly.	Add vanilla flavoring and nuts.
Stir until well mixed.
Pour into buttered dish.
Cool in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Cut and serve.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: In a blender or with hand mixer, whip potatoes until mushy. Add brown sugar and margarine.
Mix well.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Combine pecans, sugar and melted margarine. Sprinkle on top of sweet potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: barbecued steak
directions: Combine all ingredients (except steak) in saucepan.
Bring to boil; simmer 5 minutes.
Cut steak into serving size pieces and place in roasting pan.
Pour sauce over meat; cover tightly and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until meat is tender.

title: herbia burgers
directions: Mix well ground beef, onion, bread, egg and parsley.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Form into balls and brown on high heat.
Add cream of mushroom soup and 1 can water.
Cover and cook on low heat for about 30 minutes or until done.
Serve over egg noodles or rice.
Quick, easy and delicious!

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Bring butter, cream cheese and eggs to room temperature. Cream together butter and cream cheese.
Cream in sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, until well blended. Add all-purpose flour. Stir in flavorings.
Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 to 30 minutes or until done. Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely on a wire rack.

title: baked apple doughnuts
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Cut in the shortening until it resembles cornmeal.
Add eggs, milk and apples.
Stir just enough to moisten.
Fill well-greased muffin tins about 1/2 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: lettuce, watercress, and cucumber salad
directions: Soak onion in 1 cup cold water 10 minutes; drain well in a sieve. Toss lettuce, watercress, and cucumber together in a bowl and divide among 6 plates. Spoon dressing over, then sprinkle salads with onion. Makes 6 servings.

title: eggplant salad
directions: Broil eggplant until cooked (the skin comes off easily by hand, peeling it and the eggplant is soft to touch).
Add your favorite salad dressing.
Mix with chopped tomatoes, green onions, fresh basil and fresh mint.
Season with salt (optional) and black ground pepper.
Refrigerate.
Serve chilled.

title: marinated shrimp
directions: Fill bowl with alternate layers of shrimp and onions.
Combine vinegar, water, salt, sugar and spices in saucepan.
Bring to boil; cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Cool mixture.
Add lemon juice and oil.
Pour over shrimp.
Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Drain off marinade and serve.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Prepare pudding according to package directions.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Set aside.
Line bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with graham crackers.
Layer pudding on top, then crackers.
End with graham crackers on top.
Spread chocolate frosting on top.
Refrigerate overnight.
It will all mold together and the graham crackers will be soft.
Cut into squares and serve when ready.

title: budin(filipino bread pudding)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 1 1/2-quart casserole.

title: quick and easy mints
directions: Slightly beat egg white.
Add all remaining ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Roll out between wax paper until very thin.
Cut with small cutter.
Place on wax paper; let stand.
Pack in box or tin with waxed paper between.

title: fruit dip
directions: Cream together jam and cream cheese.
Fold in Cool Whip. Chill.
Thin with milk if dip becomes too thick.
Serve with apples and bananas.

title: capelli d'angelo with cream and fresh tomatoes(prep: 10 minutes, cook: 20 minutes, serves 4)
directions: In a medium skillet, simmer the tomatoes and basil until soft and juices have cooked out of tomatoes, about 10 minutes.
Add the heavy cream.
Cook, stirring, over low heat until the sauce reduces and thickens slightly, about 10 minutes.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: squirrel stew
directions: Cut squirrels.
Season with salt and pepper.
Put flour and squirrels in bag and shake.
In large pot, heat oil and add squirrels.
Fry until browned.
Remove and keep warm.
Add flour out of bag to oil to make roux; heat until flour is dark brown. Chop all vegetables and add to roux.
Add squirrels and cover with water.
Add bouillon cubes and Kitchen Bouquet for color.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer for 5 hours.
Serve over rice. Serves 12.

title: sour cream dressing for baked potatoes
directions: Combine and refrigerate several hours before serving.
Serve over baked potatoes.

title: creamy nut fudge
directions: Combine
cocoa and sugar in 4 quart saucepan.
Blend in condensed milk and add butter.
Cook, stirring constantly over medium
heat
until
mixture
comes to a boil and becomes very thick.
Boil
and stir 10 minutes, remove from heat.
Blend in nuts and vanilla; spread mixture evenly in a foil lined 9-inch square pan.
Refrigerate 30 minutes.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and add boiling water last.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch rectangular pan.

title: kraut salad
directions: Heat vinegar or sugar to boiling point.
Pour over celery, onion, green pepper and kraut.
Put into a glass jar and refrigerate.

title: apple crisp
directions: Combine first four ingredients.
Cut in butter, until crumbly.
Press 1/2 of the mixture into a 9 in. square pan.
Cover with apples.
In a saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch, water, and vanilla.
Cook and stir until thick and clear.
Pour over the apples.
Sprinkle with the remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350°F for about an hour or until the apples are tender.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix with hands.
Roll into small balls and bake at 400° for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: turkey meatball stroganoff
directions: Combine turkey, crushed seasoning cubes and garlic powder. Form into balls.
Spray skillet with cooking spray.
Brown turkey balls on all sides.
Remove and drain on paper towels.
Cook onions in 2 tablespoons chicken broth until tender.
Add minced garlic, mushrooms and flour.
Stir in broth mix, ketchup and water.
Boil.
Return turkey balls to skillet and heat but do not boil.
Simmer uncovered about 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir in sour cream but do not boil.
Serve turkey balls and sauce over cooked linguine.

title: baracuda
directions: Blend with crushed ice.
Pour into cocktail glass.
Garnish with red cherry.

title: cheese dip
directions: Mix together in a blender a little at a time.

title: sausage rolls
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut pie crust into 3 x 3-inch squares. Use about a teaspoonful of sausage; put into pastry square and fold over and together.
Use a fork to press the remaining 3 sides down.
Put a slit in each one.
Rub egg whites on top for browning glaze.
Bake for about 30 minutes, or when pastry is done.
(Kids love to do this one.)

title: winter vegetable soup(low calorie)
directions: Heat water and oil in a Dutch oven over medium heat.
Add onion and leeks.
Cover and cook 15 minutes or until tender.
Add thyme, rosemary and minced garlic; saute 2 minutes.
Add broth and next 2 ingredients; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Add potatoes and next 5 ingredients; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium.
Cook, uncovered, 45 minutes.
Stir in kale and next 2 ingredients; cook for 2 minutes. Garnish with cheese if desired.
Yield:
16 1/2 cups.

title: baked caramel corn
directions: In heavy saucepan, mix margarine, brown sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Boil mixture, stirring constantly, over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add baking soda and vanilla.
Pour over popped corn and coat evenly.
Put mixture on 2 large jelly roll pans that have been coated well with margarine.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes, stirring after 15 minutes.
Store in airtight container when cooled.

title: brownies
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Pour into 10 x 15-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: chicken and walnuts
directions: Brown chicken, if not boneless.
Slice chicken into strips. Heat oil and saute walnuts until golden.
Drain on paper towels. Reserve 1/4 cup oil.
Saute chicken in reserved oil for 5 minutes. Add broth, cover and cook on medium-high heat for 5 minutes.
In a separate bowl combine cornstarch, soy sauce and water until smooth.
Add mixture and salt to skillet.
Cook, stirring the sauce until thick and translucent.
Add walnuts.

title: apple pie
directions: Peel apples. Slice 1/4-inch thick. Mix with sugar, cinnamon and cornstarch. Add to apples and mix. Fill bottom of pie crust. Top generously with butter. Add top crust. Seal and slit with own design. Brush with water or egg white for brownness. Sprinkle with a little sugar. Bake for 50 minutes to 1 hour at 425°.

title: beet jelly
directions: Bring beet juice, lemon juice and sure jell to a boil. Add sugar and jello boil 6 minutes. Seal in hot jars.

title: pineapple glazed ham
directions: In a covered blender container at low speed, blend all ingredients until smooth.
Makes about 1 cup.
Bake ham.
During the last 30 minutes of roasting time, brush glaze over ham 2 or 3 times.

title: frozen dessert
directions: Soften cream cheese with milk.
Boil 1 cup of juice from drained fruit; add Jell-O.
Mix with cream cheese.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Add cherries. Add whipped cream.
Fold in mayonnaise, bananas, lemon juice, pineapple, maraschino cherries, pecans and marshmallows.
Add to Jell-O mixture.
Pour into pan. Cover and freeze.
Serve in sliced squares.

title: swiss creamed peas
directions: Cook peas as directed on package.
In saucepan, cook onions in butter until tender.
Blend in flour and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Add cream and lemon peel.
Add cheese.
Cook until melted.
Put peas in serving bowl.
Pour sauce over peas and serve.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except mushrooms, in a large casserole dish.
Layer mushrooms on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In small skillet, cook onion in oil until tender.
Stir in chili powder, salt, garlic salt, Tabasco sauce and tomato sauce.
In medium bowl, combine chicken with olives and 1/2 cup sauce mixture.
Over medium heat, fry tortillas in about 1/4-inch hot oil just until softened, a few seconds on each side. Drain on paper towels.
Divide chicken mixture among the 12 tortillas.
Roll up each tortilla; place seam-side down in lightly greased 13 x 9-inch (3-quart) baking dish.
Pour remaining sauce over tortillas; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until heated through.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Saute onions in butter. Add milk and cream cheese. Mix until smooth. Add remaining ingredients. Simmer about 1 hour. Top with bacon bits and Cheddar cheese.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Measure oatmeal into mixing bowl; add oil.
Blend in egg and saccharin.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with combined milk and vanilla.
Mix in raisins.
Drop by level teaspoonfuls onto baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Yields 36 cookies or 12 servings.
Each serving (3 cookies) contains approximately 1 bread exchange.

title: enchiladas
directions: Mix enchilada sauce, chili and soup; simmer 10 minutes.
Brown beef; drain and add taco seasoning with a little water.
Simmer. Soften tortillas one at a time in sauce; fill with meat mix, onion and cheese.
Roll and layer in a casserole dish.
Mix leftover sauce and meat; pour over rolls.
Add grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.
Top with chopped green onions.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cut large shrimp in half.
Melt shortening; blend in flour and brown, stirring constantly.
Add water gradually and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add shrimp and remaining ingredients, except rice.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Remove bay leaves.
Serve over Rice Pilaf.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Combine cream cheese and sugar. Set aside. Slice cookie dough into round medallions.
Lay slices on pizza pan until pan is covered.
Bake at 350° until golden around the edge.
Cookie should be soft after it has cooled. When cool, spread cream cheese mixture on top.
Take fruit and scatter all over cream cheese mixture. Cover entire cookie with fruit.
Slice into pizza slices and serve.
Makes 1 (12-inch) pizza.

title: pineapple bread pudding
directions: Place bread on a baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 4 minutes; turn over and bake 4 minutes longer or until light brown.
Cut toasted bread into 1-inch cubes.
Toss with melted margarine; set aside.
In a bowl, beat eggs until thick and lemon-colored.
Add the pineapple, raisins, sugar and vanilla; mix well.
Fold in bread cubes.
Pour into a greased 2 1/2-quart baking dish. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until bubbly and golden brown.
Serve warm.
Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: honey mustard
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Goes great with turkey or ham sandwiches.

title: scalloped chicken
directions: Cook chicken thoroughly and cut in small pieces.
Make white sauce with butter, flour and milk.
Add 1 can cream of mushroom soup, broth and celery.
Spread layer of croutettes in bottom of baking dish.
Add pieces of chicken and then the cream sauce.
Top with croutettes.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients until smooth.
Spray Pam nonstick spray into a Bundt pan.
Pour cake mixture into Bundt pan.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: bologna
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients and let set overnight in refrigerator. Add remaining ingredients.
Shape bologna.
Bake at 250° for 2 hours, turning it every 1/2 hour.

title: marinated chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken in margarine and oil in 10-inch skillet over medium heat until done, about 6 minutes on each side.
Cool slightly.
Cut into thin slices.
Mix soy sauce, sesame seed, lemon juice and garlic; toss with chicken.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 4 hours.

title: cranberry cake with vanilla sauce(serves 24)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream sugar and butter.
Mix in milk, flour, baking powder and salt.
Add cranberries.
Bake in 1 greased 9-inch pan at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: stuffed yellow squash
directions: Boil whole squash until tender.
Cool.
Cut in half lengthwise. Remove insides and mix with meat, eggs, onion, rice, breadcrumbs, salt and pepper.
Lightly sprinkle squash with salt.
Stuff squash with mixture and top with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until meat is done.

title: poor boy stew
directions: Brown ground meat and onion in a skillet; drain.
Pour into Dutch oven and add all the remaining ingredients.
Add 1/2 cup water or more if you like more juice.
Cook on low heat for 30 minutes or until warmed thoroughly.
This recipe can be doubled and cooked in a crock-pot.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast and 1 teaspoon sugar in lukewarm water.
Set aside.
In 4-quart bowl, mix flour, 3/8 cup sugar, salt, egg whites, cooking oil and yeast mixture.
Mix.

title: easy batter for deep frying
directions: Combine Bisquick and cornstarch.
Add just enough cold water to make a thick sauce that's not too pasty.
Put meat, fish or vegetable pieces into batter to coat.
Fry in hot oil until golden brown.

title: caramel creams
directions: Place first 4 ingredients in a large, heavy saucepan.
Heat over medium flame until mixture comes to a full boil.
Turn down flame to high simmer and continue to cook to 236° on candy thermometer (or soft ball in cold water) stirring constantly (about 15 to 20 minutes).
Remove from heat; add vanilla and nuts (if wanted) and mix thoroughly.
Pour hot mixture into foil-lined pan (8 x 8 or 6 x 9-inch).
Cool.
When cold, remove from pan. Peel off foil and cut into 64 squares.
Wrap in squares of wax paper.
Store in covered container.

title: osgood pie
directions: Beat egg yolks and add sugar. Continue beating until well blended. Add remaining ingredients except egg whites.
When mixture is well mixed, fold in the well beaten egg whites.
Bake in unbaked crust until firm.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Serve cold with whipped cream.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Combine flour, oatmeal, butter, brown sugar and cinnamon until crumbly.
Put half of mixture into a greased 9-inch pan.
Cover with rhubarb.
Combine sugar, cornstarch and water in a saucepan. Boil until thick.
Pour over rhubarb.
Cover with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: orange frost
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add sherbet by spoonfuls, stirring until dissolved.
Beat with mixer until frosty.
Pour into individual molds.
Chill until firm.
Garnish with whipped cream.

title: louisiana fruit salad
directions: Prepare fruits.
Add lemon juice to apples and bananas. Combine yogurt, honey, cinnamon, pecans and coconut in a separate bowl.
Gently stir into fruit mixture.
Chill before serving.

title: ambrosia fruit salad
directions: Can use any other fruits desired.
Drain fruit and combine all ingredients.
Chill and serve.

title: creamy hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and store in airtight container.
Use 1/3 cup of mixture, fill cup the rest of the way up with boiling water.
This will save for months in airtight container.

title: banana-nut bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Cream the shortening and sugar. Add eggs. Beat good. Add dry ingredients alternately with bananas.
Mix walnuts and 1 tablespoon flour.
Mix with batter.
Pour in greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: vanilla wafer surprise
directions: Crush wafers.
Add sugar and eggs.
Mix margarine and milk together.
Add to wafer mix.
Add coconut, chips and pecans.
Bake in oblong pan for 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken and veggie casserole
directions: Boil chicken and tear in small pieces.
Add mixed vegetables, broccoli, grated Cheddar cheese, onion, salt, pepper and mayonnaise.
Mix well; place in a long baking pan.
Chop bread into squares and put on top of casserole.
Bake 10 minutes or until cooked through and bread is browned.

title: hot pepper jam
directions: Using rubber gloves to handle hot peppers, place peppers and all their juices, vinegar and sugar in a 5 or 6-quart kettle. Stir over high heat to dissolve sugar and then boil for 4 minutes. Remove from heat; cool 1 minute and add Certo and coloring and stir well.
Pour into sterilized glasses and seal with paraffin or use jars with 2 piece lids and process 10 minutes in hot water bath.
Makes about 4 to 5 pint jars.

title: chicken-almond casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, topping with part of the potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: blueberry sherbet
directions: Soften gelatin in 1/3 cup warm pineapple juice.
Chill.
Put gelatin mixture and all other ingredients into blender.
Blend 5 minutes.
Strain.
Pour into ice cube trays to make cubes. Freeze.
Before serving put cubes and 1/3 cup remaining cold pineapple juice in blender.
Blend until smooth.

title: shortbread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix ingredients, it's very sticky. Spray mold and press half in mold.
Spread on jam.
Put remaining dough on top (it does not have to completely cover the jam, or be smooth).
Bake about 40 minutes.

title: south philly's sunday gravy(tomato sauce)
directions: In large quart pot, saute garlic and parsley.
Empty can of tomato paste with two cans of water.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Add tomatoes, with can of water and tomato puree.
Add basil.
Cook on very low heat.
Stir constantly, every 20 minutes.
Cook for at least 3 hours.
Add meat balls and Italian sausages or serve over favorite pasta without meat.

title: skillet spaghetti(serves 4 to 6)
directions: In large skillet, break up ground meat.
Add remaining ingredients - except spaghetti.
Cover and bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add spaghetti; stir to separate strands.
Simmer, covered, 30 minutes or longer until spaghetti is tender.
Stir frequently.
Serve with parmesan cheese.

title: mom's best fudge
directions: Mix sugar and milk; add butter.
Place over low flame to melt butter.
Turn up flame when mixture starts to boil hard.
Boil for 5 minutes, exactly, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into greased jelly roll pan.
Let cool, then cut.

title: best ever rolls(saturday, october 30)
directions: Bring 3/4 cup water and 1/4 cup milk to boil and pour into large mixing bowl.
Add potato and beat with whisk or fork until blended.
Heat remaining milk in same saucepan and pour over potato, 2/3 cup margarine and next 2 ingredients.
Cool to lukewarm.
Soften yeast in 1/2 cup warm water and add to first mixture with eggs and 3 cups flour.
Beat with wooden spoon or electric mixer until smooth and light.
Stir in enough more flour by hand to make a dough firm enough to knead.
Turn out on floured board and knead 10 minutes or until elastic.

title: 30 minute low-fat microwave quiche
directions: Place crust in 9-inch glass pie plate and flute edges. Microwave on Roast 6 to 6 1/2 minutes or until brown spots just begin to appear on crust.
Cool.

title: light dip
directions: Cream cottage cheese in mixer or blender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill several hours to soften onion bits. Serve with crackers, fresh vegetables or potato chips.

title: ground beef barbecue
directions: Mix everything well.
Do not brown hamburger.
Simmer 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: cheese crispies
directions: Mix all ingredients except cereal.
Fold in cereal and work into balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Pat flat with a fork.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: aunt cookie's baked beans
directions: Warm on top of stove.
Cook in crock-pot for 6 to 7 hours. Lift lid near end to help thicken.
Or bake at 250° in oven for 6 to 7 hours.

title: donna's special cheeseball
directions: Mix the first four ingredients in a bowl and cream together. Form into a ball.
Roll in bacon bits or chopped nuts.
Garnish with chopped green onions if desired.
Chill (best if chilled overnight).
Serves 20 - 25 people.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: In a large bowl, layer ingredients in order given.
Tightly cover.
Refrigerate overnight.
Toss before serving.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Mix together soup, oil, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, and sugar.
Pour over carrots, onions, and peppers. Cover tightly, refrigerate 12 to 24 hours.

title: tuna-cheese pie
directions: Beat eggs lightly and combine with other ingredients in 9 or 10-inch pie plate or casserole.
Bake 50 minutes at 300°.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
