This is a tasty meal for the calorie conscious.

title: mom's lemon pie
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and add boiling water.
Cook until clear.
(I cook it in the microwave.)
Stir occasionally.
Add egg yolks and lemon rind and juice.
Cook a little longer.
Add margarine and salt.
(You may add yellow food color.)
Pour into baked pie crust.
Top with meringue.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat together first 3 ingredients.
Mix together next 5 ingredients.
Add zucchini.
Mix dry ingredients and zucchini together.
Add next 2 ingredients.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans. Pour in batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: love cake
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Add slightly beaten egg yolks.
Mix until fluffy.
Add milk and flour.
Fold in coconut. Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into batter.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Simmer vegetables in broth in a nonstick skillet until vegetables are crisp and tender. Add pasta. Stir in dip and heat through. Serves 4.

title: quick and easy chocolate mousse pie
directions: Break chocolate bars into small pieces.
Set aside 2 sections (set in freezer while preparing pie).
Melt chocolate bars in a double boiler in microwave or on stove top.
Stir in Cool Whip. Spoon mixture into pie shell.
Garnish with shaved chocolate (from pieces set in freezer) or strawberries.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: scuffletown kraut salad
directions: Early in the day, combine kraut with all the other ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Great for days!

title: chocolate buttermallow cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease and flour oblong 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake cake mix as directed. Cool in pan.

title: pot roast
directions: Brown beef in bacon grease on both sides.
Add enough water to cover beef.
Add chopped onion.
Cover pan and cook for approximately 2 hours.
Add carrots, onions and potatoes under beef and cook until tender.

title: chinese fried rice
directions: Fry bacon in skillet until brown and slightly crisp.
Crumble into small pieces.
Add beef, pork or chicken, onion and pepper. Stir-fry for 2 to 3 minutes. Add rice and stir-fry 5 to 7 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Combine eggs and soy sauce.
Pour over rice and stir gently until eggs are cooked.
Sprinkle green onion over rice. Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Melt unsweetened chocolate and butter over low heat.
When melted, remove from heat and add sugar and evaporated milk; stir. Return to low heat until sauce begins to boil.
Boil for about one or two minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed and bake; cool slightly.
Pierce cake with fork and drizzle Kahlua over cake.
Prepare mousse in large bowl.
Break cake into pieces; layer cake pieces, mousse, crushed candy and whipped topping 1/3 at a time in large glass bowl.
Shave milk chocolate bar over top.
Makes 12 servings.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Cream Crisco; add sugars and cream again.
Add eggs.
Add milk, vanilla, flour, soda and baking powder.
Stir in oats, nuts, chocolate chips and corn flakes.
Drop by spoonfuls.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chocolate turtle pie
directions: Spread caramel topping on bottom of crust; sprinkle with pecans.
Refrigerate.

title: joshua's pbm treat
directions: Spread peanut butter on bread.
Top with marshmallows.
Put under broiler for a few seconds until marshmallows are tan.
Cool and enjoy.
Delicious.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Cut bell peppers in half and clean.
Parboil the peppers until tender, saving some of the water.
Put peppers aside to drain. Chop all vegetables and place in a large pot with oil.
Saute vegetables until clear.
Put ground round, ground pork and ham in pot.
Cook until brown.
Drain off excess grease.
Put in potted meat.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook on low heat for about 1 hour.
Turn off.
Add bread crumbs to dressing.
If too stiff, add water from peppers.
Take pepper shells and stuff with dressing. Dust with bread crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake until hot.

title: sicilian cheese and anchovy bread(if you're brave...)
directions: Slice the bread in half, as you would a biscuit.
Lightly brush the oil on both halves of the bread, then pepper each side. Layer the cheese, and if you are going authentic, the anchovies on one side, then replace the top.
Wrap in foil and bake in a 425° oven until the cheese is melted.

title: ritz broccoli casserole
directions: Layer ingredients in a baking dish as follows:
broccoli, 1/2 cheese, 1/2 crumbled crackers and repeat until all are used.
Melt margarine and pour over dish.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown beef and onion in large skillet.
Drain.
Add dry taco seasoning mix and 1 cup water and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes. Saute tortillas in hot oil just enough to heat.
Spoon meat mixture evenly in center of each tortilla.
Roll up and place seam down in rectangular pan or jellyroll pan.
Combine remaining ingredients except Cheddar cheese in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until cheese slices are melted.
Pour evenly over tortillas. Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbling.
(Use soft tortillas.)

title: chili(meatless)
directions: Place dried beans in water and soak overnight.
Simmer for 3 hours and drain.
Combine beans, 6 cups water, 1/3 cup chopped onion, minced garlic, bay leaf and tomato paste and simmer 2 hours.
Heat oil in separate pan, gradually stir in flour, chili powder, cumin, 1/3 cup onion and garlic powder.
Heat 5 minutes. Stir in beans and cook 1 hour until beans are soft and chili is thickened.
Add salt and pepper.

title: quick pound cake
directions: Beat, put in greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: *sausage and spinach pie
directions: Brown chopped sausage over medium heat until well browned (10 minutes).
Drain off fat.
Reserve 1 egg yolk, then beat 5 egg yolks slightly.
Add to sausage, along with the remainder of the ingredients; set aside.

title: my favorite lemon pie
directions: Remove crusts from bread and dip in bowl of water until wet. Squeeze
out
water
and measure in cup, not packing too tight. Put
sugar,
wet
bread,
egg
yolks,
lemon juice and butter
in double
boiler.
Cook
until thick enough to stand when cut.
Pour into baked crust.
Make meringue of whites and sugar and
cover pie
from edge to edge.
Bake at 300° for 10 minutes.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except Cool Whip.
Fold in Cool Whip. Freeze in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut in squares.

title: fruit sorbet
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Stir in strawberries, corn syrup and egg whites.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Freeze until partially frozen, about 2 hours.

title: griddlecakes
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
With rotary beater, beat egg.
Add milk and butter; beat until well mixed. Pour into dry ingredients.
Beat only until combined; batter will be lumpy.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix hot water and mint. Let stand 30 minutes. Strain liquid and discard mint. Pour into a 2-quart container. Stir in sugar, water, lemon and lime juices. Chill 8 hours. Pour mixture into a large punch bowl. Stir in strawberries and remaining ingredients just before serving.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Mash and mix the Avocados, Salt and Lemon Juice.
Mix Sour Cream, Mayonnaise, and Taco Seasoning.
Combine all ingredients except the Chips.
Serve.

title: chocolate banana nut bread
directions: Puree bananas in blender.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt; set aside.
Cream butter and sugar; beat in eggs.
Blend in pureed bananas.
Blend in dry mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour into well greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes until loaf tests done.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Turn out to wire rack to cool.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: fat-free honey mustard dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in bowl; whisk or blend together.

title: beer roast
directions: Salt and pepper roast.
Add the ingredients together in bowl. Place roast in baking dish. Pour mixture over roast.
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 350°.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute onion and garlic with ground chuck.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer to desired thickness.

title: stuffed beef tenderloin
directions: Marinate tenderloin overnight in Chablis.
Melt butter in saucepan; stir in thyme.
Add onion; simmer until mixture cooks down to half volume.
Add mushrooms; cook 4 minutes.
Cut a pocket in tenderloin and stuff with onion and mushroom mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes per pound.

title: calico scrambled eggs
directions: Saute green pepper and onion in butter until tender.
Remove and set aside.
In a medium bowl, beat eggs with milk, dill, salt & pepper.
Pour egg mixture into a non-stick skillet and cook until nearly set.
Add pepper mixture and tomato.
Cook and stir until heated through and the eggs are set.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: minced lamb
directions: Combine soup and milk; beat until smooth.
Add lamb.
Heat. Beat egg yolks; gradually add lamb mixture.
Return to heat; slowly cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Serve immediately on buttered toast triangles.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Season and brown pork chops on both sides.
Arrange potatoes in 2-quart baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients, except cheese, and pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Combine apples, sugar, flour, vanilla and cinnamon; set aside. Combine flour and salt; with a knife or pastry blender cut in shortening.
Add eggs, lemon juice and enough water to form a workable dough.
Divide dough in half, roll out half on floured board.
Line 13 x 9-inch pan.
Fill with apple mixture.
Roll out remaining dough, cover apples and seal edges.
Brush top with milk. Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool for 30 minutes.
Top with sauce.
Yields one 13 x 9-inch cobbler.

title: grandma hall's pound cake
directions: Combine butter, oil, milk, flour, sugar and vanilla. Beat. Beat eggs separately and add to mixture.
Mix well. Bake in a well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Test for doneness.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix pumpkin and dry ingredients together.
Add eggs and milk; mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mandarin spinach salad
directions: Combine ingredients in desired proportions.

title: creamed tomato bisque soup
directions: Saute vegetables in butter.
Add flour and cook 2 minutes. Add ingredients to broth; simmer 30 minutes.
Puree in blender. Add cream and seasonings; serve hot.
Freezes well.

title: orange delight
directions: Combine cottage cheese, orange Jell-O (undissolved) and pineapple until well mixed.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate 2 hours or more.
Decorate with maraschino cherries and mint leaves, if desired.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix sour cream, cream cheese, chopped olives, chopped green onions and chopped green chiles together in a food processor. Roll mixture into flour tortillas and wrap each with a damp paper towel.
Refrigerate overnight.
Slice in pieces (about 8 to 10 per tortilla roll).
Serve with picante sauce.

title: cabbage, apple and kielbasa pot pie(serves 6)
directions: Combine flour and salt.
Cut in shortening and butter until pea sized pieces.
Sprinkle water as needed to put dough together. Cover and chill 30 minutes.

title: adrienne's delight
directions: Let cream cheese, butter and sour cream come to room temperature.
Cream well and add sugar.
Add raisins, almonds and lemon rind.
Put in a quart mold; refrigerate.
When firm, unmold and serve with crackers or dark bread.
(This can be frozen after unmolding.)

title: cream cheese danish
directions: Press 1 can of the crescent rolls in bottom of 9 x 12-inch baking dish, mashing perforations together.

title: cheese pecan pie
directions: Mix well the cream cheese, 1 tablespoon sugar and 9 drops of vanilla. Pour into crust. Put pecans gently over cream cheese mixture. Beat eggs, Karo syrup, sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla real good and pour over pie. Bake at 350° about 30 minutes. DELICIOUS!

title: zucchini pie
directions: Cook zucchini until tender; cool and drain.
Add remaining ingredients and place in unbaked pie shell.
Cover with top crust and seal edges.
Cut slits for steam to escape.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli and macaroni
directions: Use as much or as little as you need, depending on taste and number of servings.

title: punch base
directions: Boil water, sugar and honey.
Add remaining ingredients.
Let cool and then strain the rind out.
Store in refrigerator or freezer.
Use 1 part of base to 3 parts ginger ale or 7-Up.

title: chocolate banana cream pie
directions: Arrange banana slices on bottom of crust; set aside.
Pour milk into medium bowl.
Add pie filling mix.
Beat with wire whisk 1 minute or until well blended.
Pour mixture at once into crust. Cover with whipped topping.
Refrigerate 3 hours or until set.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix well and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 30 minutes at 375°.

title: candied pecans
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan in the oven.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gradually beat in brown sugar.
Gently fold in pecans.
Pour into buttered pan, spreading evenly.
Bake for 1 hour, turning every 10 minutes.
Drain pecans on paper towels.
Makes 2 cups.

title: cream cheese dessert(or fly united)
directions: Bowl 1:
Mix cream cheese, 3/4 cup sugar and egg yolk until smooth.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Defrost strawberries.
Beat eggs until fluffy; add oil, sugar and strawberries.
Combine flour, cinnamon and soda; then add to strawberry mixture.
Stir in chopped nuts.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf (9 1/2 x 5 x 3-inch) pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes, or until done.
Cool in pans 10 minutes, then remove.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain. Melt Velveeta cheese and 1/2 stick margarine together. Crush crackers and mix with 1/2 stick of melted margarine. Grease a casserole dish. Mix broccoli and butter-cheese mixture together. Put in casserole and top with crackers. Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: venison pot pie(serves 6 to 8)
directions: A few frozen peas or corn may also be added.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash and slice cucumbers and onions crosswise.
Mix cucumbers, onions and salt; cover with ice.
Place heavy lid over and let stand for 3 hours.
Mix sugar, turmeric and cloves; add mustard seed, celery seed and vinegar.
Pour over cucumbers and onions. Cook over low heat until mixture reaches scalding point (do not boil).
Place in hot jars and seal.

title: oliebollen(tradition for new year's eve in holland)
directions: Blend yeast with a little lukewarm milk.
Sift the flour and salt.
Add milk.
Mix to a batter with yeast and egg.
Add currants, raisins and peeled, minced apple.
Leave batter in a warm place to rise to double in size.
Heat oil to 375°.
Put two metal spoons into the batter. Shape balls and drop into oil.
Fry for 8 minutes or until brown. Drain and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: meat loaf
directions: Moisten bread in 1/8 cup milk.
Mix ingredients well.
Form into a loaf and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Before baking, spread additional catsup over the top of the loaf.

title: scalloped apples
directions: Melt oleo.
Add sugar, crumbs and cinnamon.
Place half of the mixture in bottom of casserole. Add apples.
Put remainder of crumb mixture on top.
Pour 1/2 cup water over entire mixture. Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lil's egg dish
directions: Brown sausage until crumbly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Keep in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
When removed from oven, sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and paprika.

title: carrot bread
directions: Sift flour, soda, cinnamon, salt and sugar.
Add oil and eggs. Combine well.
Add carrots, vanilla, pecans and raisins.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in 2 loaf pans.

title: pineapple cheese cake
directions: Beat cheese mixture until creamy; set aside.
Mix jello in boiling water.
Cool.
Add pineapple.
Beat Milnot until peaks form.
Fold cheese mixture into jello mixture, then fold all into whipped Milnot.
Put in prepared crust.

title: blender cheesecake
directions: Put water and jello in blender and beat until dissolved.
Add lemon and 1 cup cottage cheese.
Liquefy until smooth.
Add rest of cottage cheese and beat well.
Pour into large bowl.
Add whipped cream and mix well.
Pour over crust.
Chill.

title: zippy italian dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of an electric blender. Blend well. Cover and chill at least 1 hour.
Yields 2 cups.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar and milk in medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil; turn down heat to medium flame.
Add peanut butter and butter, stirring constantly.
Test for consistency by using 1/2 cup cold water. Add a little fudge to water and when fudge forms a ball in your fingers remove from heat.
(Note:
You can use a candy thermometer; bring candy to 240°.)
Add vanilla and mix with whisk or mixer.
Butter a 9 x 12-inch cake pan or larger platter. Chill; cut into squares and serve.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt margarine and beat eggs before combining with other ingredients.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake for 60 minutes at 350°. May need to cover toward the end of baking time.

title: chicken or turkey casserole
directions: Mix together and place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix stuffing mix with broth and butter.
Spread over top of first mixture in pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sour cream fudge
directions: In a large microwave bowl (4-quart) mix the sugar, sour cream, margarine, salt and marshmallows.
Cook on full power for 14 minutes.
Stir after 4 to 5 minutes and again as needed, until done and well blended.
Stir in white coating or shave the block chocolate into the mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Stir well and pour into a greased pan to cool before cutting.

title: oyster cracker snack
directions: Put aside crackers and mix spices and oil together well in a large bowl.
Add the crackers and stir carefully to coat them well. Place crackers on large cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes, stirring once about 8 minutes into baking time.
Let cool. Munch away!

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut top off peppers and clean out, leaving spines to support the peppers.
Put peppers in boiling water for 6 to 8 minutes. Remove and drain well.
Brown beef and pour off fat.
Mix in rice and some tomato sauce.
Stuff the peppers with meat mixture.
Put in casserole dish.
Spoon a little more tomato sauce on top of each pepper.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 20 minutes.

title: fresh green bean, plum tomato and mozzarella cheese salad
directions: Mix well and refrigerate for at least 1 hour, then serve.

title: bean dip
directions: Mix all ingredients except for cheese.
Pour into pan.
Put cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until bubbly hot.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter. Add broccoli and stir until thawed. Add remaining ingredients.
Place in greased casserole. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Stir first 3 ingredients until dissolved over heat.
Bring to boil, cook 2 minutes in double boiler or stir constantly.
Cool slightly.
Mix last 3 ingredients with electric mixer, add first mixture to this.
Beat until creamy, press into pan, add peanut chips if desired on top.
Cut in squares.

title: golden punch
directions: Chill all ingredients, then pour into punch bowl.
This recipe makes approximately 33 (6 ounce) servings.

title: tomato pudding
directions: In baking dish, arrange layers of bread crumbs and tomatoes. Sprinkle each layer of tomatoes with sugar and nutmeg.
Put graham cracker crumbs over the top and dot with butter.
Bake in a 350° oven about 30 minutes.

title: rizogalo(greek rice pudding)
directions: In a large saucepan, simmer covered rice and water until water is gone.
Slowly add milk, sugar and butter.
Cook together, uncovered, for 40 minutes over very low heat.
Dissolve cornstarch in a little of the hot milk mixture; add this to well beaten eggs. Slowly pour egg mixture into hot milk in pan, stirring constantly.
Simmer over very low heat for 2 minutes, until it begins to thicken.
Add vanilla.
Pour into custard cups. Sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Makes 12 servings.

title: jiffy apple cake
directions: Combine all ingredients together with a spoon.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and let stand overnight.
Add the bananas and grapes.

title: michelle's peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil together the sugar and milk until soft ball stage is reached.
Remove from heat and add flavorings, Marshmallow Creme and peanut butter.
Mix quickly.
Pour into greased pan.
Cut in squares when cool.

title: dill-onion bread in the bread machine
directions: Add all ingredients except the onion in the order given to the bread machine.
Select a Mix Bread Menu, and add the chopped onion when the machine beeps for the addition.
The machine will do the rest.

title: crabmeat delights
directions: Blend first 6 ingredients.
Spread on English muffin halves. Freeze until ready to use. Cut into 8 wedges while frozen. Broil until bubbly.
Each muffin half yields 8 pieces.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix cake mix, coconut pudding, oil and eggs. Add poppy seed and hot water.
Mix well and bake in 2 loaf pans 45 minutes at 325°.
Adjust time if small pans are used.

title: pineapple, cherry and nuts cake
directions: Mix pudding with milk.
When this is set, mix with one container of Cool Whip.
Frost cake.
Chop nuts.
Chop well drained cherries.
Drain crushed pineapple.
Sprinkle each over frosting.

title: bone sucken chicken
directions: Put your chicken, skinned, in a shallow baking pan.
Thin barbecue sauce down to a soupy consistency by adding a mixture of beer,
mayo and spices.
Pour over chicken and then bake in oven at 375° for about 45 minutes.
Cooking time depends on type of chicken parts used.
Done when chicken falls off bone.
Serves as much as you make.

title: stir-fried chicken
directions: Remove strings from pea pods.
Place in boiling water.
Boil 1 minute.
Drain.
Rinse under cold water.
Drain.
Mix cornstarch and water.
Add soy sauce.
Reserve.
Cut boned and skinned chicken in 1/4-inch slices.
Heat wok.
Spray with Pam or small amount of oil.
Add chicken, garlic and ginger root.
Cook until chicken nicely browns over high heat.
Stir constantly.
When chicken is done, remove from skillet.
Add 2 tablespoons of oil and mushrooms. Cook until tender and add green pepper and carrots.
Cook and stir until desired doneness.
Add chicken broth.
Heat to boil.
Stir in cornstarch until thick.
Add pea pods and soy sauce.
Serve over rice.
Any vegetable may be added besides pea pods.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Cook rice as per instructions on the box. Cook broccoli as per instructions on the package until tender. Don't overcook! Combine soup, cheese, butter and cooked rice in a large bowl. Add cooked broccoli and mix together. Pour into a baking dish. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes. Top with croutons before baking if desired.

title: miss iris mae's devil's food cake
directions: Combine margarine, oil, cocoa and water.
Bring to a boil. Remove from heat.
Combine sugar and flour; add cocoa mixture. Stir until smooth.
Combine rest of ingredients and add to cocoa mixture.
Stir well.
Cook in greased sheet cake pan for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: wonder crescents
directions: Mix flour and sugar; add butter.
Mix as for pie crust.
Make a well; add egg yolks, wine and sour cream.
Mix dough; let set in refrigerator overnight.
Roll out very thin.
Cut into 3-inch squares and spread with jam or walnut filling.
Roll into crescent shape; brush with egg yolk and bake in a moderate oven until golden brown.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Coat square 8 x 8-inch dish with margarine.
Mix beans together in large bowl.
Mix brown sugar and dry mustard together in separate bowl.
Put half of beans in square dish.
Sprinkle half of dry mixture over beans.
Add remainder of beans.
Sprinkle remainder of dry mixture over beans.
Spread ketchup over the top to edges.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, combine first 3 ingredients and egg yolk (save white).
Blend well.
Stir in flour and salt.
Blend well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Slightly beat egg white.
Dip balls in egg white, then roll in nuts.
Place 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press deep indentation in center of each cookie with thumb.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Immediately remove from cookie sheet. Cool.
Fill centers with jam or jelly.

title: lemon bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, butter and 1/2 cup powdered sugar.
Mix and press into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake 20 minutes.
Meanwhile, mix eggs, sugar, salt and lemon juice. Fold in 1/4 cup flour and baking powder.
Pour onto hot crust; bake 25 minutes longer.
Cool; cut into squares and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Brown meat and onion in a large pan.
Add tomato juice, beans and ketchup.
Add seasonings to taste: onion, salt and pepper. Cook slowly one hour, then add 1/3 pound mostaccioli noodles.
Cook slowly, stirring frequently until noodles are done.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in pan (9 x 8-inch).
Mix together flour, sugar, milk and baking powder.
Put fruit over butter, then pour in mix. Bake until golden brown.

title: jalapeno dressing
directions: Crumble cornbread into
a large bowl.
Add white bread, jalapeno peppers and juice; toss to mix.
Heat bacon drippings in a large
skillet
over
medium-high
heat.
Add
onions and celery.
Cook 3
minutes, stirring twice.
Add water, salt and black pepper.
Reduce heat
to
medium,
cover and cook 5 to 7 minutes.
Celery is crisp-tender.
Add bread to mixture.
Stir in broth a
little
at
a time until well blended and stuffing was moist as
desired.
Spoon into turkey or bake in a greased 4 quart baking dish in 350° oven about 30 minutes until heated through. Makes 14 cups, enough for 12 to 15 pound turkey.
My husband loves this, he doesn't like chicken in his dressing.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in oleo.
In a separate pan, cook broccoli 5 minutes and drain.
Mix together onion, celery, cooked rice and broccoli.
Pour into casserole.
Mix Cheez Whiz and cream of mushroom soup.
Pour over top.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix syrup, water and sugar, bringing to boil.
Add warm peanuts.
Cook 7 minutes, then add soda.
Then spread on baking sheet or foil paper.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt margarine, cool; add cocoa then add remaining ingredients and blend well.
Bake in unbaked pie shell at 325° for 35 minutes until pie is firm in middle.

title: calico bean soup
directions: Rinse and drain all beans and peas, black beans separately. In a big pot, cook beans and peas with ham bone for 3 hours.
Cook black beans separately, then drain and add to other beans.
Remove ham bone.
Add veggies and salt.
Cook another hour.
Yummy!

title: vegetarian barbecue beans
directions: Drain excess liquid from beans and dump into casserole dish. Add mustard, barbecue sauce and molasses.
Stir until mustard, sauce and molasses are evenly distributed.
Bake in a preheated oven at 375° for about 45 minutes, until beans have "cooked down." Sprinkle with grated cheese and broil until brown.
Sprinkle on crushed red pepper to taste.
(The "heat" can also be adjusted by the variety of barbecue sauce used.)
Serves 4 as side dish or two as main dish.

title: aunt ella's pie crust
directions: Stir salt and flour together in large bowl.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender until size of small peas.
Sprinkle water slowly and toss with a fork until dough begins to stick together. (May not need to use all the water in humid summer weather.)

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters.
Combine 3/4 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon.
Put into bag.
Add biscuits.
Shake until biscuits are covered.
Drop into greased Bundt cake pan.
Combine remaining ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate covered candy
directions: Melt butter.
Mix
in
sugar
and milk.
Make into small balls and
chill.
Mix
paraffin
and chocolate bar.
Melt them and dip chilled candy into the chocolate mixture.
Place candy on wax paper and allow to harden.

title: flour tortillas
directions: Mix flour, salt and shortening.
Add hot water a little at a time.
Mix until firm.
Let stand.
Make rounds (testales).
Roll out with a rolling pin (palote).
Cook on hot griddle (comal) with low flame.
Serve with meal or add butter.

title: easy cheese potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients, except 1/2 cup Colby cheese.
Mix well.
Place mixture into buttered 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Top with remaining cheese and bake for another 3 to 5 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving. Enjoy!

title: hot sauce
directions: Mix well.
To make hotter can be cooked slightly.
Otherwise, does not need cooking.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Use 1/3 cup mix per cup of hot water.

title: frosty orange jell-o
directions: Drain oranges, measuring and reserving liquid.
In a large serving bowl, add water to liquid to equal 2 c.
Dissolve jell-o in boiling water.
Add sherbet by spoonfuls, stirring until melted.
Add measured liquid.
Add Mandarin oranges.
Chill until set.
Makes about 10 c. or 16 servings.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray lasagna pan.
Boil chicken; remove from water and set aside to cool.
In same water, cook your noodles.
Leave them al dente since they will cook in the oven as well.
After the chicken cools, pull apart.
Mix the soup and tomatoes in a bowl.
When the noodles are done and the chicken is pulled apart, layer the ingredients in pan (noodles, chicken, onion, soup/tomatoes, cheese and chips).
Cook until heated through and cheese begins to brown (30 to 40 minutes).

title: white chocolate-macadamia nut cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
Cream margarine.
Add sugars gradually and beat until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla. Add dry ingredients and beat until well blended.
Stir in white chocolate chips, nuts and coconut.
Drop by teaspoons onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake in 375° oven for 9 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: fancy meatballs
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Mix ground beef with onion soup mix and form into 16 (1-inch) balls. Open rolls on a cutting board. Cut the 8 rolls down the middle, making 16 pieces. Press each one with palm of hand to flatten. Place meatball on wide side and roll up, bringing sides together. Put on greased cookie sheet and bake 13 minutes or until lightly browned. Serve with dipping sauce or other sauces!

title: escalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes in 350° oven in a 9 x 18-inch buttered pan.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add vanilla.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Add oats; mix well.
Chill dough.
Make into balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Place on cookie sheet; mash down.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: hobo dinner
directions: Make three layer casserole in a 9 x 13-inch pan lined with aluminum foil.

title: pickled beets
directions: Cook small young beets until tender.
Put in cool water and peel off skins.

title: log cake
directions: You will need a 9 x 13-inch pan, flat dish or tray.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix cherry pie filling, crushed pineapple and sugar.
Let sit overnight in the refrigerator.
Next day, add bananas, marshmallows and nuts.
Serve.

title: one-bowl devil's food cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 8 or 9-inch round cake pans or one 12 3/4 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cocoa into a medium size mixing bowl.
Add butter, milk and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed with an electric mixer or 300 strokes by hand.
Scrape sides of bowl often.
Add eggs and beat 2 minutes longer.
Pour batter into prepared pans.
Bake 8-inch cakes 35 to 40 minutes, 9-inch cakes 30 to 35 minutes and oblong cake 45 to 50 minutes until top springs back when lightly touched with finger.
Cool on wire cake racks 10 minutes before removing from pan.
Remove from pan and cool completely before frosting.
Use frosting of your choice.

title: veal parmigiano
directions: Pound veal with meat hammer or edge of heavy saucer.
Season with salt and pepper.
Beat egg and 1 tablespoon of water.
Dip veal in egg mixture, then in bread crumbs.
Brown in shortening (use more if necessary).
Arrange veal in shallow baking dish (12 x 8 x 2-inch).
Mix soup, water, onion, garlic and thyme; pour over veal.
Top with Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 39 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cook bacon first.
Then put bacon in with broccoli, red onion, raisins, mayonnaise and salt and pepper.
That is all to this. Oh, don't forget to mix the salad.
Serves 5 to 10.

title: peanut butter pate
directions: Cook and stir mushrooms in butter for 5 minutes.
Stir in lemon juice.
Remove from heat.
Beat cream cheese and peanut butter until fluffy.
Stir in mushrooms and cover.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Fry bacon until crisp; drain and crumble.
Shape cream cheese mixture into a ball.
Roll ball in bacon and onions; cover.
Refrigerate until serving time.

title: spicy coffee bars
directions: Cream brown sugar and shortening, then add 1 egg.
Mix well and add the coffee.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, salt, soda and cinnamon and stir into liquid.
Blend in raisins and nuts.
Spread in 9x13 greased baking pan and bake at 350 degrees 18-20 minutes.
Frost when cool if desired.

title: squash casserole
directions: Line bottom of casserole with squash.
Dice pimento on top. Toast and add to soup, milk, 1/2 cup almonds and grated onion. Pour over squash.
Top with crushed crackers and melted butter. Bake at 375° until brown.

title: "more"
directions: Slice potatoes and brown meat.
Layer all ingredients in a crock-pot.
Add all the liquid from the canned vegetables.
Cook until potatoes are done.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine until tender.
Add flour. Stir in broth; cook for 5 minutes.
Add cream of mushroom soup and cream; remove from heat.
Add turkey, mixing lightly.
Cook spaghetti according to directions.
Place spaghetti in bottom of 2-quart casserole dish.
Pour on turkey mixture, then top with cheese and bread crumbs mixed together.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: taco soup
directions: In a large Dutch oven or kettle, brown beef and onion. Add remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes.
May be put in crock-pot.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese and serve with tortilla chips, if desired.
Yields 10 servings.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into 3/4-inch balls and freeze until ready to use.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 400°.

title: artichoke pie
directions: Saute artichokes in garlic and olive oil.
In bowl, mix eggs and cheese.
Mix with sauteed artichokes.
Pour into pie shell, cover with another pie shell, put slits in top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: scalloped potatoes supreme
directions: Spread 4 cups sliced potatoes in bottom of greased baking dish. Combine remaining ingredients, 3/4 teaspoon salt and a dash of pepper.
Pour half mixture over potatoes.
Repeat layers and cover. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 30 to 35 minutes longer.
Serves 8.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix in medium saucepan.
Heat over medium heat until bubbling for 10 minutes.
Stir frequently.

title: easy egg roll wrapper lasagna
directions: Cook sausage; drain fat.
Add spaghetti sauce and simmer for 10 minutes.
Mix eggs and cottage cheese.
Shred or grind Mozzarella cheese.
In a pan, spread a little of meat sauce on the bottom, then spread egg roll wrappers in one layer; add 1/3 of meat sauce, 1/2 cottage cheese mixture and 1/3 of Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat one more time.
Spread one more layer of egg roll wrappers, meat sauce and Mozzarella cheese.
Sprinkle generous amount of Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fudge
directions: Combine sugar, butter, milk and Marshmallow Creme in a saucepan. Heat slowly to a boil, stirring frequently. When mixture boils vigorously, boil for 4 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Stir in chocolate chips until melted. Add vanilla and peanut butter. Add nuts. Mix well. Pour into buttered 9 x 9 pan. Cool. Makes approximately 3 pounds.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Parboil 1 head of cabbage.
Boil brown rice.
Roll rice into leaves of cabbage.
Pour one can of marinara sauce over pan of cabbage rolls.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: parmesan herb spread
directions: Combine all ingredients except bread; mix well.
Spread each slice with butter mixture.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream
butter
and
sugar; add egg yolks.
Add milk and flour alternately.
Mix
well
and fold in beaten egg whites. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
A wonderful holiday treat!

title: swedish nut cake
directions: Mix sugar, baking soda, 1/2 stick margarine, 1 teaspoon vanilla, eggs, flour, pineapple and walnuts together by hand. Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan with a little butter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Place chicken in baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Bake, covered, 15 minutes in preheated oven at 450°.
Combine all other ingredients except cheese; cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Top with cheese.
Bake 5 minutes, uncovered.
Garnish with parsley.
Serves 4.

title: cottage potatoes
directions: Cook unpeeled potatoes until nearly done.
Peel and slice into a large baking dish.
Add onion, green pepper, cheese, parsley and pimento.
Cover with milk and butter; top with cornflakes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 12 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix in order listed.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes in greased pans.
Makes 3 small loaves or 2 regular loaves. Fill pans 2/3 full.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix together and pour into two 9-inch skillets.
Bake at 350°.

title: vegetable burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients; form patties and grill.

title: combination inch salad
directions: Layer ingredients in order in large bowl with tight fitting lid.
Do not stir until ready to serve.
May be made overnight and stored in refrigerator.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: barbecue wimpies
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add other ingredients.
Cover. Simmer 30 minutes.
Serve on split buns.

title: apple-walnut cake
directions: Beat butter at medium speed with electric mixer until creamy. Gradually add 2 cups sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Stir in vanilla.
